label: fat
definition: Animals exhibit an increased girth compared to a control animal of the same developmental stage.

label: large
definition: Animals have increased girth and increased length compared to control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: small
definition: Animals are shorter and thinner than control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: thin
definition: Animals exhibit a reduced girth compared to a control animal of the same developmental stage.

label: sterile
definition: Animals generate defective gametes, are otherwise unable to reproduce or they generate progeny that are unable to reproduce.

label: long
definition: Animals are longer than control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: clear
definition: Animals appear unusually transparent when compared to control.

label: short
definition: Animals exhibit a decreased body length compared to control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: pale
definition: Animals show deficiencies in chroma resulting in increased translucency.

label: blistered
definition: Fluid-filled blisters appear on the cuticle.

label: hyperactive
definition: Worms move forward or backward with an increased rate of body bends per minute compared to control animals.

label: dauer sensory response variant
definition: Variations in the state or activity of a dauer stage organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus, compared to control.

label: enhanced acute pharyngeal pumping response to light
definition: Animals exhibit an enhanced acute pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that pharyngeal pumping rate decreases in response to light to a greater extent than in controls during the first 0-5 seconds after light exposure onset.

label: obsolete swollen male tail
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: actin cytoskeleton filament morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure, composition or arrangement of actin, an abundant cytoskeletal protein in most cells, often linked to the plasma membrane and concentrated at cell junctions compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: nickel toxicity resistant
definition: Animals fail to exhibit toxicity to the concentration of nickel that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans toxic responses to nickel include delayed development or lethality.

label: sheath cell secretion failure
definition: The regulated release of materials by sheath cells is disrupted.

label: excess pronucleus early emb
definition: There is either more than one maternal or paternal pronucleus in the inviable embryo.

label: male tail morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the somatic reproductive components of the posterior segment of the male from that observed in control males. In C. elegans, this region of the male includes the terminal canals of the reproductive tract, the digestive tract, and spicule channels along with the male specific sensilla (ray, post-cloacal, hook and spicule) and extends to the tip of the acellular fan.

label: astral microtubule asymmetry defective
definition: There is significantly less difference between the number of astral microtubles or other component(s) of the spindle microtuble organizing center at the anterior versus posterior poles of the spindle, than observed in control animals.

label: heme levels variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of heme compared to control animals. Heme is any compound of iron complexed in a porphyrin (tetrapyrrole) ring.

label: tail bend angle decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of the maximum flex of the most posterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: muscle system morphology variant
definition: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the muscle system, compared to control. The muscle system consists of tissues made up of various elongated cells that are specialized to contract and produce movement and mechanical work.

label: Bacillus thuringiensis toxin resistant
definition: Animals fail to be affected by toxins produced by Bacillus thuringiensis (Bt toxins) in the same manner as control animals.

label: pharyngeal muscle paralyzed
definition: Pharyngeal muscle is immobilized resulting in lack of pumping or lack of response to external stimulation.

label: evoked postsynaptic amplitude reduced
definition: The amplitudes of synaptic currents that are elicited by firing an action potential in a population of axons are decreased, compared to those observed in control animals.

label: acetylcholine metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving acetylcholine, compared to control. Acetylcholine is the acetic acid ester of the organic base choline.

label: EMS anterior extension fails early emb
definition: The EMS blastomere fails to extend anteriorly and make extensive contact (hug) with the ABa blastomere.

label: developmental timing variant
definition: The timing of specific developmental events in some tissues is altered relative to the timing of events in other tissues.

label: somatic cell death variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the programmed cell death pathway that is triggered in cells other than germ cells and that is not subject to upstream checkpoint regulation.

label: meiotic spindle positioning defective
definition: Cells undergoing meiosis exhibit defects in the positioning of the meiotic spindle.

label: meiosis variant
definition: Variations in the specialized nuclear and cytoplasmic divisions of a single diploid cell, whose specific outcome is the formation of four haploid daughter cells compared to control. Meiosis occurs during the formation of gametes.

label: multipolar neuron
definition: Neurons have more than one process extending from the cell body.

label: cell homeostasis metabolism variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways involved in the maintenance of a steady-state at the level of the cell compared to control.

label: gubernaculum morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the sclerotic cuticle that forms the roof of the proctodeum, from that observed in control animals.

label: no differentiated gametes
definition: Animals are agametic (lack mature germ cells).

label: cell division variant male
definition: Any variation that alters the physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells in male animals compared to control.

label: spicule protraction variant
definition: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of the male that are associated with the protraction of the male copulatory spicules compared to control.

label: 22G RNA expression reduced
definition: Animals exhibit lowered levels of any or all of the clades of 22G RNA molecules, compared to control.

label: maintenance of gene silencing variant
definition: Animals differ from controls in the expression of genes targeted for silencing (gene inactivation) in subsequent generations via transcriptional or post-transcriptional processes.

label: male physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required to carry out male-specific activities or to be able to perceive and respond to male-specific stimuli compared to control.

label: organism environmental stimulus response variant
definition: The response to a change in the environment is altered compared to control.

label: muscle dystrophy
definition: Progressive degeneration of muscle.

label: extra cell division postembryonic
definition: Animals execute supernumerary cell divisions post-hatching.

label: chemical resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of a specific chemical that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: aberrant posteriorly-directed neurite
definition: Any neurite that is extended towards the posterior of the animal from neurons that in wild-type animals make only anterior projections (e.g. D-type neurons in C. elegans).

label: alae secretion variant
definition: Variations in the regulated release of proteins needed for alae formation by epidermal seam cells compared to control. Alae are small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle, lengthwise along the body (WormAtlas).

label: neuron number variant
definition: The quantity of neuronal cells, as a whole or of a specific class of neuron in the animal deviates from that observed in control animals.

label: pattern antibody staining variant
definition: Any variation in the cellular or subcellular distribution of a gene product, as detected by antibody staining, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: reversed asynchrony early emb
definition: P1 divides before AB.

label: differential touch sensitivity variant
definition: Animals differ from control animals in response to mechanical stimulation targeting different parts of the same cell. In N2 wild-type animals, response to touch near the ALM cell body is reduced compared with touch of the cell area near the second pharyngeal bulb.

label: ventral ganglion development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion which lies ventrally beside the nerve ring in the head, just anterior of the retrovesicular ganglion over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: protein transport variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that modulate the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a protein into, out of, within or between cells by means of some external agent such as a transporter or pore compared to control.

label: embryonic cell morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the appearance of embryonic cells compared to control.

label: telomere morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the sequence or organization of the components of the terminal region of its chromosome, (i.e. telomere, which serves to stabilize the chromosome) compared to control.

label: organism segment behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of a certain body region of an animal in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: ammonium acetate chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to execute directed movement in response to ammonium acetate. In C. elegans, ammonium acetate is an attractant.

label: metaphase variant
definition: Any variation in the second stage of cell division, between prophase and anaphase, during which the chromosomes become attached to the spindle fibers.

label: spermatid activation defective
definition: Spermatids fail to mature into active sperm. In C. elegans round sessile spermatids mature into spermatozoa (polarized cells with a motile pseudopod), upon copulation or treatment with proteases.

label: head bent
definition: The most anterior portion of the animal is not aligned with the axis of the body.

label: neuromuscular junction organization variant
definition: The proper localization and assembly of components at the junction of a neuron with a muscle cell varies from that observed in control animals.

label: nonstriated muscle morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the nonstriated muscle compared to control animals.

label: RNA metabolism variant
definition: Variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of RNA in the organism compared to control.

label: catalysis variant
definition: Any variation in the catalysis of a biochemical reaction compared to control. Catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component).

label: no Intestine
definition: Embryos fail to generate cells that exhibit intestinal specification. In C. elegans, the E blastomere is the precursor of all the intestinal cells.

label: forward kinker
definition: Forward movement is often characterized by severe bending motions, more sharply angled and/or much deeper than stereotypical sinusoidal body bends of the control. Animal moves forward with uncharacteristic muscle spasms causing loss of smooth sinusoidal motion or body posture (Wormatlas).

label: ammonium chloride adaptation defective
definition: Animals do not exhibit characteristic chemoattractive desensitization to ammonium chloride in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control.

label: backing increased
definition: Animals spend more time backing compared to control animals.

label: cross link induced focus formation variant
definition: Variations in the generation of foci that mark sites of aberrant bonding of molecules to the DNA strand, compared to control.

label: excess fatty acids
definition: The concentration of fatty acids in the animal are greater than that observed for control animals.

label: clear larva
definition: Larva appear unusually transparent when compared to control.

label: active phase variant
definition: The active phase of egg-laying, the period during which animals are more likely to display multiple egg-laying events, is atypical compared with control animals, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: phasmid dye filling defect
definition: Animals exhibit defects in dye-filling of the neuronal cells of the phasmid sensilla. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling with FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: synaptic spike frequency variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the autonomously initiated periodic trains of calcium transients observed at the synapse, which are independent of presynaptic inputs.

label: conflicting sensory integration variant
definition: Animals behave differently from control animals in assays testing for the ability to resolve or respond to conflicting sensory inputs.

label: light touch habituation variant
definition: Any variation in the decreased behavioral response to repeated light head or tail touch compared to control. A gentle touch to the animal's head causes backward movement, whereas a gentle touch to the animal's tail causes forward movement. When wild-type animals are touched repeatedly on the head or tail, after some repetition they stop responding to the touch stimulus.

label: posterior reversed vulval lineage
definition: The orientation of the progeny of P7.p mimic those of P5.p and face towards the posterior of the worm, a phenotype referred to as posterior-reversed vulval lineage (P-Rvl).

label: bursa swollen
definition: The adult male tail, including the lateral fan and rays, appears bloated or distended.

label: touch resistant tail
definition: Failure to execute a characteristic response when struck or stroked in the posterior region. In C. elegans, animals move forward movement when struck or stroked in the posterior region, usually with a hair or similar fiber. The posterior region lies between the vulva and the tail.

label: general pace of development defective early emb
definition: Variations in the time from pronuclei meeting to furrow initiation during the first cell division compared to control animals.

label: paralyzed body
definition: All parts of the animal are immobilized except for the head.

label: obsolete no copper sensitivity
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: dauer pheromone secretion variant
definition: Animals produce pheromone but it does not undergo controlled release into the environment.

label: chloroquinone hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to chloroquinone at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: diplo X gamete
definition: Animals produce ova/sperm that contain 2 X chromosomes.

label: rays displaced
definition: Any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan are shifted from their customary place.

label: sodium acetate chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure in directed movement in response to sodium acetate. In C. elegans, sodium acetate is an attractant. Sodium acetate has also subsequently been used to assay for Na+ attraction in C. elegans.

label: sodium chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to sodium as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, sodium is typically an attractant.

label: forward locomotion increased
definition: Animals spend more time in forward locomotion, compared to control animals.

label: wing cilia axoneme morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the microtubule-based fibrillar section, axoneme, of the cilia of the flat sheet-like cells associated with sensory function, from that observed in control animals.

label: temperature learning variant
definition: Wild-type animals will exhibit an altered temperature preference based on food/temperature conditioning. Temperature learning variants do not exhibit altered responses to temperature after conditioning compared to control animals.

label: late paralysis arrested elongation two fold
definition: In C. elegans, movement and elongation stop nearly simultaneously soon after the twofold stage of elongation. However, mutant embryos twitch at the one-and-a-half-fold stage of elongation, like control animals, and move as well as control animals at the two- fold stage.

label: post male contact variant
definition: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of a hermaphrodite after male contact during mating compared to control.

label: left right handedness variant
definition: Any variation in the establishment of left-right asymmetry of the body axis compared to controls.

label: left handed roller
definition: The body of the animal rotates around its long axis as the animal moves, causing the animal to move in a circular pattern in the left-handed direction. In liquid media, wave propogation is helical rather than planar.

label: protein aggregation variant
definition: Variations that result in the accumulation of soluble/insoluble protein aggregates in a particular cell or tissue, compared to control. Protein aggregates are often formed by interactions between misfolded protein molecules and/or deficiencies in proper protein folding.

label: Pausing decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the amount of time spent in a paused state, which is neither moving forward or backward, compared to control animals.

label: obsolete semi sterile
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: germ cell mitosis variant
definition: Variations in the mitotic expansion of germ cell populations or in the appearance of nuclei during development in the premeiotic region of the germline compared to control.

label: alternative splicing defective
definition: The process of generating multiple mRNA molecules from differential use of exons in a primary transcript(s) does not occur or occurs with outcomes not observed in control animals.

label: translation variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a protein, compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the outcome of morphogenic processes required for formation or proper placement of sex-specific structures that distinguish the animal as a hermaphrodite in the population, from that observed for control hermaphrodites.

label: gonad small
definition: A decrease in size of the specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces the male or female gametes compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: male fertility reduced
definition: Males exhibit a reduction in the production of new individuals owing to defects in sperm competence and/or function compared to control animals.

label: commissure handedness defective
definition: Outgrowth of the commissure occurs on the side of the body different from that observed in control animals.

label: brood size variant
definition: The number of offspring produced is altered compared to that of control animals.

label: mitochondria alignment variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the parallel arrangement of mitochondria within a cell compared to control.

label: no gut granules
definition: Animals lack the different inclusions within the intestinal cytoplasm, including birefringent crystalline objects and other dark-staining endosomes. In C. elegans these contents typically include glycogen granules (polysaccharide storage), rhabditin (carbohydrate storage), yolk granules (lipid and protein), and concentrated waste products (Wormatlas).

label: fertilization defect male
definition: Failure of male-derived sperm to fuse with an oocyte during sexual reproduction.

label: alimentary system pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of the alimentary system.

label: somatic gonad physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the somatic gonad to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: bent posture variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in instantaneous posture with regards to eccentricity (measure of circularity) or the mean number (and/or standard deviation) of instantaneous body bends.

label: mRNA deadenylation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the extent to which polyadenylated mRNA transcripts become deadenylated

label: H lineages variant
definition: The descendants of H1 or H2 cells exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: neuron degeneration variant
definition: Any variation in the ability of neurons to undergo a dramatic decrease in cell volume, collapse of the vacuoles and processes, and complete disintegration of the plasma membrane and most organelles under conditions that ellicit this response in control animals.

label: supernumerary molt
definition: Animals execute extra larval molts compared to control.

label: amphid morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the neuronal cells of the amphid sensillum, from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling experiments using FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: level of protein expression variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the measured expression of a protein compared to that observed in control animals.

label: head movement decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the movement of the most anterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: XX lethal
definition: XX-bearing individuals die preferentially over other animals in the population. In C.elegans, XX animals die preferentially over X0 animals.

label: pericellular component physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process taking place in extracellular spaces within or associated with the organism, from that observed for control animals.

label: swimming induced paralysis
definition: Animals become paralyzed after a measured amount of time swimming. In C. elegans, more then 80 percent of wild-type animals continue swimming vigorously in liquid even after 30 minutes.

label: embryonic lethal late emb
definition: Animals die during the final stages of embryogenesis. In C. elegans, this lethality refers to death during the last (3-fold) stage of embryogenesis, which normally occurs 620-800 min after the first cleavage at 20C, the stage after elongation.

label: thermophilic
definition: Animals tend to track and stay within high temperature environments.

label: germline nuclear positioning variant
definition: Variations in the directed movement/or positioning of a nucleus to a specific location within the germline compartment compared to control.

label: uptake of yolk defective
definition: Yolk is not taken up by oocytes in the same manner or to the same degree as observed for control animals. This often leads to an accumulation of yolk in the pseudocoelom.

label: masculinized
definition: Animals that are not ordinarily male, exhibit male-specific attributes. In C. elegans, XX animals exhibit male-specific attributes.

label: pharynx length increased
definition: Animals have an increase in the distance between most anterior and the most posterior ends of the pharynx from that observed in control animals.

label: protein modification variant
definition: Variations in the covalent alteration of one or more amino acids occurring in proteins, peptides and nascent polypeptides (co-translational, post-translational modifications), compared to control. This includes the modification of charged tRNAs that are destined to occur in a protein (pre-translation modification).

label: head bend angle increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of the maximum flex of the most anterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: calcium signaling pharynx variant
definition: Any variation in the series of molecular signals in which a pharyngeal cell uses calcium ions to convert an extracellular signal into a response, compared to control.

label: golgi apparatus morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as the Golgi apparatus, that traffic material from the endoplasmic reticulum or various endosomes, and process proteins for secretion, compared to control.

label: organism morphology variable
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts at different stages of the lifecycle, compared to control animals.

label: vulval cell induction reduced
definition: Vulval precursor cells receive a decrease in inductive signal leading to fewer VPCs adopting vulval fates compared to control animals.

label: systemic RNAi variant
definition: Animals are defective for RNAi introduced by environmental means such as in the cases of RNAi triggered by soaking or feeding.

label: mRNA expression ectopic
definition: Any variation that results in the cellular expression of an mRNA in cells/tissues, that is otherwise not observed in control animals.

label: sexually dimorphic behavior variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in sex-specific behaviors compared to control.

label: osmotic stress response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the response to osmotic stress compared to control. In C. elegans, exposure to stress-inducing osmotic conditions invokes cellular changes, including transcriptional up or down-regulation of genes.

label: drug response variant
definition: Any variation in the characteristic response(s) to drug(s) as defined by control animals.

label: deirid sensillum morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the sensilla situated laterally in the anterior (ADE) or the posterior (PDE) of the animal compared to control. In C. elegans, each of the 4 deirid sensilla (2ADE, 2 PDE) contains a pair of neurons with ciliated dendritic processes that lie in a channel formed by a socket cell and invaginated sheath cell. The cilia of the deirids terminate in the subcuticle and are not exposed to the outside; however occasionally take up FITC.

label: repetitive transgene expression increased
definition: Animals exhibit increased expression of repetitive exogenous DNA compared to control.

label: tail rounded
definition: Tails change shape and undergo retraction thereby forming a 'peloderan' or 'rounded' adult tail.

label: cytoskeleton organization biogenesis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure, composition or arrangement of any of the various filamentous elements that form the internal framework of cells, compared to control. The various elements of the cytoskeleton not only serve in the maintenance of cellular shape but also have roles in other cellular functions, including cellular movement, cell division, endocytosis, and movement of organelles.

label: reduced protein oxidation levels
definition: Protein oxidation levels, as measured by carbonylated protein levels for example, are reduced compared to controls.

label: octopamine deficient
definition: Animals do not contain or are unable to maintain a perceivable level of octopamine capable of initiating or maintaining dopamine-dependent cell activity.

label: pronuclei meet centrally early emb
definition: The maternal and paternal pronuclei meet more centrally instead of meeting in the posterior end of the embryo.

label: extended life span
definition: The duration of viability in the adult phase of the life-cycle surpasses that of control animals.

label: pore forming toxin hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to pore forming toxins at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. Increased susceptibility to pore forming toxins (e.g. Cry5B from Bacillus thuringiensis) is often measured by a decrease in the rate of survival in the presence of pore forming toxins compared to controls.

label: anal depressor contraction defect
definition: Animals fail to contract the anal depressor muscle.

label: light response variant
definition: Variations in the state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a light stimulus (electromagnetic radiation of wavelengths classified as infrared, visible or ultraviolet light) compared to control.

label: cilia length increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the length of the microtubule-based dendritic projections extending from the cell body, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism osmostic stress hypersensitive
definition: Animals exhibit hypersensitivty to osmotic stress compared to that observed in control animals.

label: late endosome morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as late endosomes,  that traffic material from early endosomes to internal compartments of the cell, such as lysosomes or the Golgi apparatus, compared to control.

label: delayed hatching
definition: The emergence of larvae from their protective egg shells is retarded compared to control animals.

label: weak pumping
definition: The contraction and relaxation movements of the pharyngeal muscle that mediate feeding is not as robust as compared to control animals.

label: alpha amanitin hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to alpha amanitin at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: cell position defective early emb
definition: Cell position is abnormal in the early embryo.

label: serotonin resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of serotonin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: lumbar ganglia development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the left and right lumbar ganglia which lie behind the pre-anal ganglion in the tail, in lateral positions over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: centrosome pair and associated pronuclear rotation variant
definition: Any variation in the rotation of the centrosome-pronuclear complex after its migration toward the center of the embryo, compared to control.

label: kinetochore organization variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the assembly, arrangement, orientation, or disassembly of the kinetochore, a multisubunit protein complex on chromosomes where the spindle fibers attach during cell division to pull the chromosomes apart.

label: organism physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the organism to carry out its normal function or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli.

label: spermatozoa retro location defective
definition: Spermatozoa do not crawl back into the spermatheca after being swept into the uterus by passing oocytes.

label: genotoxic induced apoptosis variant
definition: Programmed cell death of germ cells caused by exposure to DNA-damaging chemical agents does not occur to the same extent as it does in control animals.

label: cephalic sensillum morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of a specialized sensory organ in the head that contains a CEP receptor neuron, compared to control. In C. elegans, cells in these organs are refractory to FITC dye uptake.

label: mitochondrial stress response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to mitochondrial stress, compared to controls.

label: distal tip cell morphology variant
definition: The morphological appearance of distal tip cells is varied compared to control animals.

label: egg laying imipramine resistant
definition: Animals are not induced to lay eggs in reponse to exogenous imipramine. In C. elegans, imipramine stimulates egg-laying.

label: arsenic hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to arsenic at a lower concentration or at a shorter exposure time compared to control animals.

label: polar body reabsorbed one two early emb
definition: A polar body is reabsorbed in either the one cell- or the two-cell embryo.

label: magnesium hypersensitivity
definition: Animals exhibit an exaggerated response to magnesium compared to control animals exposed to similar concentrations.

label: glycogen levels variant
definition: Any variation in the levels of the polymerized form of glucose throughout the body of the animal as compared to controls.

label: body wall muscle cell spindle development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the region of a body wall muscle cell that contains the myofilament lattice (adjacent to the hypodermis) over time, from its initial state to the fully differentiated state compared to control.

label: cell death variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any of the processes that lead to the termination of vital functions of a cell.

label: dorsal nerve cord development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the anatomical structures that consist of processes of ventral cord motor neurons that send commissures to the dorsal side, as well as processes of certain head and tail neurons, over time from initial formation to mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: flaccid
definition: A semi-paralysed body phenotype in which muscle tone is lost and the animal fails to actively control its body shape (Wormatlas).

label: dauer arrest variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the entry/exit into a state of arrested tissue development during the dauer larval stage in response to harsh environmental conditions, compared to control. In C. elegans, the dauer larva enters a state of arrest in which no developmental changes occur, until the animal finds more suitable growing conditions, or until it spontaneously shifts back into a normal developmental schedule. (WormAtlas).

label: extra and ectopic cell
definition: Animals have one or more extra cells of a particular type, which are present in places they are normally not found, when compared to the number and location of these cells in control animals.

label: missing gonad arms
definition: Animals are missing one or both gonad arms, the normally U-shaped projections of the gonad that extend into the anterior or posterior of the animal and bends back towards the center of the animal.

label: P1 aster defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the array of microtubules emanating from a spindle pole that do not connect to kinetochores in the P1 cell.

label: VPC competence variant
definition: Any variation in the ability of multipotent vulval precursor cells to respond to signals compared to control animals.

label: socket cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a socket cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: fluoride resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of fluoride ions that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to fluoride ions to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: spindle position orientation defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the placement or the alignment of the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis.

label: low incidence male progeny
definition: Lower numbers of male progeny occur in the population compared to control populations. In C. elegans, the low incidence of males phenotype in a self-fertilizing hermaphrodite population is a result of an decrease in X chromosome nondisjunction.

label: axon vesicle variant
definition: Axons of animals exhibit variations in the gross structure or organization of its spherical, membrane-bound, fluid-filled organelles, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: trimethylthiazole chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of trimethylthiazole. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, trimethylthiazole is an attractant.

label: mitochondria localization variant
definition: The subcellular localization of mitochondrial organelles differ from that observed in control cells.

label: serotonin reuptake inhibitor resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of serotonin reuptake inhibitors that elicit a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: induced pharyngeal pumping variant
definition: Pharyngeal pumping is not influenced by treatment with specific compounds (eg: serotonin) in the same manner as control animals.

label: extra linker cells
definition: Animals produce an excess number of linker cells compared to controls.

label: organism crowding response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a situation when there is too high a density of nematodes to be supported by the available amount of food and space compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: organism high sodium chloride hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to sodium chloride at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. In C. elegans, this is often assayed through generation time and progeny number.

label: excretory gland cell morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a pair of large cells in the head that fuse to form a single gland whose contents are released into the excretory duct through a specialized secretory membrane, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: neuron activation variant
definition: Activity of the neuron varies from that observed for control animals or neurons. In C. elegans neuron activity is often assayed by observing calcium spikes.

label: protein secretion variant
definition: Variations in the regulated release of proteins from a cell or group of cells compared to control.

label: locomotion rate serotonin resistant
definition: Animals fail to decrease their locomotion rate in response the concentration of serotonin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: organ system morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any component that is part of the complement of organ tissues that comprise a specific organ system.

label: odorant positive chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to move towards attractive volatile organic molecules. In C. elegans, these compounds are sensed by the AWA and AWC neurons.

label: cloacal structures protrude
definition: Any of the contents that comprise the epithelial chamber that links the genital and alimentary tracts to the exterior via the anus extend into the external environment through the cloacal opening.

label: wing cilia morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the microtuble-based projections that in control animals invaginate individually into the sheath cell of the neuronal sensillum rather than projecting through the socket cell to the outside. In C. elegans, the cilia of each wing cell has its own unique shape and as they are not exposed to the outside, they do not typically take up dyes.

label: reduced brood size
definition: The characteristic number of offspring produced is lower compared to that of control animals.

label: potassium chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to potassium. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure of the animals to move towards potassium.

label: pharynx extension defective
definition: Embryos exhibit defects in the extension of pharyngeal cells toward the buccal opening during embryogenesis compared to controls.

label: meiotic chromosome organization variant
definition: Any variation in the process of chromosome organization that is involved in meiosis, compared to control.

label: obsolete oocyte germ cell differentiation abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: radiation induced germ cell apoptosis resistant
definition: Programmed cell death of germ cells caused by exposure to ionizing energy does not occur to the same extent as it does in control animals.

label: loss of asymmetry ASE
definition: The two morphologically bilaterally symmetric gustatory neurons ASE left (ASEL) and ASE right (ASER) fail to undergo a left/right asymmetric diversification in cell fate.

label: diacetyl chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of diacetyl. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, diacetyl is an attractant.

label: RNAi transport defective
definition: Animals are deficient in the transport of silencing RNAs between cells during the systemic RNAi response process.

label: transgene expression reduced hermaphrodite
definition: Any decrease in the intensity of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA, exclusively in the hermaphrodite, that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: starvation induced apoptosis variant
definition: Any variation in the amount of cells undergoing apoptosis in organism as a result of deprivation of nourishment, compared to control. In C. elegans, starvation normally causes increased apoptosis.

label: thermotolerance reduced
definition: Animals are not able to survive at temperatures above standard cultivation temperatures to the same extent as control animals.

label: dauer pheromone sensation defective
definition: Animals fail to detect a pheromone stimulus that induces dauer formation in control animals.

label: L1 lethal
definition: Animals die at the L1 stage of the life cycle.

label: excretory socket cell development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of an interfacial epithelial cell which links excretory duct to hypodermis, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: sex muscle development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the muscles of the adult reproductive system over time form their initial formation to their mature structure compared to control.

label: synapsis defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the stabilization of homologue pairing, which occurs through the initiation and formation of the synaptonemal complex, during meiosis.

label: egg pale
definition: Eggs show deficiencies in chroma resulting in increased translucency.

label: male tail curling serotonin variant
definition: Any variation in the posture of the male tail after application of exogenous serotonin compared to control. In C. elegans, males respond with a tight ventral curling of the male tail in response to serotonin.

label: uterus morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the portion of the somatic gonad which encloses the fertilized eggs after their passage through the spermatheca compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: precocious cell fusion
definition: Two or more individual cells form a syncytium (a mass of cytoplasm containing several nuclei enclosed within a single plasma membrane) via the fusion of the plasma membranes at an earlier stage of development compared to comparable cells in control animals.

label: path curvature decreased
definition: Animals exhibit decreases in the extent to which the overall path of movement is curved, producing shallower, less frequent curves and an overall straighter path, compared to control animals.

label: P lineages variant
definition: The descendants of any of the P precursor cells exhibit variations in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: intraflagellar transport distance short
definition: The bidirectional transport of molecules (cargo) along axonemal microtubules is reduced compared to control.

label: small RNA somatic expression variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations from controls in the expression, biogenesis, processing, or stability of any class of small RNA species in somatic cells. Small RNAs include microRNAs (miRNAs), tiny noncoding RNAs (tncRNAs), cluster of small X-chromosome derived RNAs (X cluster), and endogenous short interfering RNA (endo-siRNAs).

label: cyclic nucleotide positive chemotaxis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic movement towards cyclic nucleotides compared to control.

label: pre hermaphrodite contact variant
definition: Males exhibit variations in mating behavior prior to contacting its mate compared to control.

label: short range axon migration variant
definition: Animals exhibit axons with migration behaviors that differ from those observed in control animals before the axons reach a half-way point between opposing neural cords. In C. elegans this point is marked by the lateral seam cells between the ventral and dorsal cords.

label: clear adult
definition: Adult animals appear unusually transparent when compared to control.

label: microsatellite instability
definition: Animals exhibit variations in repeat lengths of microsatellite genomic sequences compared to control.

label: benzaldehyde chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to benzaldehyde as defined by control animals. In C.elegans benzaldehyde is typically attractive.

label: movement variant
definition: Variations in the process by which an organism travels from one location to another compared to control.

label: protein expression variant
definition: Variations in the biogenesis and stability of protein molecules compared to control.

label: larval growth variant
definition: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) during the larval stages compared to control animals.

label: diakinesis progression during oogenesis variant
definition: Developing oocytes show defects in their entry, progression through or exit from the diakinesis stage compared to control animals. Diakinesis is a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the final stage of prophase I in meiosis; the transition to meiotic metaphase I.

label: intraflagellar transport defective
definition: Bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum is disrupted.

label: neuropeptide processing variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways involved in the formation and maturation of specialized peptidergic neurotransmitters encoded as preproproteins that are posttranslationally processed to yield bioactive neuropeptides compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: exaggerated body bends
definition: The maximum ventral and dorsal flex of the animal is greater than that observed for control animals.

label: mRNA export variant
definition: Any variation in the export of mRNA from the cell nucleus compared to control.

label: muscle attachment variant
definition: Any variation in the connection of the cell(s) whose principal function is to provide contractile forces with its neighboring cells or tissues compared to control.

label: mitotic chromosome segregation variant
definition: Any variation in the cell cycle process whereby replicated homologous chromosomes are organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two sets during the mitotic cell cycle compared to control animals.

label: starvation-induced L1 arrest recovery abnormal
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the recovery from L1 larvae developmental arrest in response to a lack of food (starvation) available in the environment.

label: sperm transfer defective
definition: Any defect in the process whereby a male inseminates his partner by introducing sperm into the genital tract.

label: radial filament structure variant pharynx
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of radial arrangement of actin within the pharyngeal muscle compared to control animals.

label: track length variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the length of the minimum enclosing rectangle surrounding the worm body on a solid medium, as viewed through the microscope.

label: anus development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the caudal opening of the rectum in the tail over time compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: mitochondrial respiratory chain variant
definition: The activity, composition, or organization of the complexes of the electron transport chain, embedded in the inner mitochondrial membrane, differ from controls.

label: germ cell compartment expansion variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the increase in size of compartments of the germline. In the C. elegans germline, syncytial compartments enlarge just prior to and coincident with the loop region, eventually abscising, to become fully enclosed germ cells (oocytes).

label: thermoreceptor currents absent
definition: Cooling or warming evoked changes in membrane currents are not observed.

label: uterine vulval cell development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the epithelial cells that form the interface between the uterus and the vulva (likely via a multilayered set of flaps) over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: anesthetic response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific anesthetic compared to that observed in control animals.

label: obsolete heterochronic defect
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: early larval lethal
definition: Animals die during early larval development. In C.elegans, this occurs during the L1- L2 larval stages of the life cycle.

label: no expulsion defecation
definition: Animals lack the stereotyped muscle contractions that result in the opening of anus.

label: late endosome localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as late endosomes,  that traffic material from early endosomes to internal compartments of the cell, such as lysosomes or the Golgi apparatus, compared to control.

label: complex phenotype early emb
definition: Population of unhatched eggs exhibit a complex combination of defects that do not match other class definitions.

label: marginal cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit deviations at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell, in any physical or chemical process required for a marginal cell to carry out its normal function and activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli.

label: anterior region development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of an animal's anatomy contained in the anterior region over time, compared to control animals.

label: rachis wide
definition: The width of the nucleus-free core of germline cytoplasm in the gonad is larger compared to control animals.

label: coelomocyte uptake increased
definition: Animals exhibit intensified accumulation of fluids or fluorescent markers etc. within their coelomocytes compared to control animals.

label: dauer cephalic sensillum variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of a specialized sensory organ in the head that contains a CEP receptor neuron, compared to control. In C. elegans, cells in these organs are refractory to FITC dye uptake.

label: male reproductive longevity extended
definition: Males continue to sire progeny significantly past the time reproduction stops in control animals or show a slower decline in mating efficiency compared to age-matched control males.

label: protein RNA interaction abolished
definition: Animals lack a specific protein-RNA interaction observed in control animals.

label: dauer lifespan extended
definition: The life span of dauer-staged animals is longer than that observed in control dauer animals.

label: fat content reduced
definition: Animals exhibit less fat or lipid than observed in control animals.

label: hydrogen sulfide hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to hydrogen sulfide at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: hypodermal cell elongation defective
definition: During epidermal morphogenesis, hypodermal cells do not properly undergo the characteristic cell shape changes necessary for the embryo to elongate.

label: germ cell development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the immature germ cell over time, from its formation from precursors to the mature structure (gamete) compared to control.

label: forward point velocity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the velocity of forward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: muscle system development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the muscle system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: ciliated neuron morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any one of the specialized sensory receptor cells of the nervous system that compared to control animals. In C. elegans, these specialized cells are characterized as having axoneme containing dendritic projections emanating from their cell body.

label: male copulatory structure absent
definition: Animals lack the specialized structures of the male tail which allow the animal to sense the presence of the hermaphrodite, search her body for the vulval opening, grasp onto the vulva, and to transfer sperm (Wormatlas).

label: male mating efficiency eliminated
definition: Males sire no cross progeny.

label: body elongation defective
definition: The epidermal cells of the embryo fail to elongate. In C. elegans, this elongation occurs along an anterior-posterior axis, which is required to transform the bean-shaped embryo into the elongated shape of the worm.

label: polar body size defective early emb
definition: Polar body size is abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: maternal effect lethal emb
definition: Lethality caused by the perturbation of maternal gene products that are contributed to oogenesis and are required during embryogenesis.

label: endosome localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as endosomes,  that traffic material between the plasma membrane and internal compartments of the cell, compared to control.

label: posterior pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency of the posterior body axis compared to control.

label: fat associated bodies increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the number of fat containing organelles compared to control. In C. elegans this number can be assayed by increases in the number of BODIPY 493/503 staining.

label: posterior body thin
definition: The posterior part of the worm exhibits a reduced girth compared to a control animal of the same developmental stage.

label: heparan sulfate biosynthesis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of the heparan sulfate proteoglycan compared to control.

label: pathogen adherence increased
definition: Pathogens exhibit increased adherence to the surface of host animals.

label: protein carbonylation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the covalent modification of one or more native amino acid side chains in proteins to carbonyl derivatives such as an aldehyde or ketone.

label: peptide uptake by intestinal cell decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the degree to which an intestinal cell is able to uptake peptides (for example, di- or tripeptides) from the intestinal lumen, compared to control animals.

label: expulsion variant
definition: Any variation in the expulsion of gut contents compared to control. In C. elegans, this refers to the final step of the defecation cycle in which the intestinal muscle and anal depressor contractions further pressurize intestinal contents and open the anus to permit expulsion.

label: P0 spindle rotation delayed early emb
definition: P0 spindle rotates late in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: positive chemotaxis defective
definition: Variations in the movement towards typically attractive chemicals.

label: connective tissue morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form, structure or composition of the material made up of fibers forming a framework and support structure for body tissues and organs compared to control.

label: cell organization biogenesis variant
definition: Variations in the process(es) involved in the assembly and arrangement of cell structures compared to control.

label: L3 L4 molt defect
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates L3 to L4 transition.

label: fat associated bodies variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the formation or disassembly of fat containing organelles compared to control.

label: dorsal coiler
definition: A coiling body that bends dorsally.

label: rhythmic behavior variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in actions or responses that occur with measurable periodicity, from that observed for control animals.

label: canal lumen morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the internal space of the excretory canal compared to control animals.

label: body elongation retracted
definition: Embryos retract after the embryonic elongation process.

label: protein aggregation induced behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions in response to external or internal stimuli in response to the aggregation of proteins.

label: egg round
definition: The overall structure or appearance of fertilized oocytes that are laid has every part of their surface equidistant from the center.

label: motor neuron morphology variant
definition: Animals display variations in the structure or organization of components of the motor neuron, internal to the cell itself or in relation to the cellular environment compared to that observed in control animals. A motor neuron is a neuronal cell that synapses to an effector (muscle, gland etc.).

label: growth defective on low phosphate media
definition: Animals are unable to grow on media depleted of phosphate.

label: nucleus reforms cell division remnant early emb
definition: After division of either one-cell or two-cell embryos, the nuclei reappear next to the cell division remnant.

label: cell corpse number decreased
definition: Animals exhibit fewer cell corpses compared to controls at the same developmental life stage.

label: male posterior alae
definition: Males have alae that extend into the tail region. Alae are small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle. In C. elegans alae do not extend into the tail region (Wormatlas).

label: pericellular component development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of structures/tissues surrounding a cell over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control.

label: P0 spindle absent early emb
definition: No mitotic spindle is seen in P0.

label: glycation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the non-enzymatic glycosylation process of attaching a protein or lipid to a sugar molecule, compared to control animals.

label: drug hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to a specific drug at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: accessory cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of an accessory cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control. An accessory cell supports sensory neurons.

label: phagosome maturation defective
definition: Early phagosomes fail to undergo the maturation process following the ingestion of particulate material by phagocytosis; During maturation, phagosomes acquire markers of late endosomes and lysosomes.

label: L2 larval development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the second larval stage compared to control.

label: distal tip cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the leader cell that guides and shapes the outgrowth of the gonad while crawling along the body wall to force the germline to extend into a long tubular shape over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control.

label: body levamisole resistant
definition: The bodies of animals fail to respond to the concentration of levamisole that elicits a response in control animals.

label: AWA odorant chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of an animal in response to a volatile chemical stimulus that is usually received and processed by the AWA sensory neuron in control animals.

label: no polar body formation
definition: Animals lack the two small cells produced, each during one of the two meiotic cell divisions (Wormatlas).

label: ectopic expression transgene
definition: Any variation in the cellular expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism such that it now expresses in cells/tissues not seen when compared to the expression of that gene product in control animals.

label: chromatin modification variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the nature and/or extent of chromatin modification, including but not limited to acetylation and/or methylation of histones, compared to controls.

label: apoptosis reduced
definition: Any perturbation that causes a decrease in the frequency of cell death by apoptosis compared to control animals.

label: trimethylthiazole chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute characteristic response to trimethylthiazole compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of trimethylthiazole.

label: metal accumulation increased
definition: Animals exhibited higher amounts of internal metal concentrations compared to control animals.

label: asymmetric chromosome segregation
definition: Chromosomes are not segregated symmetrically during mitosis.

label: neuron morphology variant
definition: Animals display variations in the structure or organization of components of the neuronal cell internal to the cell itself or in relation to the cellular environment compared to control. A neuron is a major cell type of nervous tissue specialized for transmission of information in the form of patterns of impulses.

label: organelle fusion defective
definition: The formation of mature intracellular compartments via membrane fusion is disrupted.

label: muscle excess
definition: Animals exhibit a greater number of embryonic muscle cells compared to control.

label: isoflurane resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of the volatile anesthetic isoflurane that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: organism behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of an organism in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control organisms.

label: granules cytoplasm
definition: Animals accumulate an excess of vesicle-like structures in cells.

label: pharynx slippery
definition: Failure of pharyngeal contractions to trap and transport bacteria posteriorly. In C. elegans this defect results in a distention of the pharyngeal lumen.

label: mating latency increased
definition: Any increase in the length of time required for a male to find a mate and initiate the search for the vulva. In C. elegans, the latency period includes the time males spend to find a hermaphrodite and pause to press its ventral side against the surface of the hermaphrodite and initiate a backing up search for the vulva.

label: fertility variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the time of onset or duration of the fertile period, or production of new individuals that contain some portion of their genetic material inherited from that organism compared to control.

label: chemosensory behavior variant
definition: Variations in behavior that is dependent upon the sensation of chemicals, compared to control.

label: hydrogen peroxide homeostasis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in steady-state levels of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite behavior variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in hermaphrodite-specific behaviors compared to control.

label: protruding vulva
definition: Animals undergo incomplete vulval morphogenesis, resulting in the formation of a single protrusion at the site of the vulva.

label: second messenger mediated signaling variant
definition: Any variation in a series of molecular signals that help relay a receptor mediated signal within the cell, compared to control. Second messengers often comprise of ions (eg: Ca2+) or small molecules (cGMP, cAMP etc) that are formed or released into the cytosol.

label: growth arrest response to 5 FU resistant
definition: Animals grow well during or after exposure to 5-FU under conditions where control animals are growth inhibited.

label: sodium acetate chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of sodium acetate. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, sodium acetate is an attractant. Sodium acetate has also been used to assay for Na+ attraction.

label: regenerative axonal fusion defective
definition: Following axon damage, animals do not undergo axonal fusion after reconnection between the regrowing axon and its separated segment to the same extent as observed in control animals.

label: pathogen induced death increased
definition: Animals are more prone to lethality as a result of infection compared to control.

label: cell number increased
definition: The number of cells in the organism is increased compared to control animals.

label: cytoplasmic morphology defective early emb
definition: Morphology of the cytoplasm differs from control animals.

label: obsolete severe dumpy
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: germ cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of germ cells compared to control animals.

label: fat associated bodies reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the number of fat containing organelles compared to control. In C. elegans this number can be assayed by decreases in the number of Nile Red or BODIPY 493/503 staining bodies.

label: intestinal morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the chain of cuboidal cells which form a central lumen lined by microvilli that allow the passage of food, compared to control. Food passes from the posterior pharynx to the intestine where it is digested and then on to the rectum which processes the waste products for excretion (Wormatlas).

label: axon length abnormal
definition: The length of one or more axons is abnormal compared to the length of the corresponding axon(s) in control animals.

label: anticonvulsant response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific anticonvulsant compared to that observed in control animals.

label: morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts compared to control animals.

label: oocyte physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the oocyte to carry out its normal functions or activities, compared to control animals.

label: amplitude of sinusoidal movement increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of a vibratory movement (as a worm bend) measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control.

label: pharyngeal relaxation defective
definition: Defects in rhythmic pharyngeal relaxations compared to control animals. In C. elegans pharyngeal relaxation follows a contraction event and facilitates bacterial trapping within the pharynx while expelling liquid.

label: nonanone chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to nonanone compared to control. In C. elegans, nonanone is a repellant.

label: acquired thermotolerance variant
definition: Animals are altered in their capacity to survive a normally lethal temperature treatment as a consequence of pretreatment at an elevated but sublethal temperature.

label: stress induced arrest variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in cessation of development when exposed to stress stimuli that induce developmental arrest in control animals.

label: cortical dynamics defective early emb
definition: Little/no cortical ruffling or pseudocleavage furrow, or excessive cortical activity. In C. elegans, this is often characterized at the two-cell stage.

label: dendrite development variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that influence the generation of neuronal extensions, that carry afferent (incoming) action potentials towards the cell body compared to control.

label: neuronal ion channel clustering defective
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the targeting, clustering and or maintenance of ion channels in distinct subcellular domains of the neuron compared to control animals.

label: male sterile
definition: X0 animals fail to generate viable cross-progeny.

label: tail bobbed
definition: Swelling of the tail hypodermis resulting in a prematurely-truncated and thickened appearance of the tail. In C. elegans, this is usually applies to hermaphrodites.

label: cold hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond more severely to cold than control animals subjected to the same cold conditions.

label: calcium mediated signaling variant
definition: Any variation in the series of molecular signals in which a cell or tissue uses calcium ions to convert a signal into a response, compared to control.

label: gut granule development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the different inclusions within the intestinal cytoplasm, including birefringent crystalline objects and other dark-staining endosomes over time compared to control. In C. elegans these contents might include glycogen granules (polysaccharide storage), rhabditin (carbohydrate storage), yolk granules (lipid and protein), and concentrated waste products (Wormatlas).

label: other abnormality early emb
definition: Unclassified abnormality in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: bitter tastant response variant
definition: Animals are not repelled by bitter tastants such as quinine, primaquine quinacrine etc., to the same extent as control animals.

label: levamisole response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of levamisole compared to that observed in control animals. Levamisole is a cholinergic agonist.

label: zinc toxicity hypersensitive
definition: The toxic response to zinc occurs at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. In C. elegans hypersensitive animals exhibit delayed development or lethality at concentrations of zinc (e.g. ZnSO4), which has little or no effect on control worms.

label: GABA synaptic transmission variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the process of GABA neurotransmitter-based communication from a neuron to a target cell across a synapse compared to control.

label: dauer deirid sensillum variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the sensilla situated laterally in the anterior (ADE) or the posterior (PDE) of the animal compared to control. In C. elegans, each of the 4 deirid sensilla (2ADE, 2 PDE) contains a pair of neurons with ciliated dendritic processes that lie in a channel formed by a socket cell and invaginated sheath cell. The cilia of the deirids terminate in the subcuticle and are not exposed to the outside; however occasionally take up FITC.

label: high oxygen resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the high concentrations of oxygen that elicit a response in control animals.

label: protein interaction variant
definition: Variations in the selective and non-covalent physical association between two or more proteins, or a protein and nucleic acid/macromolecular complex, compared to control.

label: thermotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific temperature gradient compared to control.

label: organism UV hypersensitive
definition: Organisms respond to UV at a lower dose or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: obsolete No variantity scored
definition: OBSOLETE. Phenotypic examination of worms did not reveal an obvious abnormality compared with control animals.

label: backward point velocity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the velocity of backward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: swollen intestine
definition: The intestinal lumen is expanded and can often be shown to be filled with bacteria.

label: ooplasmic streaming slow
definition: The bulk flow of cytoplasm in the egg, that facilitates mixing of ooplasm, occurs at a reduced rate compared to that measured for controls.

label: germ cell compartment anucleate
definition: Germ cell compartments do not contain a nucleus.

label: hypersensitivity to mutagen
definition: Animals are more susceptible than control animals to the effects of a nucleic acid damaging agent. This increased susceptibility is often measured by an increase in the rate of spontaneous mutations or an increased lethality.

label: microtubule polymerization variant
definition: Any variation that alters the characteristic addition of tubulin heterodimers to one or both ends of a microtubule compared to control.

label: ectopic hypodermis
definition: Animals exhibit one or more hypodermal cells in locations not normally found in controls.

label: K lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the K precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: coelomic system development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the coelomic system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: no adult cuticle
definition: Adult animals lack the rigid external coating which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells (Wormatlas).

label: foraging reduced
definition: Animals decrease intensity or rate of roaming and or dwelling activity compared to control animals.

label: hatching variant
definition: Variations in the ability of an animal to emerge from the protective egg shell compared to control animals.

label: head muscle behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the head muscles in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: vulval muscle extension variant
definition: Any variation in the extension of vulval muscles compared to control.  In C. elegans contralateral vulval muscles fail to meet at the midline.

label: Z4 hermaphrodite lineage variant
definition: Z4 descendants exhibit altered developmental programs in the hermaphrodite compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: cell adhesion variant
definition: Any variation in the attachment of a cell, either to another cell or to an underlying substrate such as the extracellular matrix compared to control.

label: defecation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the processes involved in eliminating gut contents compared to control animals. In C. elegans the sequence of events during defecation includes posterior body contraction (pBoc), relaxation, anterior body contraction (aBoc), expulsion of gut contents by enteric muscle contraction (Emc) and opening of anus (Exp), and intercycle period (Wormatlas).

label: dauer nose morphology variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of the extreme anterior part of their body compared to control.

label: paraquat response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to paraquat compared to that observed in control animals.

label: maternal effect morphology variant
