definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of any part of an animal caused by the perturbation of maternal gene products that are contributed to oogenesis and are required during embryogenesis.

label: male fan morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the flattened structure extending laterally at the extreme tip of the adult male consisting of nine pairs of sensory rays that lie within a web-like cuticle compared to control.

label: mitochondrial content decreased
definition: Animals exhibit decreases in the overall amount of mitochondria present in the animal, as determined by, for example, Mitotracker staining.

label: pleiotropic defects severe early emb
definition: Seemingly unrelated variations that concurrently occur during early embryonic development compared to control animals. In C. elegans, this can include multiple pronuclei, aberrant cytoplasmic texture, decrease in overall pace of development and osmotic sensitivity.

label: chromosome disjunction defective
definition: Chromosomes fail to segregate away from their homolog, resulting in gametes with no or extra copies of the chromosome.

label: histone methylation variant
definition: The pattern or state of methyl modifications of histone varies from that of controls.

label: no anterior pharynx
definition: Animals lack the anterior portion of the pharynx.

label: ectopic axon outgrowth
definition: Neurons exhibit axon outgrowth in locations not normally found in controls.

label: head development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the anterior end of the animal over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: nuclear import defective
definition: The directed movement of substances into the nucleus is impaired.

label: reproductive system physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the reproductive system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: annulae morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the circumferential pattern of ridges in the outer cortical layer of the cuticle, compared to that observed in control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: head muscle contraction variant
definition: Any variation in the contractions of the muscles in the most anterior body region of the animal compared to control.

label: cell gamma ray hypersensitive
definition: Cells respond to a lower dosage of gamma rays or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: dopamine metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving dopamine, a catecholamine neurotransmitter and a metabolic precursor of noradrenaline and adrenaline, compared to control.

label: embryos small early emb
definition: Embryos are produced that are less than fifty percent of the size of control embryos.

label: general pace of development variant
definition: Variations in the progression time of an animal from pronuclei meeting to adulthood compared to control animals.

label: neuronal sheath cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for a neuronal sheath cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: hydroxyurea hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to hydroxyurea at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: body part pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of a particular body part compared to control animals.

label: surface antigen negative
definition: Cuticles or cuticular extracts do not bind antibodies that are observed to bind the surfaces or cuticular extracts of Bristol N2 animals of the same developmental stage.

label: head behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the head in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: meiotic chromosome segregation variant
definition: Variations in the process by which genetic material, in the form of chromosomes, is organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two or more sets during the meiotic cell cycle, compared to control.

label: recovery pumping response to light variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the recovery pharyngeal pumping response to light, during which the pharyngeal pumping rate slowly increases during the 0-10 seconds afterremoval of light exposure, compared to controls.

label: mitochondrial membrane potential increased
definition: Any increase in the membrane potential (voltage gradient) across the inner mitochondrial membrane compared to control.

label: cation homeostasis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of cations within a cell or between a cell and its external environment, compared to control.

label: egg laying defective
definition: Eggs are not laid, laid at a slower rate or eggs are laid at a later stage of development compared to control.

label: male V lineages variant
definition: The descendants of any of the V precursor cells (V1-V6) in male animals, exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: asymmetric cell division defective early emb
definition: Symmetric (PAR-like) divisions or excessive posterior displacement (zyg-8 like phenotypes).

label: calcium channel modulator response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to specific calcium channel modulators compared to that observed in control animals.

label: directionality variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the directional changes that separate consecutive runs, from that observed for control animals. In C. elegans, these aberrations include variations in the form or extent of omega turns or reversals (shifts from forward to backward movements).

label: one point five fold arrest emb
definition: Cessation of development that normally occurs in C. elegans 420-460 min after the first embryonic cleavage at 20C, the stage between the comma and 2-fold embryo.

label: loss of left right asymmetry
definition: Bilaterally symmetric cell fail to acquire specific left-right asymmetric properties such as L/R specific cell position, cell death or gene expression.

label: spindle position variant
definition: Any variation in the placement of the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis compared to control.

label: cell degeneration
definition: Cells are observed to undergo a dramatic decrease in cell volume, collapse of the vacuoles, and complete disintegration of the plasma membrane and most organelles.

label: obsolete vesicle number reduced
definition: OBSOLETE. Total presynaptic vesicle number is reduced, possibly refecting a defect in the replenishment of synaptic vesicles compared to control.

label: cobalt hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to cobalt at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: extra cleavage furrow early emb
definition: One or more extra cleavage furrows are seen in one or more cells of a one-cell to four-cell embryo

label: susceptible to lectin
definition: Exposure to lectin results in altered behavior, growth, or development of the animal compared to controls.

label: embryonic pigmentation variant
definition: Embryos exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter its transparency/translucency compared to control animals .

label: protein neddylation variant
definition: Any variation in the conjugation of the ubiquitin-like protein Nedd8 to another protein compared to control.

label: shaker
definition: Animals rotate back and forth around their longitudinal axes.

label: synaptic vesicle homeostasis variant
definition: The rates of synaptic vesicle exocytosis and endocytosis vary from that observed in control animals.

label: cell corpse number variant
definition: Animals exhibit differences in the number of cell corpses compared to controls at the same developmental life stage.

label: distal tip cell migration precocious
definition: DTCs migrate at an earlier stage of development, compared to control.

label: starved L1 larvae aggregation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the aggregation behavior of starved L1 larvae, compared to controls.

label: body posture variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in body posture compared to control animals. For example, in C. elegans characteristic sinusoidal body posture is altered.

label: MS lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the MS blastomere exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: diet induced life span variant
definition: Life span of the animal is not influenced by changes in diet in the same manner as control animals.

label: RNAi response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to gene silencing triggered by double stranded RNA (RNAi), compared to control.

label: posterior pharynx variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the posterior portion of the pharynx over time compared to control. In C. elegans the posterior region includes the isthmus and terminal bulb (second bulb).

label: muscle birefringence variant
definition: Animals exhibit a weak and abnormal birefringency pattern in muscle fibers when examined using polarized optics.

label: bromide chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of bromide. In C. elegans, bromide is typically an attractant.

label: cell division slow
definition: Any variation that delays the physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells compared to control.

label: induced contraction rate variant
definition: Any variation in the frequency of gonad sheath contractions triggered by internal or external stimuli compared to control.

label: cleavage furrow initiation defective
definition: Cells exhibit defects in the formation of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate at the onset of cytokinesis.

label: cell proliferation reduced
definition: The processes governing the expansion of cell populations are altered compared to control animals, such that cell populations are decreased.

label: chromosome segregation variant karyomeres early emb
definition: Karyomeres in AB or P1 often accompanied by weak/thin wobbly spindle.

label: pharyngeal vacuole
definition: The pharynx contains cavities, possibly indicative of inappropriate cell death.

label: sexually dimorphic mechanosensation variant
definition: Any variation with respect to perception or response to mechanical stimuli in a sex dependent manner compared to control animals.

label: lectin response variant
definition: Exposure to carbohydrate binding gene products result in an altered action in comparison to controls.

label: anterior posterior neurite growth variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern the directed extension of neurite projections along the anteroposterior  axis of the animal compared to controls.

label: gut granule biogenesis reduced
definition: Animals lack birefringent containing compartments in embryonic intestinal cells; however, these compartments appear in adult stages.

label: ventral cord disorganized
definition: The longitudinal nerve cord of the midbody region, connecting the nerve ring and tail ganglia, is not arranged in the same manner as control animals.

label: arecoline resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of arecoline that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: mRNA levels increased
definition: Animals exhibit elevated levels of messenger RNA compared to control.

label: chemosensory neuron development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a chemosensory neuron over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: nuclear pore variant
definition: Any variation that disrupts the assembly, distribution, localization or organization of any of the numerous similar discrete openings in the nuclear envelope, where the inner and outer nuclear membranes are joined.

label: methyl methanesulfonate response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to methyl methanesulfonate compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cell cleavage variant emb
definition: Variations that disrupt stereotypical embryonic cleavage patterns (such as cleavage rate, division axes or asymmetric division).

label: octanol chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of octanol. In C. elegans, octanol is typically a repellant.

label: sickened by nonpathogenic bacteria
definition: Animals are negatively affected by bacteria that is nonpathogenic to control animals.

label: vulval development incomplete
definition: The developmental progression of the egg-laying organ of female and hermaphrodite nematodes is halted prior to the formation of the mature structure.

label: muscle membrane potential variant
definition: The difference in electrical potential between the interior and the exterior of the muscle cell either in the resting state or during evoked stimulation differs from controls.

label: response to food variant
definition: Any variation in the state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) in response to a food stimulus, compared to control.

label: wavelength of movement variant
definition: Any variation in the distance in the line of advance of a body wave from any one point to the next point of corresponding phase compared to control.

label: epithelial development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the epithelia over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control. This process involves autonomously generated changes in epidermal cell shape and position, and interactions with internal tissues, including the developing nervous system and body wall muscles to affect epidermal enclosure, cell intercalation, and epidermal elongation.

label: extended life span response to mianserin resistant
definition: Animals do not live longer in response to mianserin compared to control.

label: extra dopaminergic neuron
definition: Animals produce an excess number of dopaminergic neurons compared to controls.

label: nuclear positioning variant
definition: Variations in the directed movement of the nucleus to a specific location within a cell compared to control.

label: pathogen adherence variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations that result in variations in the ability of or extent to which pathogens adhere to the surface of animals, compared to control.

label: roaming increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in their high-speed movement in the forward direction with brief backward movement compared to control.

label: nose morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of the extreme anterior part of their body compared to control.

label: phasmid socket absent
definition: Animals are missing the interfacial hypodermal cell (socket cell) of the phasmid sensillum pore.

label: mitochondrial DNA copy number variant
definition: Relative levels of mtDNA differ from that observed for control animals.

label: pheromone induced dauer formation defective
definition: Animals do not enter dauer when exposed to chemicals that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: nuclear appearance number defective early emb
definition: The size, number and organization of the components of the nuclei in the early embryo deviate from control . In C. elegans, this is characterized by nuclei that are completely missing or are significantly smaller than normal; often accompanied by spindle and cytokinesis defects.

label: meiotic chromatin reorganization variant
definition: Animals differ from control animals in the length of or mechanics of the steps that culminate in the preservation and subsequent disassembly of the synaptonemal complex, the specification of bivalent arms, and proper cohesion of sister chromatids.

label: G1 checkpoint variant
definition: Mitotic cells exhibit variations during the passage through a cell cycle control point late in the G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle just before entry into S phase, compared to control cells.

label: embryonic cell fate specification variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern acquisition of particular cell fates in the embryo, from the time of zygote formation until hatching compared to control.

label: pre mRNA levels increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the levels of nuclear mRNA species compared to control.

label: masculinization of germline
definition: The germ line is sexually transformed from hermaphrodite to male. In C. elegans, XX mog animals are somatically hermaphrodite, but germ cells that normally would become oocytes are transformed into sperm.

label: actin organization biogenesis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the formation and/or arrangement of actin, an abundant cytoskeletal protein in most cells, often linked to the plasma membrane and concentrated at cell junctions compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: metacorpus morphology defective
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the first pharyngeal bulb compared to control.

label: necrotic cell death increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the cell death process that is morphologically characterized by a gain in cell volume (oncosis), swelling of organelles, plasma membrane rupture and subsequent loss of intracellular contents, compared to control.

label: hydrogen peroxide levels reduced
definition: Animals exhibit reductions in steady-state levels of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) compared to control.

label: mitotic chromatin remodeling variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations from controls in the organization of chromatin, including in relation to associated complexes, that occur during the mitotic cell division cycle.

label: gonadal lineage variant
definition: The descendants of a gonadal precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: sluggish
definition: Animals move more slowly compared with control animals.

label: touch resistant
definition: Variations in characteristic response with respect to perception or transmission of a touch stimulus compared to responses in control animals.

label: contraction response to ouabain resistant
definition: Animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to ouabain to elicit the rapid muscular contractions seen in control animals.

label: pathogen release reduced
definition: Infected animals exhibit a reduction in the release of pathogens back into the environment, compared to control.

label: cell cleavage variant
definition: Variations that disrupt stereotypical cleavage patterns (such as cleavage rate, division axes or asymmetric division) compared to control.

label: protein expression absent
definition: Animals fail to express a given protein or class of proteins.

label: turning frequency reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the frequency of execution of the behavior by which the animal alters its trajectory of movement compared to control, excluding shifts from forward to backward movements (this is reversal).

label: epithelial attachment variant
definition: Variations in the adhesion of the layer of cells that cover the external surface of an organism which serves to protect the animal from external environment compared to control.

label: cell death sexually dimorphic increased
definition: Animals exhibit in increase in the rate or extent of programmed cell death as it pertains to a sex-specific feature, compared to control populations.

label: circumferential actin bundles disorganized
definition: The distribution or presence of actin in circumferential actin bundles (CFB) differs from that observed in control animals. Contraction of CFBs provide the driving force for epidermal elongation.

label: pronuclear envelope defective early emb
definition: Any deficiency in the lipid bilayer, the equivalent of the nuclear envelope, that surrounds each pronucleus within gametes and within the early zygote after pronuclear reformation (Wormatlas).

label: missing distal tip cells
definition: Animals produce less distal tip cells compared to controls.

label: endogenous transposase levels increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the levels of transposase mRNA, from endogenous transposons, over that measured in control animals.

label: X linked gene expression reduced
definition: Levels of transcripts associated with genes on the X chromosome are decreased compared to control.

label: persistent primordial germ cell lobes
definition: Animals exhibit persistent cellular lobes of the primordial germ cells Z2 and/or Z3 at the L1 larval stage or later, in contrast to wild type animals

label: cell cycle arrest
definition: Cells of the animals cease during one of its replicative phases (G1, S, G2, M).

label: body posture wavelength increased
definition: Animals exhibit variations in body posture caused by an increase in the distance between repeating units of a wave pattern compared to control animals. In C. elegans, characteristic sinusoidal body posture is sinusoidal.

label: excretory secretory system physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the excretory/secretory system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: L3 lethal
definition: Animals die at the L3 stage of the life cycle.

label: life span variant
definition: Adult life span is either longer or shorter than typical of control animals.

label: oocytes disorganized
definition: Oocytes are no longer arranged in the gonad in the same manner as control animals.

label: Y lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the Y cell (which divides only in the males) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: muscle cell activity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction compared to control animals.

label: activity level variant
definition: Any variation in the degree of movement compared to control animals.

label: dauer body morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of an animal progressing through an alternative larval stage in response to environmental stresses compared to control animals.

label: head protrusion
definition: Any irregular swelling in discrete regions of the head.

label: reduced acute pharyngeal pumping response to light
definition: Animals exhibit a reduced acute pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that pharyngeal pumping rate decreases in response to light to a lesser extent than in controls during the first 0-5 seconds after light exposure onset.

label: gonad morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form or composition of a specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces the male or female gametes compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: dendritic termini number reduced
definition: The number of terminal regions of a neuron's dendrite is less that that observed for control animals.

label: amphid sheath secretion failure
definition: Amphid sheath cells lack the ability to secrete vesicles and their contents within the amphid pocket.

label: excess maternal pronucleus early emb
definition: One-cell embryos have two or more maternal pronuclei.

label: axon termination defective
definition: Axons in animals do not end in the same manner as they do in control animals. Some defects described include an overextension of the axon or termination of the axon in the shape of a hook, either large or small.

label: head morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of their anterior end (which typically includes the anterior sensilla, pharynx and all muscles that are innervated by the nerve ring) compared to control.

label: heme levels decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the amount of heme compared to control animals. Heme is any compound of iron complexed in a porphyrin (tetrapyrrole) ring.

label: body posture amplitude variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in body posture with regard to the extent of displacement measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control animals.

label: nervous system morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any component that is part of the complement of organ tissues that serve to detect, relay and coordinate information about an animal's internal and external environments and to initiate and integrate its effector responses and activities, compared to that in control animals.

label: anchor cell fusion defective
definition: Any perturbation that disrupts the fusion between the anchor cell and the surrounding utse syncytium. Such variations result in the loss of uterine-vulval connectivity and continuity.

label: cell fate transformation
definition: The cell takes on a different identity from which it was initially committed.

label: endogenous synaptic events variant
definition: Any variation in the currents observed in the absence of presynaptic action potentials and that are elicited by fusion of a single endogenous vesicle of transmitter compared to control.

label: serotonin deficient
definition: Animals do not contain or are unable to maintain a perceivable level of serotonin capable of initiating or maintaining serotonin-dependent cell activity.

label: EMS anterior extension extreme early emb
definition: EMS extends too far anteriorly at the four cell stage.

label: embryonic polarity variant
definition: Contents or structures of an embryonic cell are not restricted/localized to the same positions (or poles) compared with control animals.

label: germline mortal
definition: Progressive decrease in brood size culminating, over generations, in the loss of reproductive ability and thus becoming effectively sterile.

label: passage through meiosis defective early emb
definition: Male and female PNs not visible; embryo often fills egg shell completely.

label: twisted pharynx
definition: The growth of pharyngeal components occurs in a radial fashion around the longitudinal axis of the worm as demonstrated by bent radial contractile arrays within the pharyngeal muscle cells. The defect is more pronounced as development progresses resulting in a more obvious twisting phenotype. Depending on the allele, the twist can be right-handed or left-handed

label: bleach hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to bleach at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: mating plug deficient
definition: Males do not form copulatory mating plug.

label: non reflexed gonad arms
definition: Gonadal arms do not bend or curve. In C. elegans gonad arms normally reflex to form a stereotypical U-shaped pattern.

label: dauer lifespan variant
definition: The life span of dauer-staged animals is either longer or shorter than that observed in control dauer animals.

label: pyrimidine biosynthesis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of pyrimidine nucleobases, 1,3-diazine, organic nitrogenous bases.

label: protein phosphorylation increased
definition: Animals exhibit higher levels of protein phosphorylation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: 3 prime target RNA uridylation reduced
definition: 3' uridylation of mRNA targeted for silencing does not occur at the same rate or extent of targeted mRNA in control animals.

label: pronuclear envelope morphology defective early emb
definition: Morphology of the pronuclear envelope is atypical in the inviable embryo.

label: maintenance of gene silencing defective
definition: Animals express genes that had been targeted for heritable silencing in previous generations.

label: hermaphrodite physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required to carry out hermaphrodite-specific activities or to be able to perceive and respond to hermaphrodite-specific stimuli compared to control.

label: DNA damage response variant
definition: Variations in the activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating damage to its DNA from environmental insults or errors during metabolism, compared to control.

label: head muscle dystrophy
definition: Progressive degeneration of the head muscle.

label: tunicamycin response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of tunicamycin compared to that observed in control animals. Tunicamycin induces the unfolded protein response.

label: ventral nerve cord maintenance variant
definition: Any variation in the mechanisms used to ensure that axons in the ventral nerve cord maintain their correct positioning after termination of axonal outgrowth and target recognition compared to control.

label: egg size variant
definition: Any variation in the overall size of fertilized oocytes that are laid compared to those laid by control animals.

label: early exit cell cycle
definition: Cells leave the M phase (mitosis and cytokinesis) at an earlier time than sister or other control cells.

label: uterine muscle variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the sex-specific muscles of the hermaphrodite, over time, whose contractions squeeze on the uterus to help move eggs towards the vulval opening compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: antimony hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to antimony at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: synchronous second division early emb
definition: AB and P1 divide synchronously.

label: gonad independent vulva differentiation
definition: VPCs differentiate in the absence of inductive signals coming from the gonad.

label: pattern of transgene expression variant
definition: Any variation in the cellular or subcellular pattern of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: protein ubiquitination variant
definition: Variations in the process by which one or more ubiquitin moieties are added to a protein, compared to control.

label: centrosome attachment defective early emb
definition: Centrosomes detach from the male pronucleus.

label: male gonad development variant
definition: Males exhibit variations in the reproductive system, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control.

label: body axis morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a discrete axis (dorsal/ventral/anterior/posterior/transverse) of their anatomy, compared to control animals.

label: ER stress response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to the presence of unfolded proteins in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) or to other ER-related stressors compared to control.

label: defecation missing motor steps
definition: Animals lack one or more of the stereotyped muscle contractions that result in defecation compared to control. In C. elegans these contractions include posterior body contraction (pBoc), anterior body contraction (aBoc), expulsion of gut contents by enteric muscle contraction (Emc) and opening of anus (Exp).

label: anaphase variant
definition: Any variation in the stage of meiotic or mitotic cell division in which the chromosomes move away from one another to opposite poles of the spindle.

label: body twisted
definition: Any portion of the animal, between the head and the tail, appears distorted, usually due to uncharacteristic winding.

label: neuron calcium transient levels variant
definition: The degree of stimulus-evoked calcium concentration changes differs from that of controls.

label: striated muscle morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the striated muscle compared to control animals.

label: RNAi persistence variant
definition: Variations in the persistence of an RNAi induced phenotype compared to control.

label: hypodermal cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the hypodermal system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: endosome fusion defective
definition: Animals are deficient in the formation or disassembly of lysosomes.

label: backward kinker
definition: Backward movement is often characterized by severe bending motions, more sharply angled and/or much deeper than stereotypical sinusoidal body bends of the control. Animal moves backward with uncharacteristic muscle spasms causing loss of smooth sinusoidal motion or body posture (Wormatlas).

label: odorant negative chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to move away from repellant volatile organic chemicals.

label: cell differentiation variant
definition: Variations in the processes leading to the specialization of cell. Differentiation impacts diverse cellular properties such as size, shape, polarity, gene expression and responsiveness to signals/cues.

label: RNAi enhanced
definition: Animals show increased susceptibility to gene silencing triggered by double stranded RNA (RNAi), compared to control.

label: cell position defective
definition: a cell (or group of cells) is not found in the correct body position compared the placement in control animals.

label: egg laying serotonin resistant
definition: Animals are not induced to lay eggs in reponse to exogenous serotonin. Serotonin stimulates egg-laying in C. elegans.

label: amphid dye filling defect
definition: Animals exhibit defects in dye-filling of the neuronal cells of the amphid sensilla. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling with FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: no synaptic spike frequency
definition: Calcium transients at presynaptic regions do not occur.

label: endocytic recycling defective
definition: Variations in the directed movement of membrane-bounded vesicles from recycling endosomes back to the plasma membrane where they are recycled for further rounds of transport, compared to control.

label: presynaptic vesicle number reduced
definition: Animals exhibit an overall decrease in the quantity of synaptic vesicles at the synapse compared to control animals.

label: grinder relaxation variant
definition: Variations in the rhythmic relaxations of the a highly specialized cuticle region of the pharynx inside the lumen of the second bulb, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: xenotoxicity suppressor
definition: Animals are resistant to the toxicity of an anti-infective xenobiotic such as R24. Such small molecules protect the host from bacterial infection by inducing antibacterial immune responses via the p38 MAPK pathway. These molecules tend to have toxic effects in addition to immunostimulatory activity.

label: acetylcholinesterase inhibitor response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific acetylcholinesterase inhibitor compared to that observed in control animals.

label: food dependent body size variant
definition: Animals do not differ in size when grown on different food sources to the same extent as that measured for control animals. For example, in C. elegans, wild type worms are 1.65 times larger when grown on HB101 compared to those grown on OP50.

label: acetylcholine levels variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of acetylcholine compared to control animals at a defined stage. Acetylcholine is the acetic acid ester of the organic base choline.

label: head withdrawal defective
definition: Animals are deficient in the foraging response in which an animal quickly pulls its head away from a stimulus to the nose (Wormatlas).

label: dauer recovery variant
definition: Characteristic exit from the dauer stage is altered compared to control animals.

label: obsolete mitochondria morphology variant muscle
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: transgene subcellular localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of a gene product produced by DNA coded for by exogenous genetic material that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: sperm recruitment variant
definition: Any variation in the mechanism by which sperm find their correct target destinations (spermatheca).

label: chloroquinone resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of chloroquinone that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: lethal gamete
definition: Animals produce ova/sperm that contain lethal factors as a result of chromosomal disjunction defects.

label: sensillum morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the sense organs comprised of ciliated sensory nerve endings enveloped by sheath and/or socket cells, from that observed in control animals.

label: aqueous chemosensory response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in response to water-soluble chemicals, compared to control.

label: forward locomotion decreased
definition: Animals spend less time in forward locomotion, compared to control animals.

label: wing cilia axoneme short
definition: The microtuble-based fibrillar-bundle, axoneme, of the wing cell cilia are reduced in length and do not extend into the sheath cell as far as they do in control animals.

label: translation repression variant
definition: The extent of translational repression varies from controls.

label: egg laying phases variant
definition: Fluctuation pattern between inactive, active, and egg-laying states is atypical, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events compared to control.

label: pre male contact variant
definition: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of a hermaphrodite prior to male contact during mating compared to control.

label: cell cycle progression variant
definition: Cells of the animals exhibit variations in the progression or exit from the biochemical and morphological processes that occur during successive replication or nuclear replication events from that observed for control animals.

label: right handed roller
definition: The body of the animal rotates around its long axis as the animal moves, causing the animal to move in a circular pattern in the right-handed direction. In liquid media, wave propogation is helical rather than planar.

label: protein expression reduced male
definition: Variations that result in a decrease in protein expression in male animals compared to that observed in control animals.

label: dauer pheromone production defective
definition: Animals are incapable of synthesizing pheromones that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: meiosis metaphase to anaphase transition block
definition: Oocyte chromosomes arrest in metaphase of meiosis I without transitioning to anaphase or producing polar bodies.

label: post translational processing variant
definition: Any variation in the posttranslational modification of a protein (which may include cleavage of peptide bonds) leading to the attainment of the full functional capacity of the protein compared to control.

label: nuclear morphology variation early emb
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the membrane enclosed organelle which contains most of the cell's genetic material during the early embryonic stage compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: gonad degenerate
definition: Animals contain a gonad that initially functioned, but subsequently stopped.  In hermaphrodites or females there is often the presence old embryos and/or hatched larva, but no young embryos, in the uterus.

label: early elongation arrest
definition: Cessation of development during the initial period of elongation. In C. elegans, this period refers to the conversion of the bean-shaped embryo into the two-fold- shaped embryo.

label: commissure number variant
definition: Variations in the quantity of circumferential axonal tracts from the number observed in control animals.

label: slow development
definition: The developmental progression of an animal, from its formation to its mature structure occurs over a longer time period compared to control.

label: cholinergic agonist resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of cholinergic agonist that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: embryo small
definition: The organism's size during the embryonic developmental stage is decreased compared to that observed in control.

label: organism hypersensitive gamma irradiation
definition: Organisms respond to a lower dosage of gamma rays or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: intestine dark
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that decrease the transparency/translucency of the intestine.

label: somatic sheath physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the somatic sheath system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: bent posture increased
definition: Animals exhibit increased posture eccentricity (measure of circularity) or the mean number (and/or standard deviation) of instantaneous body bends.

label: mutagen induced apoptosis variant
definition: Programmed cell death of germ cells caused by exposure to physical or chemical DNA-damaging agents does not occur to the same extent as it does in control animals.

label: precise vulval location variant
definition: Any variation in the mating process that includes the male positioning his tail precisely over the vulva so that he may insert his spicules and ejaculate compared to control. In C. elegans precise vulva location (coordinating movement and tail positioning) requires the post cloacal sensillium and the spicules.

label: hypoxia resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to low amounts of oxygen that elicit a response in control animals.

label: V lineages variant
definition: The descendants of any of the V precursor cells (V1-V6) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: dauer formation variant
definition: Characteristic entry into the dauer stage is altered compared to control animals.

label: adult development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of an animal over time from the end of larval stage to a mature adult compared to control animals.

label: phasmid morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the neuronal cells of the phasmid sensillum, from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling experiments using FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: mitochondria morphology variant
definition: The morphological appearance of mitochondria is varied compared to control animals.

label: head movement increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the movement of the most anterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: organism stress response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in response to stress stimuli compared to control animals.

label: cuticle integrity variant
definition: The physical strength or function of the cuticle is varies from that observed for control animals.

label: suicidal
definition: Animals do not avoid, and perhaps seek, environments that result in their death. In the case of C. elegans, this behavior is exemplified by animals that tend to crawl off the plate.

label: male sexual development variant
definition: Genetically male animals exhibit deviations in the sexual program specific to males. In C. elegans, this often refers to XO animals being transformed into fertile hermaphrodites.

label: athermotactic
definition: The responses of an animal towards temperature are not influenced by its cultivation temperature.

label: nuclear fallout
definition: Nuclei have fallen out of developing germ cell compartments into the rachis.

label: uptake by intestinal cell defective
definition: Uptake of subtances from the intestine is altered from that observed in control animals.

label: nicotine response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of nicotine compared to that observed in control animals. Nicotine is a cholinergic agonist.

label: ribosome localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of the ribosome compared to control. The ribosome is an intracellular organelle, about 200 A in diameter, consisting of RNA and protein. It is the site of protein biosynthesis resulting from translation of messenger RNA (mRNA).

label: protein methylation variant
definition: Variations in the processes that incorporate methyl groups to one or more amino acids within a protein, compared to control.

label: tail movement variant
definition: The most posterior portion of the animal exhibits variations in its movement compared to control.

label: disorganized pharyngeal EPG
definition: Electropharyngeograms do not show a similar pattern as control animals. C. elegans animals show a repeating regular pattern in which each pump is associated with an excitatory depolarizing wave, often punctuated by brief negative spikes, followed by a plateau phase, and ending with an inhibitory hyperpolarizing wave.

label: lysosome morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosomes, that have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell, compared to control.

label: increased pathogen survival
definition: Pathogens internally associated with the animal exhibit an increase in survival compared to control animals.

label: sex determination variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern the sexually dimorphic development of germline or somatic tissue compared to control.

label: body length variant
definition: Animals vary in the distance between anterior and posterior ends of the animal from that observed in control animals.

label: axon fasciculation variant
definition: The ability of axons to converge and form a bundle of nerve fibres (fascicle) is compromised.

label: embryonic cell patterning variant
definition: Embryos exhibit variations in the patterning of differentiated cell types, compared to control.

label: larval development retarded
definition: The developmental progression of a larva over time, from its formation to its mature structure is delayed compared to control. The larva is the early, immature form of an animal between hatching and adulthood.

label: actin cytoskeleton dynamics variant
definition: Any variation in the dynamic structural changes to the arrangement of constituent parts of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins compared to control.

label: caffeine resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of caffeine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: pronuclear size defective early emb
definition: Maternal or paternal pronucleus is either too small or too large.

label: coiling frequency increased
definition: Animals spend more time with their body posture in a coil or they increase the frequency with which they form coils compared to control animals.

label: lethal
definition: Animals die prematurely at any stage of the life cycle.

label: RME-1 recycling endosome morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes, positive for the endocytosis protein RME-1, that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: intestinal contractions variant
definition: Any variations in the contraction of the enteric muscles that are involved in defecation motor program compared to control.

label: meiotic sister chromatid segregation variant
definition: Variations in the process by which sister chromatids, identical chromosomes resulting from DNA replication, are physically separated during the meiotic cell cycle, compared to control.

label: cilia length decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a reduction in the length of the microtubule-based dendritic projections extending from the cell body, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: autophagy increased
definition: Animals exhibit increased levels of the process by which their cells digest parts of their own cytoplasm, compared to control.

label: early endosome morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as early endosomes,  that traffic material from endocytic vesicles (having recently internalized portions of the cell's plasma membrane) to internal compartments of the cell, such as recycling endosomes, late endosomes, or the Golgi apparatus, compared to control.

label: giant oocytes
definition: The size of haploid female germ cells (oocytes) are significantly larger compared to control.

label: amplitude of sinusoidal movement decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of a vibratory movement (as a worm bend) measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control.

label: no germ line
definition: Animals lack all germline progenitor cells, thereby resulting in the complete absence of a germline.

label: cell cycle slow early emb
definition: Embryos take longer to divide during the first and second cell divisions.

label: posterior lateral ganglion development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the neuron somata associated with the post-deirid over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: integrity of membranous organelles defective early emb
definition: Sparse or enlarged yolk granules.

label: axon regeneration defective
definition: Animals do not regrow axons following axon loss or damage, to the same extent, or in the same manner as observed in control animals.

label: organism homeostasis metabolism variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways involved in the maintenance of a steady-state at the level of the organism compared to control.

label: pathogen infected pharynx variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the extent of pathogen invasion into the pharynx compared to control. This is often measured as the percentage of animals exhibiting a pathogen-invaded pharynx within a given population.

label: sperm nonmotile
definition: The mature male gametes lack self-propelled movement.

label: labial sensillum morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the sensilla of the mouth compared to control. In C. elegans, these sensillum are arranged in two (inner and outer) concentric rings around the mouth.

label: less susceptibility to induced DNA damage
definition: Nematodes exposed to DNA damaging agents or conditions exhibit lower susceptibility to DNA damage than other animals.

label: cell induction variant
definition: Variations in a cell's ability to influence the fate of another cell (often of different developmental potential or ancestry via short range signaling).

label: egg laying phentolamine resistant
definition: Animals are not induced to lay eggs in reponse to exogenous phentolamine. In C. elegans, phentolamine stimulates egg-laying.

label: endogenous zinc levels reduced
definition: Animals exhibit reduced levels of endogenous zinc compared to control animals.

label: pronucleus centrosomes defective early emb
definition: Pronucleus is abnormal in the inviable embryo.

label: photocurrent defective
definition: Animals do not exhibit light-induced currrents to the same extent or with the same quality as control animals.

label: mitochondrial membrane potential reduced
definition: Any reduction in the membrane potential (voltage gradient) across the inner mitochondrial membrane compared to control.

label: somatic gonad primordium development defective
definition: The developmental progression of the set of precursor cells that later give rise to the somatic tissues of the gonadal tract is impaired (Wormatlas).

label: hindgut damaged
definition: The terminal portion of the intestine exhibits structural defects such as scarring or blockage.

label: antibody temporal expression variant
definition: The expression of a protein, as determined by antibody staining, varied from controls with respect to timing such that the protein was observed to be expressed at earlier timepoints or later timepoints than controls.

label: defecation contraction variant
definition: Any variation in the stereotyped muscle contractions that result in defecation compared to control . In C. elegans these contractions include posterior body contraction (pBoc), anterior body contraction (aBoc), expulsion of gut contents by enteric muscle contraction (Emc) and opening of anus (Exp).

label: cell cycle defective early emb
definition: The progression of biochemical and morphological processes that occur during successive replication or nuclear replication events is disrupted during the early embryonic stage.

label: retarded seam cell fusion
definition: Seam cells fuse to form a continuous syncytium along the body wall at a later stage of development compared to control.

label: pharyngeal pumping irregular
definition: Pharyngeal pumping motion occurs at intervals that vary from control animals.

label: anterior ganglion development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a cluster of neuron somata located close to the nerve ring over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: ivermectin response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to ivermectin, an agonist of glutamate-gated chloride channels, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: spindle position defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the placement of the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis.

label: organism hypersensitive X ray irradiation
definition: Animals respond to iononizing radiation at a lower dose or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. Iononizing radiation has a wavelength in the 10 to 0.01 nanometer range. In C. elegans, increased sensitivity to X-ray irradiation is often observed as a decrease in survival upon exposure compared to control animals given the same treatment.

label: neuronal outgrowth variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern the extension of neuronal projections.

label: anterior body contraction variant
definition: Any variation in the defecation motor program that involves the contraction of the anterior body wall muscles compared to control.

label: serotonin reuptake inhibitor hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to serotonin reuptake inhibitors at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: food suppressed pumping variant
definition: Exposure to food does not reduce pharyngeal pumping to the same extent as observed in control animals.

label: mitochondrial DNA damage variant
definition: Any variation in the extent of mitochondrial DNA damage observed compared to controls.

label: constitutive enzyme activity
definition: Any variation that results in the misregulation of enzymatic activity such that catalysis occurs at a constant rate regardless of physiological demand or the concentration of a substrate.

label: protrusion at vulval region
definition: Large protrusion at the normal position of the vulva, as seen in C. elegans lin-12 null animals.

label: gut granule morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphology of the different inclusions within the intestinal cytoplasm, including birefringent crystalline objects and other dark-staining endosomes compared to control. In C. elegans these contents might include glycogen granules (polysaccharide storage), rhabditin (carbohydrate storage), yolk granules (lipid and protein), and concentrated waste products (Wormatlas).

label: abamectin sensitive
definition: Animals are do not survive, or become paralyzed in the presence of abamectin.

label: pale adult
definition: Adults show deficiencies in chroma resulting in increased translucency.

label: pathogen load variant
definition: The number of pathogens associated with the animal vary from that associated with control animals.

label: lipid metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of an internal store of lipid within the organism or cell compared to control.

label: egg laying serotonin variant
definition: Any variation in egg laying behavior after application of exogenous serotonin compared to control. In C. elegans, serotonin induces egg laying.

label: organism morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any part of their anatomy compared to control animals.

label: anion positive chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to move towards attractive anions.

label: VPC cell division variant
definition: Any variation that alters the physical partitioning and separation of a vulval precursor cell into daughter cells compared to control.

label: amphid channel cilia morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the dendritic projections of the amphid sensory neurons that traverse the sensillum pore to connect with the outside of the animal, compared to that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, amphid channel cilia morphology is frequently assayed by dye-filling experiments using FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: cell polarity reversed
definition: Contents or structures of the cell are oriented on the opposite side of the cell compared to control animals; In C. elegans, this can result in the fate pattern of descendants being flipped.

label: magnesium chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to magnesium. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards magnesium.

label: corpse morphology variant
definition: Corpses resulting from programmed cell death appear different in size or shape from those of corpses in control animals.

label: univalent meiotic chromosomes
definition: Chromosomes fails to pair with homologous chromosomes during the prophase stage of meiosis.

label: connective tissue development variant
definition: Variations in the material made up of fibers forming a framework and support structure for body tissues and organs compared to control.

label: radiation induced reproductive cell death variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in radiation induced non-apoptotic death of multipotential precursor cells or tissues (clonogens) compared to control. Elimination of clonogens results in normal tissue damage as well as solid-tumor eradication.

label: loss of asymmetry AWC
definition: The two morphologically bilaterally symmetric olfactory neurons AWC left (AWCL) and AWC right (AWCR) fail to undergo a left/right asymmetric diversification in cell fate.

label: hexanol chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of hexanol. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, hexanol is an attractant.

label: reversion of swimming paralysis
definition: Animals that exhibit paralysis (reduced thrashing) revert back to normal swimming behavior that can be tabulated as a reversion index (number revertants/number paralysis) and reversion probability (time in reversion/time after paralysis).

label: stuffed pharynx
definition: Pharynx becomes clogged with food. In C. elegans, this is often a result of pharyngeal pumping defects.

label: cell fate transformation to endoderm
definition: Animals develop endodermal cells/tissue from precursor cells that do not normally produce endodermal cells/tissue.

label: larval defecation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the elimination of fecal matter during the larval stage compared to control animals.

label: dauer development variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern development of the dauer larva, a developmentally arrested, larval stage that is specialized for survival under harsh, or otherwise unfavorable, environmental conditions. In C. elegans this is an alternative third larval stage.

label: L2 lethal
definition: L2 lethal: Animals die at the L2 stage of the life cycle.

label: rectal morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the rectum compared to control animals.

label: crossover defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the number or extent of connections between chromatids that occur during the process of genetic material exchange between homologous segments of non-sister chromatids.

label: obsolete pattern of reporter gene expression variant
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: male tail curling serotonin resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of serotonin that elicits a male tail curling response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans males respond to serotonin with a tight ventral curling of the male tail and posterior body.

label: organ system development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of an organismal system from its formation to the mature structure when compared to control animals.

label: chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific chemical concentration gradient compared to control. Directed movement may be towards a higher concentration (positive chemotaxis) or towards a lower concentration (negative chemotaxis).

label: imipramine resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of imipramine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: body proportion variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the body-area-to-length ratio and/or the width-to-length ratio, compared to control animals.

label: intraflagellar transport absent
definition: Bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum is completely abolished.

label: somatic RNAi resistant
definition: Animals show reduced susceptibility to gene silencing in somatic cells triggered by double stranded RNA (dsRNA), compared to control.

label: starvation induced dauer formation defective
definition: Animals do not enter dauer under nutrient-poor conditions that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: cGMP chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to cGMP. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards cGMP.

label: post hermaphrodite contact variant
definition: Males exhibit variations in mating behavior after contacting its mate compared to control.

label: high temperature induced L1 arrest
definition: Animals undergo an irreversible high temperature-induced developmental arrest during the first larval stage.

label: hermaphrodite germline proliferation variant
definition: Nuclear divisions in the germ line of hermaphrodites are either expanded are reduced compared to control.

label: organism hypersensitive interstrand cross link agents
definition: Animals exhibit increased sensitivity to interstrand cross-linking agents, such as HN2 (nitrogen mustard) and CDDP (cisplatin) compared to control. In C. elegans, increased sensitivity to these agents is often observed as a decrease in survival compared to control animals after exposure to the agent.

label: noxious heat avoidance defective
definition: Animals fail to execute their characteristic movements to avoid noxious heat in a manner consistent with controls.

label: apoptotic cell shedding variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the process by which cells having undergone programmed cell death are shed or extruded into the extracellular environment.

label: diacetyl chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to diacetyl as defined by control animals. In C.elegans diacetyl is typically attractive.

label: protein signaling variant
definition: Any variation in a series of protein mediated signals that help relay information within the cell, and thereby affecting changes in the functioning of the cell, compared to control.

label: RNA expression variant
definition: Variations in the biogenesis and stability of any class of RNA molecules (rRNAs, miRNAs, tRNAs etc) compared to control.

label: adult growth variant
definition: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) during the adult stage compared to control animals.

label: diakinesis region organization variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations from control animals in the organization of the germ cell nuclei in the gonad that are in the diakinesis stage. In C. elegans the diakinesis region occurs in the proximal gonad arm and is preceded by the diplotene region. In the diakinesis region oocytes arrest until oocyte maturation occurs.

label: pseudocoelom development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the fluid-filled space which separates the body wall from internal organs over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: 21U RNA expression variant
definition: Variations in the biogenesis or stability of the 21U-RNA class of molecules compared to control. Molecules are classified as 21U-RNA based on the presence of a 5'U and a conserved upstream motif, which may specify the production of these molecules, in addition these molecules are typically 21nt in length.

label: connection of gonad variant
definition: Any variation that disrupts the connectivity between the somatic gonad and the adjoining tissues compared to control. In C. elegans this connnection is between the somatic gonad and the vulva in hermaphrodites and between the somatic gonad and proctodeum in males.

label: body wall muscle myosin organization defective
definition: The characteristic organization of myosin filaments into discrete A-bands within the muscle cells is disrupted. In C. elegans, myosin filaments no longer appear as continuous longitudinally oriented fibers across the muscle quadrants.

label: muscle detached
definition: Animals fail to establish or maintain the connection between cell(s) whose principal function is to provide contractile forces and its neighboring cells or tissues.

label: organism toxic chemical response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific toxic chemical compared to that observed in control animals.

label: slow recovery from starvation-induced L1 arrest
definition: Animals exhibit a slow recovery from starvation-induced L1 arrest, compared to controls.

label: ray tips swollen
definition: The extreme ends of any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan appear bloated or distended.

label: adherens junctions variant pharyngeal muscle
definition: Any variation in the cell junctions of the pharyngeal muscle at which the cytoplasmic face of the plasma membrane is attached to actin filaments compared to control.

label: track length increased
definition: Animals exhibit increased length of the minimum enclosing rectangle surrounding the worm body on a solid medium, as viewed through the microscope.

label: M lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the M precursor cell exhibit variations in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.  In C. elegans the M lineage is a postembryonic mesodermal lineage.

label: mitochondrial respiratory complex II variant
definition: The part of the respiratory chain that catalyzes the oxidation of succinate and connects the TCA cycle with the respiratory chain, differs in activity, composition, or organization, from that of controls.

label: hermaphrodite mating variant
definition: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of a hermaphrodite during mating compared to control.

label: germ cell compartment expansion absent
definition: The compartments of the germline do not increase in size.

label: defecation cycle temperature compensation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in temperature dependent differences in the length of their defecation cycle. In C. elegans the length of the cycle is the same at different temperatures, showing temperature compensation.

label: adult behavior variant
definition: Activity characteristic of an adult worm is altered compared to control.

label: spindle assembly defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle, the array of microtubules and associated molecules that serves to move duplicated chromosomes apart.

label: retarded heterochronic variations
definition: Variations that result in the deceleration of the rate, frequency or extent of the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition, compared to control.

label: obsolete sensory neuroanatomy variant
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: late larval lethal
definition: Animals die during late larval development. In C. elegans, this occurs during the L3- L4 larval stages of the life cycle.

label: nicotine hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to nicotine at lower concentrations or shorter exposure compared to control. Nicotine is a cholinergic agonist.

label: early endosome localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as early endosomes,  that traffic material from endocytic vesicles (having recently internalized portions of the cell's plasma membrane) to internal compartments of the cell, such as recycling endosomes, late endosomes, or the Golgi apparatus, compared to control.

label: organism pathogen response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to disease causing agents, compared to control. Pathogen response includes prevention, damage control and recovery from the infection caused by the attack.

label: oocyte number decreased
definition: A decreased number of celullarized haploid female germ cells (oocytes) are present in the gonad compared to control.

label: touch resistant anterior body
definition: Animal does not respond to stroking in the anterior body region with a hair or similar fiber compared to control. In C. elegans, the anterior region is defined as the body region that lies between the posterior bulb of the pharynx and the vulva.

label: endosome to lysosome trafficking defective
definition: Contents of endosomes fail to be transported to lysosomal compartments.

label: social feeding increased
definition: Worms are found in clumps and/or crowded at the border of the bacterial lawn more frequently than control animals. This behavior is not due to mobility defects.

label: duration of self fertility variant
definition: The window of production of self-fertilized eggs exceeds or does not extend to the same length as control.

label: translation rate reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a reduction in the rate of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a protein, compared to control.

label: HSN migration variant
definition: Any variation in the normal anterior movement of the HSN motor neurons from their birthplace in the tail to positions near the middle of the embryo compared to control animals.

label: pronuclear nuclear appearance variant emb
definition: The shape and size of nuclei as well as the distribution of nucleoporins are strongly affected.

label: breaks in alae
definition: The small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle, lengthwise along the body, contain gaps as opposed to a continuous arrangement (Wormatlas).

label: acute functional tolerance to alcohol defective
definition: Animals do not develop acute functional tolerance to alcohol after a short exposure, unlike that observed in control animals

label: fat content increased
definition: Animals exhibit a greater amount of fat or lipids than observed in control animals.

label: hypersensitive to dauer pheromone
definition: Animals respond to dauer pheromone at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: epidermis cuticle detached
definition: Animals are deficient in the adhesion of the cuticle to the epidermal surface of the animal.

label: dorsal intercalation defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the generation of the dorsal epithelial sheet, which entails distinct cell shape changes and movements to affect the interdigitation of two rows of dorsal cells resulting in a single row of cells across the dorsal midline.

label: gland cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a gland cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: centroid velocity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the translocation of the mean position of the rear two-thirds (centroid position) of the animal over time, from that observed for control animals.

label: nervous system development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of nervous tissue over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: amphid phasmid sensillum morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of any specialized chemosensory organs located on the head or along the tail, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: DNA synthesis variant
definition: Variations in the processes involving the production of new DNA strands compared to control.

label: adrenergic receptor antagonist response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific adrenergic receptor antagonist compared to that observed in control animals.

label: engulfment failure by killer cell
definition: Removal of cell corpses through a dedicated engulfment pathway is defective.

label: polar body defective early emb
definition: Polar bodies are abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: paralyzed arrested elongation two fold
definition: Movement and elongation ceases at the two-fold stage. The myofilament lattice in body wall muscle cells is variant. However, development in embryos continues. Embryos hatch as inviable larvae.

label: two fold arrest
definition: Cessation of development that normally occurs in C. elegans 460-520 min after the first cleavage at 20C, the stage between the 1.5-fold and 3-fold embryo.

label: endoplasmic reticulum localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of the endoplasmic reticulum compared to control. The endoplasmic reticulum (ER) is an irregular network of membranes, that exists in the cytoplasm, and forms a complex meshwork of tubular channels. The ER has two forms, rough (or granular), with ribosomes adhering to the outer surface, and smooth (with no ribosomes attached).

label: blast cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the blast cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to cues, compared to control animals.

label: body wall muscle sarcomere morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the repeating units of a myofibrils in a muscle cell that are composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments, compared to control.

label: body axis behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of one of the longitudinal axes of the extended body of the worm in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: localized movement variant
definition: Specific body regions of an animal display variations in movement compared to that observed in control animals.

label: hookless
definition: Male animals lack a copulatory hook.

label: dietary sugar response variant
definition: Animals exhibit enhanced negative effects on growth, health, development or metabolism, in response to dietary sugar-rich diets, compared to controls.

label: crossover variant
definition: The frequency and distribution of crossover events differs from that observed for controls.

label: autosomal nondisjunction meiosis
