definition: A non-sex chromosome fails to segregate away from its homologous chromosome, resulting in gametes with no or extra copies of the non-sex homolog.

label: aldicarb hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to aldicarb at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: cuticle morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the appearance or structure of the rigid external coating which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: L4 adult molt defect
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates L4 to adult transition.

label: cell corpse appearance delayed
definition: Animals exhibit a decreased rate programmed cell death pathway leading to the destruction of the cell, viewable in its terminally dismanteled form of a cell corpse, compared to that observed for control cells.

label: fat associated body size increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the size of fat containing organelles compared to control. In C. elegans this can be assayed by BODIPY 493/503 staining.

label: axon ultrastructure variant
definition: Animals display variations in the structure or organization of the components of the axon, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: circadian rhythm behavior variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the actions or reactions that recur with a periodicity associated with light/dark cycles, compared to control.

label: pharyngeal pumping shallow
definition: Pharyngeal muscle contractions show less displacement than that observed in control animals.

label: spicules protrude
definition: The elongated sclerotized structures covered by a hardened layer of cuticle in the male tail (which are actively everted during copulation to fasten the male copulatory fan to the vulva) constitutively extend into the external environment through the cloacal opening. In C. elegans males there are two copulatory spicules.

label: gonad arm morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the 'arm-like' form, structure or composition of the specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces gametes compared to control. In C. elegans the reproductive tract in the hermaphrodite has two equivalent gonad 'arms', while the male has a one-armed gonad.

label: protein aggregation induced reduction of life span
definition: The duration of viability in the adult phase of the life-cycle is lowered in response to the aggregation of proteins.

label: vesicle number variant
definition: Animals display variations in the number of spherical membrane-bound fluid-filled organelles, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: endo lysosomal degradation pathway defective
definition: The degradation of endocytosed and intracellular material does not occur to the same extent as it does in control animals.

label: nuclear number defective early emb
definition: Nuclear number is abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: iron homeostasis variant
definition: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of iron within an organism compared to control.

label: pharyngeal contraction variant
definition: Any variation in the muscle contractions that control feeding compared to control. Contractions are necessary for bacterial uptake from the surrounding environment.

label: fluoxetine resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of fluoxetine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: spermatogenesis to oogenesis switch defective
definition: Hermaphrodites continue to produce sperm past the time at which the transition to oogenesis normally occurs. Thus, germ cells that would normally become oocytes are transformed into sperm instead.

label: cuticle development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the formation of the rigid external coating (which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells) over time compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: P0 spindle position defective early emb
definition: Altered P0 spindle placement causes either a symmetric first division, a division in which P1 is larger than AB, or a division in which the asymmetry is exaggerated such that AB is much larger than normal.

label: proteasome core activity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations from controls in their protein degradation machinery, which functions through the hydrolysis of internal, alpha-peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain.

label: drug resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of a drug that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. Animals are not affected by exposure to the drug.

label: ganglion development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a cluster of neuron cell bodies (somata) over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control.

label: sterol induced dauer formation variant
definition: Variations in the processes that facilitate/permit dauer entry when exposed to specific sterol molecules, compared to control.

label: L3 larval development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the third larval stage compared to control.

label: cell junction variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the specialized region of connection between two cells or between a cell and the extracellular matrix compared to control.

label: shrinker
definition: The whole body undergoes longitudinal shortening in response to head touch or tail touch (Wormatlas).

label: AWC odorant chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of an animal in response to a volatile chemical stimulus that is usually received and processed by the AWC sensory neuron in control animals.

label: egg shape variable
definition: The overall structure or appearance of fertilized oocytes that are laid exhibit nonconsistent and significant deviation from that of control animals.

label: transformer
definition: XX animals are transformed into males or pseudomales .

label: cold resistant
definition: Animals exhibit increased ability to survive at low temperatures compared to controls.

label: apoptosis increased
definition: Any perturbation that causes an elevation in the frequency of cell death by apoptosis compared to control animals.

label: acetone chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute characteristic response to acetone compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of acetone.

label: manganese induced oxidative stress response
definition: Oxidative stress induced by manganese differs from that of control worms.

label: molt variant
definition: Animals exhibit variation in timing or ability to molt.

label: uterine vulval cell morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the epithelial cells that form the interface between the uterus and the vulva (likely via a multilayered set of flaps) compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: muscle cell attachment variant
definition: Any variation in the connection of a cell whose principal function is to provide contractile forces with its neighboring cells or tissues compared to control.

label: cell pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of a cell.

label: terminal bulb relaxation variant
definition: Variations in the rhythmic relaxations of the posterior pharynx (terminal bulb). In C. elegans the relaxation of the terminal bulb returns the grinder to its relaxed forward position.

label: organism temperature response variant
definition: Animals do not respond to changes in temperature or thermal stress in the same manner as control animals. In C.elegans this is often measured by changes in the expression of stress proteins or changes in life span.

label: early embryonic lethal
definition: Animal dies prior to the gastrulation stage of embryogenesis.

label: actomyosin contractility defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the flow rate or targeting of the cortical actomyosin network, which occurs during polarization as well as contraction of the contractile ring, compared to control animals.

label: male behavior variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in male-specific behaviors compared to control.

label: vulvaless
definition: No vulval tissue is produced. In C. elegans, this is usually a result of all six vulval precursor cells adopting a tertiary fate.

label: drug withdrawal response variant
definition: Any variation in the state or activity of an organism as a result of abrupt discontinuation or decreased dosage of a drug, compared to control.

label: anchor cell invasion variant
definition: Any variation in the process by which the gonad anchor cell makes contact with vulval cells in order to create a uterine-vulval connection. In C. elegans, this includes the loss of the basement membranes between these cells and the crossing of the basolateral portion of the anchor cell through this gap.

label: sodium chloride chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of sodium chloride. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, sodium chloride is an attractant.

label: touch-induced suppression of head movement defective
definition: Animals do not suppress exploratory head movements in response to anterior touch stimuli, unlike control animals.

label: vulval cell induction variant
definition: Vulval precursor cells inappropriately adopt fates that are normally restricted to other vulval precursor cells compared to control.

label: seam cell morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure, organization or placement of the population of the lateral, alae-producing epithelial cells (seam cells), compared to that observed in control animals.

label: large cytoplasmic granules early emb
definition: Abnormally large granules are observed in the cytoplasm of P0.

label: obsolete moderate dumpy
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: gland cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of gland cells compared to control animals.

label: mitochondria vesiculated
definition: Inner membrane of mitochondria are disconnected and form vesicular bodies.

label: organism hypersensitive ionizing radiation
definition: Animals exhibit increased sensitivity to the effects of ion producing radiation compared to control animals.

label: anticonvulsant resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of compounds that act as anticonvulsants that elicit a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: axon length reduced
definition: The length of one or more axons is reduced compared to the length of the corresponding axon(s) in control animals.

label: pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency.

label: receptor mediated endocytosis defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the cell-mediated uptake of external materials via receptor activity. Receptor-mediated endocytosis ensures specificity of transport and generally occurs via clathrin-coated pits and vesicles. In C. elegans, this is often judged by the lack of yolk uptake in oocytes.

label: inhibitors of na k atpase resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of sodium potassium ATPase antagonists that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: ouabain resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of ouabain that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans, resistance to ouabain is often assayed via body contraction response.

label: obsolete temporal frequency of sinusoidal movement variant
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: cell division polarity variant
definition: Any variation in the orientation of the physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells compared to control.

label: stress induced lethality increased
definition: Animal populations exhibit a further decrease in survival when exposed to stress stimuli compared to the lethality rate observed in control animals.

label: linker cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the linker cell compared to control animals.

label: sporadic pumping
definition: Pharyngeal pumping contractions are brief and occur arhythmically in response to stimulus compared to control.

label: germ cell partition morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of the compartment partitions in the germline of females/hermaphrodites that exist when nuclei are still connected to a common cytoplasm (rachis), compared to control animals.

label: nerve ring development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the major zone of overlapping axons in the head, which encircles the isthmus of the pharynx to form a tightly packed ring-like structure on the outside of the pharynx, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: phototaxis defective
definition: Animals do not respond via directed movement to light stimuli in the same manner as control animals. In C. elegans, animals move away from light.

label: male sperm fertilization defect
definition: Any perturbation that renders male derived sperm ineffective at fertilizing an oocyte.

label: muscle missing
definition: Any variation that results in a fewer than control number of muscle cells.

label: membrane fluidity increased
definition: Animals exhibit increased fluidity of cell membranes, compared to control animals.

label: alkaline pH chemotaxis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic movement towards typically attractive alkaline pH (pH higher than 7) compared to control. However animals tend to avoid very high pH levels (pH11).  pH is a measure of the acidity or basicity of an aqueous solution. In C. elegans animals chemotax toward higher alkaline pH.

label: cell polarity variant
definition: Contents or structures of a cell are no longer restricted/localized to their typical positions within the cell.

label: male nervous system development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the male nervous system over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals. The nervous system is involved in the coordination and control of bodily activities and the interpretation of information from the senses.

label: presynaptic region physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process in the region of the vesicle-filled varicosities of the synapse compared to control.

label: acetylcholine synaptic transmission variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the process of acetylcholine neurotransmitter-based communication from a neuron to a target cell across a synapse compared to control.

label: antimicrobial gene expression variant
definition: Changes in the levels of innate immune gene products in response to pathogen exposure are significantly different from that observed in control animals.

label: high oxygen hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to hyperoxic (high oxygen tension) conditions after a shorter exposure time compared to control.

label: diethyl ether hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to the anesthetic ether at lower concentrations or shorter response times than control animals.

label: backing absent
definition: Animals do not exhibit backward locomotion under conditions that induce backward locomotion in control animals.

label: organism X ray response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to X-ray radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: biofilm absent head
definition: Animals can move thorough a lawn of bacterially produced biofilm without accumulating an enormous amount of biofilm on its nose. When C. elegans is exposed to certain bacteria (e.g., Y. pestis), a biofilm accumulates on a worm's head. The presence of this biofilm inhibits feeding by the worm, and thereby prevents growth.

label: backward point velocity decreased
definition: Animals exhibit decreased velocity of backward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: shrunken intestine
definition: Intestine is shrunken and may appear constricted.

label: anterior cell migration defective
definition: The orderly movement of cells along the anterior axis of the animal is abolished, misdirected or incomplete compared to control.

label: predator escape defective
definition: Animals are less successful than controls in evading predators during predator-prey interactions.

label: chemosensory response variant
definition: Variations in the state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a chemical stimulus, compared to control.

label: germ cell compartment multinucleate
definition: Germ cell compartments contain multiple nuclei.

label: anoxia response attenuated
definition: Response to trace levels of oxygen is reduced or weakened compared to the response of control animals.

label: fainter
definition: Alternating periods of stopping and moving; Motion is interrupted by periods of inactivity lasting several seconds.

label: ectopic neuron
definition: Animals exhibit one or more neurons in locations not normally found in controls.

label: male specific lineage variant
definition: The descendants of a male specific precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: epithelial system development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the epithelial system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: copulatory structure development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the specialized structures of the animal which allow the successful transfer of sperm from one organism to another, compared to control.

label: vulval cell lineage variant
definition: The descendants of a vulval precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals. In C. elegans, the VPCs are P3.p-P8.p.

label: postembryonic development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of an animal over time, from hatching to adulthood, compared to control.

label: L4 lethal
definition: Animals die at the L4 stage of the life cycle.

label: protein aggregation induced paralysis
definition: Animals become paralyzed in response to aggregation of proteins like poly-glutamine or beta-amyloid.

label: Z1 male lineage variant
definition: Z1 descendents exhibit altered developmental programs in the male compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: adherens junction variant
definition: Any variation in a cell junction at which the cytoplasmic face of the plasma membrane is attached to actin filaments compared to control.

label: constipated
definition: Animals exhibit delayed or infrequent passage and/or expulsion of fecal matter.

label: dauer sensory system morphology variant
definition: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the dauer sensory system, compared to control. The dauer sensory system is used to perceive the physical and chemical environment during the dauer larval stage.

label: hyperinduction of antimicrobial peptide expression after infection
definition: Animals exhibit hyperinduction of expression of an antimicrobial peptide after an infection, compared to control animals.

label: paraquat resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of paraquat that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: male bursa development variant
definition: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the male bursa over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control. The male bursa consists of the lateral fan and rays (WormAtlas).

label: obsolete cell cycle slow
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: oxygen consumption increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increased rate of oxygen utilization compared to control animals.

label: high incidence male progeny
definition: Higher numbers of male progeny occur in the population compared to control populations. In C. elegans, the high incidence of males phenotype in a self-fertilizing hermaphrodite population is a result of an increase in X chromosome nondisjunction.

label: delayed reproductive maturity
definition: The animal's ability to reproduce, or start of reproduction occurs later than that observed for control animals.

label: L1 arrest
definition: The developmental program of the animals does not continue past the first larval stage (L1).

label: ectopic neurite outgrowth
definition: Neurons exhibit neurite outgrowth in locations not normally found in controls.

label: body development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the overall structure or appearance of the animal over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: protein export from nucleus defective
definition: The directed movement of a protein from the nucleus into the cytoplasm is impaired.

label: GLR development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the GLR accessory cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: biogenic amine physiology variant
definition: Any variation in the levels and/or localization of biogenic amines compared to control animals.

label: antibody staining variant
definition: Any variation in the characteristic expression of a gene product, as detected by antibody staining, compared to control animals.

label: posterior body dumpy
definition: The posterior part of the worm is shorter and stouter compared to control animals.

label: dopamine deficient
definition: Animals do not contain or are unable to maintain a the level of dopamine capable of initiating or maintaining dopamine-dependent cell activity compared to control animals.

label: nucleus defective early emb
definition: Nucleus is abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: egg size defective early emb
definition: Egg is smaller or larger compared to eggs of control animals.

label: ventral cord patterning variant
definition: Any variation in the developmental process that results in the creation of defined areas or spaces within the ventral cord to which cells respond and eventually are instructed to differentiate compared to control.

label: body axis pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency along a particular body axis compared to control.

label: muscle arm development defective
definition: Animals extend altered or fewer numbers of dorsal and or ventral muscle arms compared to control animals.

label: body behavior variant
definition: Activity characteristic of the body is altered compared to control.

label: organ senescence variant
definition: Any variation in the preprogrammed process that occurs in an organism that is associated with the dismantling of an organ and an overall decline in metabolic function compared to control animals. This may include variations in the rate or extent of morphological disarray and of the breakdown or organelles, membranes and other cellular components.

label: dauer buccal cavity morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form or composition of the cuticle-lined lumenal region which lies just behind the lips at the entrance to the pharyngeal lumen in dauer stage animals compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: enhanced recovery pumping response to light
definition: Animals exhibit an enhanced recovery pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that during the 0-10 seconds after removal of light exposure the pharyngeal pumping rate increases to a greater extent than in controls.

label: hermaphrodite self sterile
definition: Hermaphrodites fail to produce any viable progeny via self-fertilization. However, such hermaphrodites can successfully reproduce if mated to control males.

label: ATP levels increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the cellular levels of Adenosine-5'-triphosphate (ATP), compared to control. ATP is a nucleotide that plays a versatile role in cell biology.

label: sterile F0 48 hours post injection
definition: Injected worm stops producing embryos 48 hours after RNAi injection and contains no live/developing embryos at this time.

label: centrosome dynamics variant
definition: Animals vary in the directed or coordinated movement of their centrosomes during cell division, compared to the pattern of movement observed in control animals.

label: bag of worms
definition: A worm carcass is formed with retained eggs that hatch inside.

label: male T lineages variant
definition: The descendants of TL or TR cells in male animals exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: embryonic development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of an embryo over time, from zygote formation to hatching compared to control.

label: calcium channel modulator hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to a calcium channel modulator at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: body bend variant
definition: Any variation in the maximum ventral and dorsal flex of the animal compared to control animals.

label: pretzel arrest
definition: Cessation of development during the final two stages in embryogenesis, 'early pretzel' stage and 'late pretzel' stage, just prior to hatching. The animal now is folded into four lengths within the eggshell and resembles a pretzel. By early pretzel stage, the head begins to move independently from the body (Wormatlas).

label: dense core vesicle exocytosis variant
definition: Variations in the process of secretion of a class of membrane-bound vesicles found inside neurons, gland cells, and some epithelial cells in which the central core appears darkly stained when viewed in thin section by electron microscopy, compared to control. Exocytosis occurs via the fusion of the vesicle with the plasma membrane of a cell (Wormatlas).

label: spindle rotation variant
definition: Any variation in the rotation of the spindle compared to control.

label: neuron degeneration
definition: Cells specialized for receiving, conducting and transmitting impulses in the nervous system are observed to undergo a dramatic decrease in cell volume, collapse of the vacuoles and processes, and complete disintegration of the plasma membrane and most organelles.

label: vesicle morphology variant
definition: Animals display variations in the shape or size of their vesicles, which are spherical, membrane-bound fluid-filled organelles, compared to vesicles observed in control animals.

label: lead response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to lead compared to that observed in control animals.

label: division axis defective
definition: The cell division axis is not normal.

label: nuclear envelope organization variant
definition: The appearance and association of components along the double lipid bilayer enclosing the nucleus differs from controls. The NE separates nuclear contents from the rest of the cytoplasm and includes the intermembrane space, perinuclear space.

label: anterior pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of the anterior body axis compared to control.

label: anaphase bridging
definition: Chromosomal masses fail to fully separate and remained linked during anaphase.

label: body wall muscle thin filament variant
definition: Any variation in the extremely thin elongated cytoplasmic filament, usually composed principally of actin protein to form a myofilament lattice, as in muscle cells compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: postsynaptic region morphology variant
definition: The region opposite to the presynaptic region deviates in the structure, configuration or ratio of its components specific for receiving signals from the other side of the synapse compared to control.

label: metal response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific metal compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cell division precocious
definition: Cells divide at an earlier stage of development compared to control animals.

label: neurotransmitter response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific neurotransmitter compared to that observed in control animals.

label: kinker
definition: The animal moves or rests with uncharacteristic muscle spasms causing loss of smooth sinusoidal motion or body posture. Movement is often characterized by severe bending motions, more sharply angled and/or much deeper than stereotypical sinusoidal body bends of the control animals.

label: developmental morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts during a given developmental stage compared to control animals.

label: drug induced gene expression variant
definition: Gene expression of an animal is not influenced by drug treatment in the same manner as control animals.

label: transgene induced cosuppression variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the silencing of endogenous genes after introduction of repetitive exogenous cognate DNA compared to control.

label: no posterior pharynx
definition: Embryos fail to generate cells that give rise to the posterior portion of the pharynx. In C. elegans, the MS blastomere- derived pharyngeal cells constitute the posterior portion of the pharynx.

label: hypoosmotic shock hypersensitive
definition: Any variation in the ability to adjust to a decline in ambient solute concentrations, thereby causing the body to swell and explode.

label: chloride chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of chloride.

label: gut granule birefringence misplaced
definition: The birefringent inclusions typically found in the intestinal cytoplasm accumulate extracellularly in the intestinal lumen.

label: induced cell death variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the extent of activation of programmed cell death, compared to control.

label: cleavage furrow termination defective
definition: Cells exhibit defects in the maintenance or termination of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate during cytokinesis.

label: basal lamina development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the layer of connective tissue over the surface of tissues that serves to separate it from neighboring tissues, from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: cytokinesis defective early emb
definition: Cytokinesis is abnormal in the first or second stages of cell division.

label: uterus vacuole
definition: The uterus contains cavities, possibly indicative of inappropriate cell death.

label: lectin binding variant
definition: Animals differ from controls in the range, specificity, or presence of targets for exogenously applied lectins.

label: meiotic spindle rotation defective
definition: Cells undergoing meiosis exhibit defects in the rotation of the meiotic spindle.

label: adoption of fused vulval cell fate
definition: Vulval precursor cells forgo further cell division and fuse to the hypodermis instead of adopting their intended fate (becoming primary, secondary or tertiary vulval cells).

label: obsolete posterior region morphology abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: phagosome sealing defective
definition: The closure of a phagosome does not occur and it remains connected with the plasma membrane, leaving the lumen open to the outside.  Complete closure usually occurs once an apoptotic cell has been surrounded by an engulfing cell.

label: pharyngeal development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the pharynx (feeding organ) over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control. In C. elegans the pharynx is divided into the anterior and posterior regions. The anterior region includes the corpus (procorpus and metacorpus - first bulb) and the posterior region includes the isthmus and terminal bulb (second bulb).

label: behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: corpus contraction defect
definition: Any defect in the muscle contractions of the extended anterior region of the pharynx lying just anterior to the isthmus and terminal bulb (Wormatlas).

label: mRNA levels reduced
definition: Animals exhibit decreased levels of messenger RNA compared to control.

label: telomere length regulation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the processes that are required to maintain the length of telomeric DNA from generation to generation compared to control.

label: maternal sterile
definition: Animals produce no or very few embryos as a result of experimental treatment. This is in contrast to sterility due to genetic perturbations (maternal effect sterility).

label: membrane trafficking variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of substances in a cell, from one side of a membrane to another, compared to control.

label: ethyl methanesulfonate response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to ethyl methanesulfonate (EMS) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: excess hypodermal cells
definition: Embryos generate an excess number of hypodermal cells compared to control.

label: high sodium chloride concentration osmotic avoidance variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their avoidance response to high concentrations of sodium chloride solution compared to control.

label: metabolite content increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the quantity of metabolites, small molecule products or intermediates required for the metabolic functioning of the cell or organism.

label: peroxisome morphology variant
definition: The morphological appearance of peroxisomes is variant compared to control animals.

label: transgenerational accumulation of histone methylation
definition: The amount of histone methylation, for example as measured by the amount of H3K4me2, increases over successive generations

label: egg laying response to food variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in egg-laying behavior in response to food compared to control. In C. elegans, well-fed animals lay more eggs compared with starved animals.

label: velocity of movement variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the net velocity of an animal, that is, the maximum distance an animal traverses over an extended period of time, from that observed for control animals.

label: epithelial cell fusion failure
definition: Any perturbation that renders epithelial cells incompetent at undergoing membrane fusion during development.

label: ethanol hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to ethanol at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: VNC nuclear positioning variant
definition: Variations in spacing or location were observed between adjacent ventral cord nuclei or between ventral cord nuclei and another nucleus used as a reference point. In C. elegans, these nuclei are distributed equally and predictably, such that they can be unambiguously distinguished by their position.

label: pathogen adherence defect
definition: Pathogens are unable to adhere/colonize the surface of host animals. This defect is often associated with changes in cuticle surface properties of the host.

label: nose rounded
definition: The extreme anterior part of the body appears blunted in shape.

label: commissure variant
definition: Animals display variations in the structure, organization or path of the part of the axon that forms a bridge between body regions, compared to that in control animals.

label: pheromone induced dauer formation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the entry into the dauer stage when exposed to concentrations of chemicals that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: sterile F1
definition: Any variation that compromises the reproductive ability of an F1 generation animal.

label: somatic gonad precursor symmetrical sisters
definition: All somatic gonad precursor (SGP) daughters adopt a proximal fate resulting in an increase in the number of AC precursor cells at the expense of distal tip cells (DTC), which are thereby absent.

label: G2 checkpoint variant
definition: Mitotic cells exhibit variations during the passage through a cell cycle control point late in the G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle just before entry into M phase, nuclear division, compared to control cells.

label: embryonic somatic cell fate specification variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern acquisition of somatic cell fates in the embryo, from the time of zygote formation until hatching compared to control.

label: nuclear RNAi defective
definition: Animals fail to silence nuclear-localized RNAs. Animals still retain sensitivity to RNAi for those RNAs located outside of the nucleus.

label: fewer germ cells
definition: Germ cell populations are reduced compared to control animals.

label: microtubule organization biogenesis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure, composition or arrangement of a robust macromolecular array, composed primarily of tubulin, which forms long extended cytoskeletal elements compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: neurite morphology variant
definition: Animals display variations in the structure, organization of components, or spatial pattern of any projection stemming from a neuronal cell, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: tRNA expression increased
definition: Animals exhibit elevated levels of transfer RNA compared to control.

label: multipolar mitotic spindle
definition: Cells exhibit mitotic spindles with more than two poles.

label: hermaphrodite gonadal lineage variant
definition: The descendants of a gonadal precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs in the hermaphrodite compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: copulation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any processes that lead to the successful transfer of sperm from one organism to another.

label: organism starvation hypersensitive
definition: Animals show enhanced suceptibility to deprivation of nourishment, compared to control.

label: biogenic amine receptor antagonist resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of biogenic amine receptor antagonist that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: pathogen infection clearance variant
definition: Infected animals exhibit variations in the clearance of pathogen infection compared to controls.

label: cell cleavage delayed
definition: Any variation that causes a delay in the stereotypical cleavage event compared to control.

label: cuticle carbohydrate surface variant
definition: Animals exhibit an altered display of glycosylated proteins or lipids or altered access to glycosylated moieties along their surface from that observed in control animals of the same developmental stage. In C. elegans, variations in surface accessible glycosylated species are often revealed by altered lectin-binding from that observed in control animals.

label: roaming variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their movement at high-speed in the forward direction with brief backward movement compared to control. During roaming, control animals often traversing wide regions.

label: cuticle shedding defect
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement.

label: nose touch defective
definition: Animal fails to exhibit characteristic response after a nose-on collision with an object compared to control. In C. elegans, this is usually assayed with a hair or similar fiber. The nose is the anterior most tip of the animal.

label: growth inhibition response to chemical
definition: Animals do not grow fast or the quality of growth is decreased when exposed to a specific chemical compound when compared to control animals.

label: pronuclear migration reduced early emb
definition: Any variation in the movement/fusion of pronuclei in the fertilized oocyte compared to control. For example, lack of male pronuclear migration, female pronuclear migration variable, sometimes multiple female pronuclei, no or small spindle.

label: homolog association variant
definition: The association of homologs during diakinesis and the maintenance of their association through meiosis I as well as the preservation of centromeric cohesin between sister chromatids does not proceed as it does in control animals.

label: enhanced locomotion defective
definition: Animals do not exhibit an increase in speed when placed in an environment that relies on a combination of swimming and crawling behaviors compared to control.

label: XXX progeny
definition: Animals segregate progeny with 3 X chromosomes.

label: intestinal integrity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the integrity of the intestine, compared to controls.

label: cell acidification variant
definition: Variations in the processes that reduce the internal pH of a cell (measured by the concentration of the hydrogen ion), compared to control.

label: coiling variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the occurrence of a coil-like body posture compared to control animals. This includes the amount of time spent in a coil, the frequency with which coils form and the inappropriate formation of a coil, for example when attempting to locomote.

label: gonad sheath contraction rate increased
definition: Basal contraction rate and or peak contraction rate of the gonadal sheath is increased relative to control animals.

label: C lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the C blastomere exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: acetate chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to acetate compared to control animals.

label: dauer resistance to harsh conditions variant
definition: Variations which lead to the decreased ability of dauer larva to survive at extreme conditions, such as high or low temperatures, the presence of dilute acids, detergents, anesthetics, or even fixatives, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: tail protrusions
definition: Any irregular swelling in discrete regions of the tail, usually caused by a local defect in the normal smooth tapering of the hypodermis and/or cuticle (Wormatlas).

label: male sex muscle morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the muscles of the adult male reproductive system compared to control. In C. elegans males, the M myoblast gives rise to a much larger set of specialized muscles, compared to hermaphrodites, which differentiate within the tail region (Wormatlas).

label: ectopic cleavage furrow
definition: One or more cells exhibit one or more cleavage furrows in locations not normally found in control cells.

label: axoneme morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the microtubule-based fibrillar bundle (axoneme) that makes up the core of the middle part of the cilium (in a pattern of nine doublet microtubules attached to the membrane and a variable number of smaller singlet microtubules occupying the center). In C. elegans, the axoneme microtubules are arranged in a pattern of nine doublets attached to the membrane with seven smaller singlet microtubules occupying the center.

label: excess paternal pronucleus variant centrosome early emb
definition: More than one paternal pronucleus is present in the inviable one-cell embryo or there is a defect in centrosome structure.

label: Pausing increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the amount of time spent in a paused state, which is neither moving forward or backward, compared to control animals.

label: body morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of their anatomy between the head and the tail compared to control animals.

label: mitochondrial DNA repair variant
definition: Any variation in the process of restoring mitochondrial DNA after damage.

label: heme levels increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the amount of heme compared to control animals. Heme is any compound of iron complexed in a porphyrin (tetrapyrrole) ring.

label: body posture amplitude decreased
definition: Animals exhibit variations in body posture caused by a decrease in the extent of displacement measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control animals.

label: reproductive system morphology variant
definition: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the reproductive system, compared to control. The reproductive system is involved in the generation of progeny which contain genetic material inherited from the parents.

label: rays missing
definition: Any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan are absent.

label: necrotic cell death variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the cell death process that is morphologically characterized by a gain in cell volume (oncosis), swelling of organelles, plasma membrane rupture and subsequent loss of intracellular contents, compared to control.

label: endogenous synaptic event frequency reduced
definition: The rate (frequency) of currents elicited by fusion of a single endogenous vesicle of transmitter in the absence of presynaptic action potentials is decreased compared to control. Changes in frequency are indicative of presynaptic modifications.

label: serotonin synthesis defective
definition: Animals are unable to carry out the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of serotonin.

label: cleavage furrow defective early emb
definition: Embryos exhibit defects in the formation, maintenance or termination of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate during cytokinesis.

label: larval body morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of the animal as it progresses from hatching to adult compared to control animals.

label: obsolete male tail spike
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: polar body extrusion defective early emb
definition: Unextruded or resorbed polar body(ies) leading to an extra PNs in P0 and/or extra karyomeres in AB/P1.

label: meiotic DNA double strand break formation variant
definition: Any variation in the creation of double-strand breaks that occur during meiosis that may result in the initiation of meiotic recombination.

label: obsolete lectin staining variant
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: thermal bias in tracking variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the duration of the trajectory of the forward track in a thermal gradient compared to control.

label: harsh body touch resistant
definition: Animals do not respond to prodding with a fine platinum wire or similar tool compared to controls.

label: dauer gonad arrest variant
definition: Variations in the execution of the developmentally-regulated cell cycle arrest in the gonad during the dauer stage, compared to control.

label: extra and ectopic hypodermis
definition: Animals have one or more extra hypodermal cells, which are present in places they are normally not found, when compared to the number and location of these cells in control animals.

label: protein phosphorylation reduced
definition: Animals exhibit decreased levels of protein phosphorylation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: amino acid metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of amino acids within the organism or cell compared to control.

label: maternal pronucleus indistinct early emb
definition: Maternal pronucleus has a blurry appearance. The nuclear envelope does not have a crisp circular shape.

label: basement membrane remodeling variant
definition: Animals display variations in the manner in which the basement membrane (a thin, dense, sheet-like structure built on a network of polymeric laminin and type IV collagen) is remodeled, compared to control animals.

label: epithelial system morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form, composition or structure of the epithelial system that serves to protect the organism from the external environment compared to control.

label: maternal effect sterile
definition: Sterility caused by aberrant maternal components required for normal postembryonic development and/or function of the germ line.

label: cytokinesis variant
definition: Any variation that disrupts the cytoplasmic division of a cell during development compared to control.

label: no defecation cycle
definition: Animals lack the stereotyped sequence of muscle contractions that result in defecation over a fixed time period compared to control.

label: vulval muscle variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the sex-specific muscles in the hermaphrodite, over time, that are specialized for egg-laying compared to control. In C. elegans the contractions of the vulval muscles open the lips of the vulva to help in expelling an egg from the uterus (Wormatlas).

label: vulva cell fate specification variant
definition: Any aberrancy in the processes that govern acquisition of vulval cell fates compared to control animals.

label: arsenite hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to arsenite at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: ABa ABp EMS synchronous division early emb
definition: EMS divides at the same time that ABa and ABp divide.

label: growth variant
definition: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) compared to control animals.

label: mechanoreceptor current variant
definition: Animals differ from controls in their electrical response to mechanical stimulus.

label: level of transgene expression variant
definition: Any variation in the measured expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: reduced pathogen accumulation
definition: Animals exhibit a reduction in pathogen accumulation, persistent colonization, and luminal distension of the intestine.

label: sister chromatid segregation defective early emb
definition: Daughter nuclei are deformed and stay close to central cortex, cytokinesis defects.

label: touch receptor cell morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of any neuron within the class of sensory neurons responsible for relaying mechanical stimuli to the animal compared to control.

label: organism segment morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any anterior/posterior section of their anatomy compared to control animals.

label: unfolded protein accumulation
definition: Animals accumulate unfolded proteins in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) and or the mitochondria.

label: intestinal fluorescence increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that fluoresce in the intestine.

label: lannate resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of lannate that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: sperm fertility defective
definition: Any perturbation that renders sperm incompetent at fertilizing an oocyte.

label: silver hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to silver at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: pore forming toxin resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of pore forming toxins that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: sex muscle morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the sex muscles compared to control animals.

label: premature spermatid activation
definition: Any variation that results in the premature differentiation of spermatids into motile spermatozoa compared to control.

label: endoreduplication of hypodermal nuclei variant
definition: Any variation in the regulated re-replication of DNA in the hypodermal cells during a single cell cycle, compared to control.

label: roaming reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in their high-speed movement in the forward direction with brief backward movement compared to control. In C. elegans, Animals do not move more than a few body lengths from their starting position and searches occur locally with pivoting behavior.

label: egg retention
definition: Eggs are retained in the uterus at a later stage when compared with control animals.

label: aqueous negative chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to move away from repellent water soluble chemicals.

label: HSN differentiation precocious
definition: Specialization of HSN precursor cells to mature HSN neurons occurs at an earlier stage of development compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite fertility reduced
definition: Hermaphrodites exhibit a reduction in the production of new individuals owing to defects in gamete competence and/or function compared to control animals.

label: P cell misalignment at ventral midline
definition: Ventral midline blastomeres (P cells) are misaligned (not properly paired) along the ventral midline of larval animals.

label: cell fusion variant
definition: Variations in the ability of two or more individual cells to form a syncytium (a mass of cytoplasm containing several nuclei enclosed within a single plasma membrane) via the fusion of the plasma membranes. Cell fusion is dependent on the merging of lipid bilayer membranes as well as cytoplasmic mixing.

label: increased egg laying events during active
definition: More eggs are laid during the active phase compared with control animals, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: kinase activity reduced
definition: Any variation that results in a decrease in the catalytic phosphorylation activity of a kinase enzyme compared to control. Catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component). Kinases are enzymes capable of phosphorylating their respective substrates.

label: spike frequency variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the autonomously initiated periodic trains of calcium transients observed either at the cell body or the synaptic region, which are independent of presynaptic inputs.

label: environmental stimuli induced gene expression variant
definition: Gene expression of an animal is not influenced by environmental changes in the same manner as control animals.

label: vesicle organization variant
definition: Animals display variations in the distribution of spherical membrane-bound fluid-filled organelles, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: thrashing increased
definition: The number of body thrashes within an aqueous environment in a given period of time is increased, compared with control worms.

label: high pH avoidance defective
definition: Animals fail to avoid a high pH (alkaline) environment as compared to control animals.  This is at very high pH, for example around pH11.

label: social behavior variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in actions and responses that occurs predominantly, or only, in individuals that are part of a group, from that observed for animals in a control group.

label: food dependent growth variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in growth rate or the outcome of growth in response to food compared to control. In C. elegans, animals exhibit an increase or decrease in growth rate depending on the type of bacteria they are fed.

label: nonsense mRNA accumulation
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the regulated breakdown of mRNA transcripts in which an amino-acid codon has changed to a premature stop codon and the 3 prime end is not protected by a poly(A) tail.

label: cell cycle delayed
definition: Cells of the animals proceed through their replicative phase at a pace slower than observed for control cells.

label: temperature induced dauer formation increased
definition: Animals are more likely to form dauers at temperatures that do not induce dauer entry in control animals.

label: obsolete body wall muscle cell development variant
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: meiotic progression prophase variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any process necessary for the progression through prophase during meiosis compared to control animals.

label: apoptosis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any processes that influence the programmed cell death pathway. Induction of the apoptotic pathway triggers the activity of proteolytic caspases, which in turn lead to the destruction of the cell.

label: organism electrophilic stress hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to compounds that elicit electrophilic stress at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: muscle arm development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the process extension from the muscle belly by which the muscle cells reach to the nerve cords to obtain innervation over time from initial formation to mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: aqueous adaptation defective
definition: Animals do not exhibit characteristic desensitization to a water-soluble chemo-attractive signal in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control.

label: frequency of body bends increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the frequency of oscillations between adjacent body segments from that observed for control animals.

label: hermaphrodite tail spike variant
definition: Any variation in the structure or appearance of the thin cuticle specialization found at the extreme posterior end of the hermaphrodite tail compared to control.

label: amphid channel cilia bulbous
definition: The dendritic processes that normally extend through the amphid sensillum pore to the outside are truncated and have swollen ends as opposed to the extended and finger-like tips of channel cilia in control animals.

label: cleavage furrow not discrete early emb
definition: Embryos do not form a defined shallow groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate at the onset of cytokinesis.

label: P granule degradation defective
definition: The selective elimination of P granule components and subsequent aggregation of degraded components into PGL granules is disrupted.

label: inactive phase long
definition: Animals display uncharacteristically long periods during which they do not lay eggs compared to control, usually based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events. In C. elegans, long inactive phases can be observed in HSN-ablated and serotonin-deficient animals.

label: dauer nictation behavior variant
definition: Any variation in the behavior exhibited by dauer larva in which they crawl up upon the substrate and wave back and forth while standing on their tail compared to control. Nictation is often associated with the search for a new host.

label: cell cycle quiescence variant
definition: Any variation in the cell cycle arrest process that results in arrest during G1 phase, whereupon the cell enters a specialized resting state known as G0 or quiescence before entering the S phase, compared to control.

label: neuron degeneration enhanced
definition: Neurons undergo a dramatic decrease in cell volume, collapse of the vacuoles and processes, and complete disintegration of the plasma membrane and most organelles at a faster rate or greater extent than those under conditions that elicit this response in control animals.

label: fewer hypodermal cells
definition: The population of hypodermal cells is reduced compared to control animals.

label: endoreduplication variant
definition: Any variation in the multiple rounds of DNA replication that take place without chromosome condensation, segregation or cytokinesis compared to control. In C. elegans this process is normally seen in intestinal nuclei during each larval lethargus which results in adult intestinal nuclei with 32 copies (32C) of each chromosome(Wormatlas).

label: protein expression reduced cell specific
definition: Variations that result in a decrease in protein expression in specific cells compared to that observed in control animals.

label: meiotic progression during oogenesis variant
definition: Developing oocytes show defects in their initial entry or progression through the meiotic pathway (such as failure to exit diakinesis).

label: germ cell mitosis metaphase to anaphase transition block
definition: Germ line cells exhibit variations in the process whereby a cell progresses from metaphase to anaphase during mitosis, compared to control.

label: enzyme expression level reduced
definition: Variations that cause a decrease in the expression level of a biological catalyst, compared to control animals.

label: nuclear position defective early emb
definition: Embryos show defects in the placement of the nucleus to a specific location within the cell.

label: spindle pole pulling force variant
definition: Pulling forces on the astral microtubules at the spindle poles vary from that observed for control spindles.

label: amphid sheath cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for a amphid sheath cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: cytoplasmic RNAi defective
definition: Animals fail to silence cytoplasmic-localized RNAs. Nuclear-localized RNAs may still be sensitive to RNAi.

label: zygotic lethal
definition: Animals die after fusion of gametes without dividing.

label: cholinergic agonist hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to a cholinergic agonist at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: dauer death increased
definition: The survival of animals in the alternative larval stage which they enter when placed under conditions of environmental stress is reduced.

label: cell gamma ray resistant
definition: Cells fail to respond to the dosage of gamma irradiation that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, cells require longer exposure times to gamma irradiation to mimic the response observed in control animals.

label: thermotolerance increased
definition: Animals are able to survive for longer periods at temperatures above standard culture temperatures than control animals.

label: gonad sheath contractions variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the contraction of a thin continuous tube surrounding the proximal portions of the ovary and covering the maturing oocytes to the near portion of the distal gonad arm, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: bent posture decreased
definition: Animals exhibit decreased posture eccentricity (measure of circularity) or the mean number (and/or standard deviation) of instantaneous body bends.

label: dsRNA processing defective
definition: The production of silencing RNA from dsRNA is significantly deficient compared to controls. Deficiencies in this process can result in a defective RNAi response compared to controls.

label: sperm transfer cessation defective
definition: Any variation in the retraction of spicules after all sperm that exit the seminal vesicle have been released compared to control.

label: hypoxia response attenuated
definition: Response to low levels of oxygen is reduced or weakened compared to the response of control animals.

label: T lineages variant
definition: The descendants of TL or TR cells exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: molt defect
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the process of periodic shedding, of part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates each larval stage.

label: adult cuticle development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the formation of the rigid external coating (which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells) over time in adults compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: cell secretion variant
definition: Variations in the regulated release of substances by a cell compared to control.

label: connected mitochondria
definition: Mitochondria are interconnected by thin tubules of mitochondrial inner or outer membrane.

label: tail movement decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the movement of the most posterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: oxidative stress response variant
definition: Any variation in the state or activity of a cell (in terms of secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) in response to high levels of reactive oxygen species, compared to control.

label: cuticle fragile
definition: The strength of the cuticle is less robust than that observed for control animals. In C. elegans the strength of the cuticle is often assayed by it's ability to protect the animal from exposure to bleach or other compounds.

label: subviable
definition: Animals are barely alive, but not entirely dead.

label: hermaphrodite sexual development variant
definition: Genetically hermaphrodite animals exhibit deviations in the sexual program specific to hermaphrodites. In C. elegans, this refers to XX animals that develop as males or intersexuals instead of self-fertile hermaphrodites.

label: diplotene absent during oogenesis
definition: The diplotene stage is not observed in developing oocytes. Diplotene is a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the fourth stage of prophase I in meiosis, in which the homologous chromosomes begin to separate and the synaptonemal complex dissolves.

label: nonstriated muscle development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of muscle cells that lack transverse striations in its constituent fibers and are almost always involuntary, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: carbon dioxide response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to carbon dioxide compared to control.

label: spermatogenesis variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that influence the generation and maturation of spermatozoa (motile sperm) compared to control.

label: ATP levels variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the cellular levels of Adenosine-5'-triphosphate (ATP), compared to control. ATP is a nucleotide that plays a versatile role in cell biology.

label: axotomy response variant
definition: Any variation in the cellular and molecular pathways in a neuron in response to having its axon severed compared to severing in control animals.

label: pyrazine chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to pyrazine as defined by control animals. In C. elegans pyrazine is typically an attractant.

label: fertility reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a reduction in the production of new individuals that contain some portion of their genetic material inherited from that organism as a result of defective gametes.

label: tail bend angle variant
definition: Any variation in the extent of the maximum flex of the most posterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: sperm absent
definition: Animals lack fully specialized male gametes that are competent for fertilization.

label: extra and ectopic neuron
definition: Animals have one or more extra neurons, which are present in places they are normally not found, when compared to the number and location of these neurons in control animals.

label: cell component localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of the basic structural and functional components of cells compared to control. Includes the nucleus, endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus, mitochondria, endosomes, lysosomes, and peroxisomes as well as other vesicles and organelles.

label: protein acetylation variant
definition: Variations in the processes that incorporate acetyl groups to one or more amino acids within a protein, compared to control. An acetyl group is CH3CO-.

label: germline proliferation variant
definition: Nuclear divisions in the germ line are either expanded are reduced compared to control.

label: body width variant
definition: Animals vary in the distance between dorsal and ventral sides when measured across the body at right angles to the length, from that observed in control animals.

label: axon branching variant
definition: Animals display variations in the number or pattern of axonal tracts stemming from the neuron cell body, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: mRNA turnover variant
definition: Any variation in the ability of cells to monitor the quality of their mRNAs and degrade any transcripts that are poorly or incompletely translated compared to control.

label: spicule morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the appearance of the elongated sclerotized structures covered by a hardened layer of cuticle in the male tail (which are actively everted during copulation to fasten the male copulatory fan to the vulva) compared to control.

label: intestinal calcium signaling variant
definition: Any variation in the series of molecular signals in which an intestinal cell uses calcium ions to convert an extracellular signal into a response, compared to control.

label: movement erratic
definition: Animals exhibit a lack of consistency, regularity, or uniformity while traveling from one location to another.

label: pronuclear breakdown defective early emb
definition: Pronuclear breakdown is atypical in the inviable embryo.

label: nose movement variant
definition: The extreme anterior of the animal exhibits variations in its movement compared to control.

label: terminal arrest variable
definition: Variations that cause developmental progression to cease at different stages of the lifecycle.

label: RME-1 recycling endosome localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes, positive for the endocytosis protein RME-1, that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: glutathione levels variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of glutathione compared to control animals at a defined stage. Glutathione, the tripeptide glutamylcysteinylglycine, acts as a coenzyme for some enzymes and as an antioxidant in the protection of sulfhydryl groups in enzymes and other proteins.

label: autophagy block
definition: Animals fail to undergo the cellular catabolic process in which cells digest parts of their own cytoplasm.

label: autophagy reduced
definition: Animals exhibit reduced levels of the process by which their cells digest parts of their own cytoplasm, compared to control.

label: recycling endosome morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes,  that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: lumpy
definition: Animals have protrusions or bumps on their exterior which are not characteristic of control animals.

label: cell fate specification variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern acquisition of particular cell fates compared to control animals.

label: lipid depleted
definition: Animals are unable to take up or store lipids. In C. elegans, this defect results in pale, skinny and arrested larva.

label: preanal ganglion development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion which lies at the posterior limit of the ventral nerve cord in the tail over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: cytoplasmic structure defective early emb
definition: Areas devoid of yolk granules throughout the embryo.

label: fewer coelomocytes
definition: The number of coelomocytes are reduced compared to control animals. Coelomocytes are free-floating spherical cells lying in the pseudocoelomic cavity of animals that can endocytose many compounds.

label: body axis development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a discrete axis of an animal's anatomy over time, compared to control animals.

label: pathogen infected pharynx increase
definition: Animals exhibit a greater extent of pathogen invasion into the pharynx compared to control.

label: sperm morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the mature male gamete, which merges with an oocyte to create a fertilized embryo copared to control (Wormatlas).

label: inner labial morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the inner labial ring compared to control. In C. elegans, the ring is composed of six sensilla, which include associated neurons IL1 & IL2.

label: high susceptibility to induced DNA damage
definition: Nematodes exposed to DNA damaging agents or conditions exhibit greater susceptibility to DNA damage than other animals.

label: obsolete vulval cell induction abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: egg laying imipramine hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to exogenous imipramine at a lower concentration or within a shorter time period than control animals under the same conditions.

label: endogenous zinc levels increased
definition: Animals exhibit increased levels of endogenous zinc compared to control animals.

label: pronuclear migration defective early emb
definition: Pronucleus migration is abnormal in the inviable embryo.

label: eating variant
definition: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of an organism causing an alteration in the ingestion of food compared to control animals.  In C. elegans the main food source is bacteria and alterations in eating behavior usually lead to malnutrition.

label: muscle cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the muscle cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: nuclear number variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the number of nuclei contained in a particular cell type compared to control.

label: no uterus
definition: Animals lack the portion of the somatic gonad which encloses the fertilized eggs after their passage through the spermatheca (Wormatlas).

label: hook morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of the structure that lies on the ventral surface just anterior and central to the base of the spicule openings (small lump on the gubernaculum of the male tail) and contains a sensory structure called the hook sensillum, compared to control. In C. elegans the hook is necessary for proper male mating.

label: hook development variant
definition: Any variation in the development of the structure that lies on the ventral surface just anterior and central to the base of the spicule openings (small lump on the gubernaculum of the male tail) and contains a sensory structure called the hook sensillum, compared to control. In C. elegans the hook is necessary for proper male mating.

label: defecation contraction asynchronous
definition: The rhythmic contractions of the muscles coordinating the elimination of gut contents are no longer synchronized compared to control.

label: cell cycle timing defective early emb
definition: Cell cycle timing is abnormal during the first four cell divisions.

label: squat
definition: Squat animals are dumpy as homozygotes, but roll as heterozygotes.

label: fewer eggs in utero
definition: Adult animals display a smaller number of eggs inside the uterus compared to controls

label: dorsal ganglion development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion that lies dorsally beside the nerve ring in the head over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control. In C. elegans, It contains neuron cell bodies that send their neuronal processes into the ring and longitudinal nerves, but form no local neuropil separate from the nerve ring. The dorsal ganglion is in close contact with the dorsal hypodermal cord (Wormatlas).

label: pathogen induced gene expression variant
