definition: Gene expression of an animal is not influenced by the exposure to disease causing agents in the same manner as control animals.

label: embryonic cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit deviations at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell, in any physical or chemical process required for an embryonic cell to carry out its normal function and activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli.

label: methyl methanesulfonate hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to the chemical mutagen methyl methanesulfonate (MMS) a methanesulfonate ester and alkylating agent at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. In C. elegans, increased sensitivity to MMS can be observed as a decrease in egg hatch upon acute exposure or inhibition of growth after chronic exposure compared to control animals given the same treatment.

label: obsolete neuronal branching variant
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: anterograde transport variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell body toward the cell periphery in nerve cell axons, compared to control.

label: lipid synthesis defective
definition: The de novo synthesis of any lipid species is reduced compared to that observed in control animals.

label: suppressed pharyngeal pumping defective
definition: Animals do not exhibit a decrease in pumping rate when treated with specific compounds (such as pheromones) as is observed for control animals.

label: alternative lengthening of telomeres
definition: A telomerase-independent telomere maintenance pathway that allows for strains to survive in the absence of telomerase.

label: dominant negative enzyme
definition: Any variation within an enzyme that causes it to act antagonistically towards the wild-type enzymatic product. These mutations usually result in an altered molecular function (often inactive) and are characterized by a dominant or semi-dominant phenotype.

label: premature spermatocyte germ cell differentiation
definition: Unspecialized male germ cells (spermatocytes) prematurely acquire the specialized properties of functional sperm.

label: feeding reduced
definition: Animals consume less food than control animals

label: ascaroside biosynthesis variant
definition: The production or regulation of ascaroside molecule populations differs from that of control animals.

label: excretory cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the excretory cell compared to control animals.

label: ligand binding variant
definition: Any variation of the specific binding of a molecule to its partner, which typically results in a change in cell activity, compared to control.

label: cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell, in any physical or chemical process required for the cell to carry out its normal functions or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: adult pigmentation variant
definition: Adult animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter its transparency/translucency compared to control animals.

label: body wall muscle contraction interval during defecation abnormal
definition: Any variation in the time interval between successive contractions of the body wall muscles during the defecation motor program compared to cantrol.

label: germ cell cytoplasmic morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the composition or structure of the contents within a germ cell, excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, compared to control. Germ cells include sperm, oocytes, and their precursors.

label: procorpus contraction defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the muscle contractions of the anterior region of corpus, the area responsible for allowing food to enter the corpus.

label: aster defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the array of microtubules emanating from a spindle pole that do not connect to kinetochores.

label: current measurement variant
definition: Any observed variation in the measurement of current across the cell membrane compared to measurements in control animals. Current is a flow of electric charge through a medium.

label: blast cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of blast cells compared to control animals.

label: antihelmintic response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to an agent that destroys or causes the expulsion of parasitic intestinal worms compared to that observed in control animals.

label: spermatheca development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the somatic gonad structure that connects the distal gonad arm to the uterus over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: isoamyl alcohol chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of isoamyl alcohol. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, isoamyl alcohol is an attractant.

label: mRNA poly-A tail length decreased
definition: Animals exhibit one or more mRNAs with decreased length of the 3' polyadenine tail, compared to control.

label: mitochondrial metabolism variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways of the mitochondria compared to control.

label: cell fate transformation to pharyngeal muscle
definition: Animals develop pharyngeal muscles from precursor cells that do not normally produce pharyngeal muscles.

label: larval defecation defect
definition: Animals fail to expel fecal matter during the larval stage.

label: SDS sensitive dauer
definition: Any variation that decreases the ability of dauer larva to tolerate the exposure to sodium dodecyl sulfate (a detergent) compared to control.

label: protein expression increased
definition: Any change that results in higher than normal levels of protein expression compared to control animals.

label: coelomocyte morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of coelomocytes compared to control animals.

label: desynapsis defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the asymmetric diassembly of the synaptonemal complex during progression through meiosis.

label: obsolete level of reporter gene expression variant
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: male tail curling serotonin hypersensitive
definition: Males respond to serotonin by curling their tails at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. In C. elegans males respond to serotonin with a tight ventral curling of the male tail and posterior body.

label: organism development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a worm at any time from its fertilization to adulthood compared to control.

label: ammonium chloride chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure in directed movement in response to ammonium chloride compared to control. In C. elegans, NH4Cl is an attractant. NH4Cl has also subsequently been used to assay for Cl- attraction in C. elegans.

label: chloride chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to chloride. In C. elegans, chloride is typically an attractant.

label: body proportion increased
definition: Animals exhibit increases in the body-area-to-length ratio and/or the width-to-length ratio, compared to control animals.

label: imipramine hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to imipramine at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: no transport middle segment cilia
definition: The bidirectional transport of molecules along the middle segment of axonemal microtubules of the cilia is absent.

label: anterior pharynx extra cells
definition: Embryos generate an excess number of anterior derived pharyngeal cells. In C. elegans, embryos generate an excess number of AB blastomere-derived pharyngeal cells. This hyperinduction of anterior pharyngeal tissue is associated with defects in fate specification of the ABp blastomere.

label: X cluster small RNA expression variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations from controls in the expression, biogenesis, processing, or stability of the small X-chromosome derived RNAs (X cluster) species of small RNA.

label: bromide chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to bromide. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards bromide.

label: periodic spicule prodding defective
definition: Males exhibit defects in the continuous prodding of spicule tips at the vulva prior to prolonged spicule insertion.

label: acetylcholinesterase activity variant
definition: Any variation in the measured levels of acetylcholinesterase (AChE) activity compared to control animals.

label: male germline proliferation variant
definition: Nuclear divisions in the germ line of male animals are either expanded are reduced compared to control.

label: pachytene arrested germline nuclei
definition: Germline nuclei do not progress through pachytene to diplotene.

label: vesicle maturation defective
definition: Vesicles, including those in cells, cell bodies, or synaptic terminals, do not properly form or maintain an intermediate state, such as remain coated with a clathrin coat.

label: extra excretory cells
definition: Animals produce an excess number of excretory cells compared to controls.

label: isoamyl alcohol chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to isoamyl alcohol as defined by control animals. In C.elegans isoamyl alcohol is typically attractive.

label: RNAi resistant
definition: Animals show reduced susceptibility to gene silencing triggered by double stranded RNA (RNAi), compared to control.

label: mRNA expression variant
definition: Variations in the biogenesis and stability of messenger RNA molecules compared to control.

label: cytokinesis variant emb
definition: Any variation that disrupts the cytoplasmic division of a cell during embryonic development compared to control.

label: excretory gland cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a gland cell of the secretory-excretory system over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: ovulation variant
definition: Any variation that disrupts the release of a mature oocyte into the spermatheca (for subsequent fertilization), compared to control.

label: oocyte septum formation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the partitioning of oocytes from each other compared to control animals.

label: progressive muscle detachment
definition: The connection between cell(s) whose principal function is to provide contractile forces and its neighboring cells or tissues diminishes over time.

label: organism oxidative stress response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to oxidative stress compared to that observed in control animals.

label: embryo disorganized
definition: Embryos fail to be organized in the same manner as observed in control animals.

label: lysosome organization biogenesis variant
definition: Variations in the processes that are carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a lysosome, compared to control.

label: cloacal development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the epithelial chamber that links the genital and alimentary tracts to the exterior via the anus (cloacal opening) over time compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: track length decreased
definition: Animals exhibit decreased length of the minimum enclosing rectangle surrounding the worm body on a solid medium, as viewed through the microscope.

label: male tail sensory ray differentiation variant
definition: Variations in the processes leading to the specialization of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan compared to control.

label: mitochondrial respiratory complex I variant
definition: The protein complex located in the mitochondrial inner membrane that is the first entry point for electrons into the electron transport chain and catalyzes proton translocation coupled to the oxidation of NADH by ubiquinone, differs in activity, composition, or organization from that of controls.

label: chemosensation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any of a series of events in which an organism receives a sensory chemical stimulus, converts it to a molecular signal, and recognizes and characterizes the signal, compared to control.

label: attraction signal defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the production of the sensory signal to attract males.

label: cell membrane organization biogenesis variant
definition: Variations in the process(es) involved in the assembly, transport, arrangement or disassembly of cell membrane structures or components compared to control.

label: nuclei small
definition: Nuclei of specific cells are smaller compared to control animals.

label: postembryonic behavior variant
definition: Behavior characteristic of postembryonic stage(s) is altered compared to control.

label: excess neurite outgrowth
definition: Any variation that causes an increase in the frequency of neurite (axon or dendrite) outgrowth. As a result, an excess number of neuronal projections are generated.

label: precocious heterochronic variations
definition: Variations that result in the acceleration of the rate, frequency or extent of the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition, compared to control.

label: osmotic avoidance defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic avoidance response to solutions of high osmotic strength as defined by control animals.

label: larval arrest
definition: The developmental program of the animals halts at any larval stage and thus fails to reach adulthood. In C.elegans, this occurs anytime during L1-L4 stage.

label: nicotine resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of nicotine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: RAB-11 recycling endosome localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes, positive for the RAB protein RAB-11, that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: pathogen susceptibility increased
definition: Animals are more prone to infection compared to control.

label: oocytes small
definition: The size of haploid female germ cells (oocytes) are significantly smaller compared to control.

label: ciliated neuron physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the ciliated neuron to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: UV induced mitotic germ cell arrest defective
definition: Animals do not arrest mitotic germ cell division, as control animals, when treated with UV radiation.

label: solitary feeding increased
definition: Animals disperse across a bacterial lawn and feed alone. When food is limiting, they can aggregate into swarms or clumps, but disperse once again when food is absent.

label: lysine chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute characteristic response to lysine as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, lysine is an attractant.

label: plate tap habituation variant
definition: Any variation in the decrease in a behavioral response to a repeated plate tap stimulus compared to control.

label: ALM migration variant
definition: Any variation in the normal posterior movement of the ALM mechanosensory neurons from their birthplace (anterior to the V1 hypodermal cell) to positions in between the V2 and V3 cells in the embryo compared to control animals.

label: transgene expression undetectable
definition: The expression of a gene product produced by DNA coded for by exogenous genetic material that has been introduced into the organism is reduced below the threshold of detection.

label: fat associated body size decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the size of fat containing organelles compared to control. In C. elegans this can be assayed by BODIPY 493/503 staining.

label: male sex muscle development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the muscles of the adult male reproductive system over time form their initial formation to their mature structure compared to control.

label: epidermis muscle detached
definition: The cell(s) whose principal function is to provide contractile forces, is separated from the adjacent epidermis.

label: embryonic developmental delay early emb
definition: The developmental progression of an early embryo over time, from its formation to its mature structure is delayed compared to control.

label: cell component morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of the basic structural and functional components of cells compared to control. Includes the nucleus, endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus, mitochondria, endosomes, lysosomes, and peroxisomes as well as other vesicles and organelles.

label: ventral closure defective
definition: The animal displays defects in any step of the ventral enclosure process resulting an embryo that is not enclosed and or with interior cells protruding out of the embryo.

label: marginal cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a marginal cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control. A marginal cell is a pharyngeal cell that connects the basement membrane to the apices of the triangle-shaped pharyngeal lumen.

label: instantaneous velocity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the mean translocation of the points along the animal's track compared to control.

label: reproductive system development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the reproductive system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: sensillum accessory cell morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of the sensillum channel including the sheath and or socket cells, their junctions with each other, channel neurons or surrounding epithelia compared to control.

label: sexual maturation defective
definition: The developmental process by which a progressive change in the state of some part of an organism specifically contributing to its ability to form offspring is impaired.

label: phentolamine resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of phentolamine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: apoptotic arrest
definition: Cells fail to complete the form of programmed cell death characterized by rounding-up of the cell, retraction of pseudopodes, reduction of cellular volume (pyknosis), chromatin condensation, nuclear fragmentation (karyorrhexis), classically little or no ultrastructural modifications of cytoplasmic organelles, plasma membrane blebbing (but maintenance of its integrity until the final stages of the process) and engulfment by resident phagocytes.

label: polar body reabsorbed early emb
definition: Polar body is reabsorbed in the one- to four-cell embryo.

label: larval lethal
definition: The animal dies at any time between hatching and onset to adulthood.

label: golgi apparatus localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as the Golgi apparatus, that traffic material from the endoplasmic reticulum or various endosomes, and process proteins for secretion, compared to control.

label: epithelial cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the epithelial cell to carry out its normal functions or activities, compared to control animals.

label: posterior body uncoordinated
definition: The movement of the posterior part of the worm is not coordinated with the rest of the body.

label: rachis morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the nucleus-free core of germ line cytoplasm in the gonad compared to control animals. In the C. elegans germline, nuclei exiting mitosis and entering meiosis are arranged along the cortex of the germline, partially enclosed by cellular membrane, forming a nucleus-free core of germline cytoplasm, called the rachis.

label: zinc toxicity resistant
definition: Animals fail to exhibit toxicity to the concentration of zinc that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans toxic responses to zinc include delayed development or lethality.

label: obsolete dauer sensory system plug variant
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: multiple hooks
definition: Male animals exhibit multiple copulatory hooks. In wild type C. elegans males, a single hook is normally present.

label: protein protein interaction variant
definition: Variations in the selective and non-covalent physical association between two or more proteins, compared to control.

label: plugged on body
definition: Males receive copulatory plugs from other males, deposited elsewhere on their bodies, in the absence of any orifice. This typically involves penetration of the depositing male's spicules directly through the cuticle of the recipient male.

label: accumulated germline cell corpses
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the quantity of germ line cells that have undergone programmed cell death but have not been engulfed.

label: crossover interference variant
definition: Animals differ from controls in respect to the frequency of expected double crossover events observed.

label: defecation cycle variant
definition: Any variation in the stereotyped sequence of muscle contractions that result in defecation over a fixed time period compared to control .

label: aldicarb resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of aldicarb that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: pseudocoelom morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the appearance of the body cavity compared to control. In C. elegans , an aberrancy in the psedocoelom can involve an accumulation of fluids or fluorescent reporters.

label: spindle defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during a cell cycle.

label: cell corpse degradation variant
definition: Variations in the process(es) that constitute cell corpse degradation within the engulfing cell compared to control.

label: centrosome biogenesis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the formation, maturation or disassembly of the centrosome (a subcellular body consisting of two centrioles embedded in a protein matrix).  The centrosome serves as a microtubule organizing center as well as a regulator of cell-cycle progression.

label: axon varicosities
definition: Animals display markedly swollen areas along their axons, which are larger than synaptic varicosities in control animals.

label: locomotory rhythm variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in locomotor activity during its light/dark cycle from that observed in control animals.

label: head notched
definition: The most anterior portion of the animal contains a V-shaped indentation.

label: extracellular matrix variant
definition: Any variation in the makeup, density or area of the ECM compared to control.

label: protein aggregation induced associative learning variant
definition: Variations in the behavioral plasticity induced by the integration of two sensory signals in response to the aggregation of proteins.

label: hypodermis disorganized
definition: Hypodermal cells fail to be organized in the same manner as observed in control animals. In C. elegans, hypodermal cells typically organize into distinct dorsal, lateral and ventral rows and cover the entire body.

label: neuron cell body absent misplaced
definition: The body of a neuron is not where it should be when compared to control animals; it is absent or misplaced.

label: endocytic recycling compartment organization and biogenesis defective
definition: Animals exhibit disruptions in tubular or tubulo-vesicular structures that function in endocytic transport from early to recycling endosomes.

label: multiple nuclei early emb
definition: Embryos contain more than one nucleus per cell in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: muscimol response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to muscimol compared to that observed in control animals. Muscimol is a GABA-A receptor agonist.

label: spermatocyte meiosis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the meiotic divisions undergone by the primary and secondary spermatocytes to produce haploid spermatids (non-motile sperm) compared to control.

label: cleavage furrow initiation defective early emb
definition: Embryos exhibit defects in the formation of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate at the onset of cytokinesis.

label: nose resistant to fluoxetine
definition: The nose of an animal fails to respond to the concentration of fluoxetine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: glycosyltransferase activity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their catalytic ability the transfer glycolsyl groups from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor) often measured by a reduction in the amount of glycosylated products compared to that observed in control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: alae variant
definition: Any variation in the small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle, lengthwise along the body compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: spindle orientation variant AB or P1 early emb
definition: The orientation of the spindle is aberrant in either the AB or the P1 cell.

label: dauer constitutive
definition: Formation of dauer larvae under conditions that do not favor dauer formation.

label: neurite development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a neuronal extension (such as axons or dendrites) over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control.

label: tube morphogenesis variant
definition: Variations in the process by which the anatomical structures of a tube are generated and organized, compared to control. Morphogenesis pertains to the creation of form or shape.

label: L4 larval development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the fourth larval stage compared to control.

label: intercellular junction variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the specialized region of connection between two cells compared to control.

label: echo defecation cycle
definition: Muscle contractions that make up the defecation motor program are repeated before the onset of the next cycle unlike in control animals.

label: benzaldehyde chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of benzaldehyde. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, benzaldehyde is an attractant.

label: early divisions prolonged
definition: The time interval in which early embryonic cell divisions occur is increased compared to control.

label: transgene expression reduced
definition: Any decrease in the intensity of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: tunicamycin resistant
definition: Animals respond to tunicamycin at a higher concentration or a longer exposure compared to control animals.

label: apoptosis fails to occur
definition: Cells do not undergo the form of programmed cell death characterized by rounding-up of the cell, retraction of pseudopodes, reduction of cellular volume (pyknosis), chromatin condensation, nuclear fragmentation (karyorrhexis), classically little or no ultrastructural modifications of cytoplasmic organelles, plasma membrane blebbing (but maintenance of its integrity until the final stages of the process) and engulfment by resident phagocytes.

label: pentanol chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute characteristic response to pentanol compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of pentanol.

label: synaptic remodeling variant
definition: The polarity reversal process by which synaptic components are removed from one side of the synapse and then reformed on the opposite cell does not occur or occurs in a different manner than in controls. In C. elegans, at the end of the L1 stage, the DD neurons undergo a complete polarity reversal such that the ventral synapses disappear and new synapses are formed on opposing dorsal body muscles.

label: molting arrhythmic
definition: Molting cycles do not occur in a temporally controlled manner and cannot be synchronized across a population.

label: endoplasmic reticulum morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the endoplasmic reticulum compared to control. The endoplasmic reticulum (ER) is an irregular network of membranes, that occurs in the cytoplasm, and forms a complex meshwork of tubular channels. The ER has two forms, rough (or granular), with ribosomes adhering to the outer surface, and smooth (with no ribosomes attached).

label: constitutive larval display
definition: Animals display surface antigens throughout all larval stages, unlike Bristol N2 worms, which display the antigens only during one larval stage.

label: anus morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the structural appearance of the caudal opening of the rectum in the tail compared to control animals.

label: gene expression variant
definition: Variations in the processes that convert a gene's coding sequence into a mature gene product or products (proteins or RNA), compared to control.

label: organism pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of the organism.

label: grinder relaxation defective
definition: Failure of the grinder to come to a full relaxed position between pumps compared to control.

label: organism starvation response variant
definition: Any variation in the state or activity of an organism as a result of deprivation of nourishment, compared to control.

label: egg laying response to drug variant
definition: Characteristic response to drugs with respect to egg-laying behavior varies compared to control.

label: actomyosin cytoskeletal tension variant
definition: The tension of the cytoskeleton comprised of the actomyosin network differs from controls. This tension can be measured by laser-cutting of the actomyosin cytoskeleton and observing any differences the recoil velocity of cortex adjacent to the cut site.

label: sexually dimorphic physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required to carry out sex-specific activities or to be able to perceive and respond to sex-specific stimuli compared to control.

label: vulva development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the egg-laying organ of female and hermaphrodite nematodes over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control. In nematodes, the vulva is formed from ventral epidermal cells during larval stages to give rise to a fully formed vulva in the adult.

label: hormone metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the degradation, biosynthesis or accumulation of hormones within the organism compared to control. Hormones are naturally occurring substances secreted by specialized cells that affect the metabolism or behavior of other cells possessing functional receptors for the hormone.

label: cadmium response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to cadmium compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cAMP chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of cAMP.

label: non-living barrier escape defective
definition: Animals are less successful than controls in extracting themselves from mesh or other non-living obstructing obstacles.

label: organism heat response variant
definition: Any variation in the state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, gene expression, etc.) in response to heat (high temperatures above the optimal temperature for that organism), compared to control.

label: plasma membrane composition variant
definition: Any variation in the components that make up the semipermeable bilayer surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment compared to control.

label: multiple cytoplasmic cavities early emb
definition: Multiple vesicles, vacuoles, or cavities are seen during early embryogenesis.

label: intestinal cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of intestinal cells compared to control animals.

label: protein stabilization variant
definition: Any variation in the ability of a protein to resist disintegration via chemical or physical modifications compared to control.

label: germ cell ionizing radiation response variant
definition: Germ cells exhibit variations in their response to ionizing radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: trimethadione resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of trimethadione, which acts as an anticonvulsant, that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: organism region behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of a certain defined body area of an animal in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: coelomocyte uptake defective
definition: Fluid-phase endocytosis by coelomocytes is less frequent or efficient compared to control.

label: inhibitors of sodium potassium ATPase hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to inhibitors of sodium potassium ATPase at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: transgene expression increased
definition: Any increase in the intensity of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: cell stress response variant
definition: Variations in the activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress, compared to control. The stress is usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

label: pharyngeal muscle morphology variant
definition: Any variations associated with the characteristic morphology of the pharyngeal muscle such as shape, birefringence etc compared to control.

label: recovery from enhanced locomotion variant
definition: Animals that exhibit an increase in locomotion activity do not return to basal level locomotion activity at the same rate as that of control animals.

label: germ cell partition absent
definition: Animals lack germ cell partitions (germ cell compartments).

label: AWB morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of either of a set of two ciliated wing neurons, AWBL or AWBR, of the amphid sensilla, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: resistant to mutagens
definition: Animals survive longer than control animals after or during exposure to DNA damaging agents.

label: hermaphrodite sterile
definition: Hermaphrodites fail to generate viable self-progeny and/or cross-progeny.

label: inhibitor of serotonin uptake variant
definition: Treatment with inhibitors of serotonin reuptake does not elicit the same response as observed for control animals.

label: protein sumoylation variant
definition: Variations in the process by which one or more SUMO moieties are added to a protein, compared to control.

label: pathogen release variant
definition: Infected animals exhibit variations in the process of releasing pathogens back into the environment, compared to control.

label: male response to hermaphrodite variant
definition: Any variation in the response by the male to a hermaphrodite after initial contact following mate finding compared to control. In C. elegans the male stops forward locomotion, presses the ventral side of his tail against his partner's body, and begins moving backward along the hermaphrodite. Male response behavior is initiated when sensory neurons located in the rays of his tail contact a potential mate.

label: oocyte meiotic maturation variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a developing oocyte, from diakinesis to metaphase (meiosis I), in response to a signal compared to control animals. Meiotic maturation is accompanied by nuclear envelope breakdown (germinal vesicle breakdown), cytoskeletal rearrangement and meiotic spindle assembly.

label: developmental pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of a particular developmental stage of the amimal compared to control animals.

label: presynaptic component localization variant
definition: Animals display variations in the distribution of the constituents that make up the synaptic machinery such as those required for priming, docking or fusion of vesicles at the active zone, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: neuronal synaptic transmission variant
definition: Any variation in the process of information transfer between two neurons; usually in reference to chemical synapses, but can also be used to refer to electrical synapses compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: axodendritic polarity variant
definition: Animals fail to establish or maintain characteristics that delineate the dendrite from the axon. The exclusion of presynaptic components from the dendrite is one indication of axodendritic polarity.

label: age associated fluorescence increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the intensity of fluorescence signals in intestinal cells with advancing age, compared to control.

label: halothane hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to the lipid-soluble anesthetic halothane at lower concentrations or shorter response times compared to control animals.

label: organism pathogen response defective
definition: Animals exhibit a defective response to pathogens.

label: rhythm slow
definition: The timing of a biological cycle that recurs with regularity is delayed compared to control.

label: endocytic transport variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the directed movement of substances into, out of or mediated by the endosome, a membrane-bound organelle that trafficks material to different compartments of the cell or back to the plasma membrane for recycling compared to control.

label: backward point velocity increased
definition: Animals exhibit increased velocity of backward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: body wall cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a body wall muscle cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: intraflagellar transport accelerated
definition: The rate, frequency or extent of bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum is increased compared to control.

label: organism predator response variant
definition: Predator-prey interactions differ from that observed in control interactions.

label: meiosis defective early emb
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the progression of meiosis which ultimately result in embryonic lethality.

label: germ cell compartment size variant
definition: Any variation in germ cell compartment size compared to control.

label: ligand gated channel activity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the actions of a channel that catalyses the transmembrane transfer of a cation when acetylcholine has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts compared to control animals.

label: transgene silencing variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the homology-dependent transcriptional level silencing of the expression of exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism, compared to control. In C. elegans this silencing occurs only in the germline.

label: ectopic pharyngeal muscle
definition: Animals exhibit one or more pharyngeal muscle cells in locations not normally found in controls.

label: cell UV response variant
definition: Cells exhibit variations in their response to ultraviolet radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: pharyngeal relaxation variant
definition: Any variation in the relaxation of pharyngeal muscles after contraction events compared to control.

label: resistant to protein aggregation induced paralysis
definition: Animals fail to respond to the aggregation of proteins that elicits a paralysis response in control animals.

label: Z4 male lineage variant
definition: Z4 descendants exhibit altered developmental programs in the male compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: tight junction defective
definition: Any perturbation in the belt-like region of very close contact between the plasma membranes of adjacent cells that results in the complete occlusion of the intercellular space.

label: sensory system variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the sensory system over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals. The sensory system is involved in the perception of a stimuli, its conversion into a signal and the recognition and characterization of the resulting signal.

label: dauer sensillum variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the sense organs comprised of ciliated sensory nerve endings enveloped by sheath and/or socket cells, from that observed in control animals.

label: paraquat hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to paraquat at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: male fan development variant
definition: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the male fan over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control.

label: fewer neurons
definition: Animals exhibit fewer neurons compared to control animals.

label: egg laying irregular
definition: The rate of the intrinsic behavioral program that serves to move fertilized eggs down the uterus, through the vulva, and out of the worm onto the substrate does not conform to the pattern observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: one cell shape defective early emb
definition: One-cell embryos have an altered shape.

label: reversal variant
definition: Variations in the behavior by which an organism shifts from forward to backward movements.

label: L2 arrest
definition: The developmental program of the animals does not continue past the second larval stage (L2).

label: post mating variant
definition: Males exhibit variations of the behaviors observed in control animals that follow the completion of mating.

label: ectopic body wall muscle
definition: Animals exhibit one or more body wall muscle cells in locations not normally found in controls.

label: tail development variant
definition: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the tail over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control. The tail includes the posterior region that spans from the rectum to the end.

label: rhythmic tolerance to stress variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in light/dark cycle recurrence of reactions to stress conditions compared to that observed for control animals.

label: cilia morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the microtubule-based dendritic projections extending from the cell body, compared to that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, cilia are classified as channel cilia or wing cilia depending on their placement within the sensillum. Channel cilia of control animals are cylindrical, extend into the sensillum pore and are exposed to the outside. Wing cilia of control animals vary in shape, are embedded in the sensillum sheath cell and are not typically refractory to dyes indicating exposure to the outside.

label: posterior cell migration variant
definition: Any variation in the orderly movement of cells along the posterior axis of the animal (abolished, misdirected or incomplete) compared to control.

label: antibody staining reduced
definition: Any variation that results in a decrease in the characteristic expression of a gene product, as detected by antibody staining, compared to control animals.

label: curly
definition: Animals exhibit a greater number of bends in their body compared to control. C. elegans posture assumes more than a single sine wave.

label: dopamine synthesis defective
definition: Animals are unable to carry out the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of dopamine.

label: nuclear envelope assembly variant early emb
definition: Nuclear envelope does not reassemble properly.

label: developmental delay postembryonic
definition: The developmental progression of an animal after the embryonic stage, over time, from its formation to its mature structure is delayed compared to control.

label: somatic gonad morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the components of the gonad that are separate from the germline proper compared to control animals.

label: posterior pale
definition: Animals have decreased accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that causes increased translucency of the posterior body axis compared to control.

label: muscle arm axon connection variant
definition: The morphology or number of connections between muscle arms and commissural motor axons varies from control animals.

label: tail behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the tail in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: spontaneous spicule protraction
definition: Males exhibit spicule-muscle seizures leading to inappropriately timed protraction compared to control.

label: dauer cuticle variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the formation of the rigid external coating (which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells) during the dauer larva stage, compared to control animals (Wormatlas). The dauer larval stage is a developmentally arrested larval stage that is specialized for survival under harsh, or otherwise unfavorable environmental conditions.

label: reduced recovery pumping response to light
definition: Animals exhibit a reduced recovery pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that during the 0-10 seconds after removal of light exposure the pharyngeal pumping rate increasesto a lesser extent than in controls.

label: chromosome condensation variant
definition: Any variation in the progressive compaction of dispersed interphase chromatin into threadlike chromosomes prior to mitotic or meiotic nuclear division, or during apoptosis, in eukaryotic cells compared to control.

label: lysosome-related organelle biogenesis variant
definition: Variations in the processes that are carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosome-related organelles (LROs) that, like lysosomes, have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell but are distinct in function, composition, and morphology, compared to control.

label: shortened life span
definition: The duration of viability in the adult phase of the life-cycle is less than that of control animals.

label: eggshell formation variant
definition: Embryos exhibit variations in the processes that lead to the construction of the eggshell, a protective structure that minimizes water loss whilst allowing gas exchanges essential for embryonic respiration, compared to controls

label: anesthetic hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to anesthetic at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: posterior region development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of an animal's anatomy contained in the posterior region over time, compared to control animals.

label: multiple alae
definition: Alae contain more cuticular ridges than control animals. In C. elegans alae are composed of three cuticular ridges.

label: excretory system physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the secretory system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: synaptic vesicle endocytosis variant
definition: Variations in the uptake of a small membrane-bound organelle, filled with neurotransmitter(s) and/or neuropeptides, by the invagination of small region of the plasma membrane to form a new membrane-bounded vesicle compared to control(Wormatlas).

label: spindle absent
definition: Cells lack the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis.

label: levamisole hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to levamisole at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. Levamisole is a cholinergic agonist.

label: cell ionizing radiation response variant
definition: Cells exhibit variations in their response to ionizing radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: aluminum response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to aluminum compared to that observed in control animals.

label: tail withered
definition: The girth of the region posterior to the vulva is reduced compared to that anterior to the vulva (the Wit phenotype). In C. elegans this phenotype is associated with anteriorward misplacement of the CAN neurons.

label: Aba ABp division axis defective early emb
definition: ABa or ABp divide in the wrong orientation.

label: one cell arrest early emb
definition: Embryos fail to divide and arrest as one-cell embryos.

label: ciliary localization defective
definition: Proteins show defects in their localization in the cilia compared to control animals.

label: neuronal sheath cell morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the glia-like support cell of neuronal sensilla that ensheathes the dendrite tips and or processes of neurons, from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, sheath cells have highly invaginated and vesiculated surfaces, which provide a specialized environment for dendritic structures.

label: centriole biogenesis variant
definition: Any variation in the formation or disassembly of the cylindrical structures that are composed of groupings of microtubules found close to the nucleus (centrioles) compared to control. Centrioles are arranged perpendicularly and are surrounded by an amorphous mass of dense material (the pericentriolar material). The centrioles and the pericentriolar material constitute the compound structure known as the centrosome.

label: body wall muscle thick filament variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a robust elongated cytoplasmic filament composed principally of myosin protein compared to control animals. In C. elegans, thick filaments also contain paramyosin and twitchin (Wormatlas).

label: postsynaptic region physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process in the region, opposite to the presynaptic region, which is required for receiving signals from the other side of the synapse compared to control.

label: copper response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to copper compared to that observed in control animals.

label: metaphase to anaphase transition defect
definition: Cells exhibit variations in the process whereby a cell progresses from metaphase to anaphase, compared to control. Metaphase is the second stage of chromosome segregation in the cell cycle where chromosomes become aligned on the equatorial plate of the cell and anaphase is the stage where sister chromatids (or homologous chromosomes) separate and migrate towards the poles of the spindle.

label: burst pharyngeal pumping response to light
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the burst pharyngeal pumping response to light, during which the pharyngeal pumping rate slightly increases during the5-10 seconds after light exposure onset, compared to controls.

label: gamete necrotic death increased
definition: Ooctyes and or sperm appear vacuolated and degenerated compared to gametes in control animals. This degeneration is not due to normal programmed cell death.

label: egg laying response to muscimol variant
definition: Animals do not mimic control animals in their egg-laying response to muscimol exposure. In C. elegans, muscimol inhibits egg-laying.

label: obsolete flattened locomotion path
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: D lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the D blastomere exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: phorbol ester resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of phorbol esters that elicit a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. Phorbol esters such as PMA act as DAG mimetics.

label: transposon silencing variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the activity of endogenous transposons compared to control. In C. elegans transposon activity is often measured by the rate of reversion of mutations induced by transposon insertions.

label: Fluorouracil resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of Fluorouracil (5-FU) that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. Elegans Fluorouracil induces germ cell death, inhibits embryogenesis and inhibits larval growth (depending on dose) in control animals.

label: drug adaptation variant
definition: Animals show variations in their decreased responsiveness after prolonged or repeated exposure to a drug compared to that in control.

label: iodide chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of iodide.

label: embryo osmotic integrity defective early emb
definition: Variations in the ability of an embryo to maintain osmotic balance. In C.elegans this can result in an embryo filling the egg shell and lysing.

label: pathogen induced cell death variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to a pathogen or pathogenic cue, compared to control.

label: multiple nuclei
definition: Animals have more than one nucleus in a particular cell type.

label: hypercontracted
definition: Excessive and often uncoordinated body wall muscle contraction leading to shortening of the body.

label: cytoplasmic dynamics defective early emb
definition: Cytoplasmic movements are atypical.

label: manganese hypersensitivity
definition: Animals respond at a faster rate or to lower concentrations of manganese that that observed for control animals.

label: lectin binding occurs
definition: Animals contain targets for exogenously applied lectins.

label: drug induced life span variant
definition: Life span of the animal is not influenced by drug exposure in the same manner as control animals.

label: spindle orientation variant
definition: The alignment of the spindle relative to other cellular structures varies from that observed in control animals.

label: obsolete anterior region morphology abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: corpse engulfment initiation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in recognition of cell corpses and initiation of corpse engulfment, compared to controls.

label: intestinal development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the intestine over time from its initial formation to its mature structure compared to control.

label: development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: terminal bulb contraction variant
definition: Variations in the rhythmic contractions of the posterior pharynx (terminal bulb), such as timing, strength etc. In C. elegans contraction of the terminal bulb inverts the grinder, allowing bacteria in front of the grinder to be broken up and transported to the intestine.

label: lipid composition variant
definition: The constituent parts or ratio of elements that make up lipids are altered when compared to that of control animals.

label: sexually dimorphic development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of morphogenic processes required for formation or proper placement of sex-specific structures that distinguish the animal as one sex or the other in the population, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: mRNA splicing variant
definition: Variations in the processes regulating the excision of intervening introns from the primary mRNA transcript, compared to control.

label: cell cycle variant
definition: Cells of the animals exhibit variations in the initiation, progression or exit from the biochemical and morphological processes that occur during successive replication or nuclear replication events from that observed for control animals.

label: protein metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of proteins in the organism compared to control.

label: body muscle dystrophy
definition: Progressive degeneration of muscle along the body wall.

label: quinine chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of the bitter tastant quinine, a water soluble molecule. In C. elegans, quinine is typically a repellant.

label: transdifferentiation defective
definition: The conversion of one differentiated cell type into another does not occur as it does in control animals. In C. elegans, the Y cell undergoes a dramatic redifferentiation from being a cell in of the rectum to a PDA neuron. This transdifferentiation requires the cell to withdraw from its established position, migrate, and then become a motor neuron.

label: cytoplasmic streaming defective
definition: The directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of, or within the cytoplasm of a cell is impaired.

label: peroxisome physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the peroxisome to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: transgenerational loss of fertility
definition: Animals exhibit a decline in fertility over generations. This is often assessed by counting laid eggs over successive generations.

label: precocious alae
definition: Formation of alae occurs earlier in development compared to control animals; In C. elegans, adult lateral alae are typically generated during the late L4 stage.

label: vulval muscle unresponsive to serotonin
definition: The vulval muscle does not respond to serotonin in the same manner as control animals. This phenotype is often assayed by imaging of calcium transients in response to serotonin.

label: nose touch variant
definition: Variations in the ability of an animal to respond with characteristic backward movement after a nose-on collision with an object compared to control. In C. elegans, this phenotype is usually assayed via stroking with a hair or similar fiber on the anterior most tip of the animal.

label: variable cell division timing
definition: Animals exhibit larger variations in cell division timing events than in controls.

label: epithelial morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form, composition or structure of the layer of cells that cover the external surface of an organism and form the inner lining between the tissues and organs of that organism and the external environment compared to control. In C. elegans epithelial cells include epithelium of the alimentary tract, intestinal cells, hypodermis, interfacial cells and somatic gonad cells (Wormatlas).

label: paralysis response to ethanol hypersensitive
definition: Animals become paralyzed in response to ethanol at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: obsolete touch response abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: organism desiccation response variant
definition: Any variation in the state or activity of an organism in response to extreme dryness or drought-like conditions, compared to control .

label: head swollen
definition: The most anterior portion of the animal appears bloated or distended.

label: commissure absent
definition: Animals are missing any one of its commissures, an axon tract that connects one body part to another.

label: expression lipogenic enzyme reduced
definition: The levels of an enzyme involved in the manufacture of lipids are decreased compared to control animals.

label: sterile progeny
definition: Any variation that compromises the reproductive ability of the progeny of an animal.

label: germ cell compartment morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of the compartments in the germline of females/hermaphrodites compared to control animals. In C. elegans these compartments contain a nucleus and are connected to a common cytoplasm (rachis).  These compartments eventually undergo cellularization and become oocytes.

label: S phase checkpoint variant
definition: Mitotic cells exhibit variations during the passage through a cell cycle control point late in the S phase of the mitotic cell cycle, which ensures DNA replication is complete, compared to control cells.

label: odorant imprinting variant
definition: Any variation in a learned olfactory response whereby exposure of animals to odorants during specific developmental times or physiological states results in a lasting memory compared to control. In control animals, this imprinting determines the animal's behavior upon encountering the same odorant at a later time.

label: miRNA expression variant
definition: Variations in the biogenesis or stability of the microRNA class of molecules compared to control. In C. elegans these molecules are endogenous single-stranded regulatory molecules, 19-25 nucleotides long, with the potential to arise from hairpin, foldback, structures from their primary transcripts.

label: larval growth slow
definition: Any variation that causes a reduction in growth rate during larval stages compared to control.

label: microtubule nucleation variant
definition: Any variation that alters the characteristic de novo formation of a microtubule compared to control.

label: ray ectopic
definition: Animals have finger-like sensory sensilla (rays) that are present in places they are normally not found, when compared to the location in control animals.

label: cell membrane morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the structure, form or composition of the semipermeable lipid bilayer that creates a boundary between the interior and exterior environment for cells, cellular organelles and tissues, within an organism compared to control.

label: tRNA expression decreased
definition: Animals exhibit reduced levels of transfer RNA compared to control.

label: oxygen consumption decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decreased rate of oxygen utilization compared to control animals.

label: obsolete exaggerated body bends
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: male gonadal lineage variant
definition: The descendants of a gonadal precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs in the male compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: male mating variant
definition: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of the male that are associated with reproduction compared to control.

label: starvation resistant
definition: Animals show enhanced tolerance to deprivation of nourishment, compared to control.

label: methiothepin resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of methiothepin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: pathogen infection clearance rate increased
definition: Infected animals exhibit an increased rate of clearance of pathogen infection compared to controls.

label: P cell cleavage delayed
definition: Any variation that causes a delay in the stereotypical cleavage pattern of the P cell compared to control.

label: alae morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the organization of the longitudinal ridges on the cuticle along the length of the animal, from that observed for control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: dwelling variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the low-speed/high turning movement that restricts them to a confined region compared to control.

label: seam cells stacked
definition: The hypodermal cells, which lie along the lateral body wall to form longitudinal stripes of epithelial cells underlying the alae, are misplaced such that they are stacked along the dorsal-ventral axis rather than forming a continuous row of adjacent cells .

label: transposon mutator
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in frequency of transposition events (DNA movement to different positions within the genome of a single cell) causing an accumulation of lesions within the genome, compared to control.

label: intestinal fluorescence decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that fluoresce in the intestine.

label: larval behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of a larvae in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: dopaminergic fate atypical
definition: Animals exhibit differential regulation of the dopaminergic fate among the various classes of dopaminergic neurons.

label: obsolete mitochondria morphology variant epithelial
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: gut on the exterior
definition: An epidermal enclosure defect that results in internal organs lying on the outside of the embryo.

label: aldicarb response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to aldicarb compared to that observed in control animals.

label: chromosome alignment variant
definition: Any variation in the movement of chromosomes to the spindle equator during mitosis compared to control animals.

label: intestinal integrity increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the integrity of the intestine, compared to controls.

label: pharynx disorganized
definition: The components of the feeding organ fail to be arranged in the same manner as control animals.

label: cell acidification defective
definition: Animals lack the capacity to reduce the internal pH of a cell.

label: coiling frequency
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of time spent with its body posture in a coil or the frequency with which they form coils compared to control animals.

label: extra distal tip cells
definition: Animals produce an excess number of distal tip cells compared to controls.

label: U lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the U cell (which divides only in the males) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: aqueous compound discrimination defective
definition: Animals are unable to locate the gradient peak of a water soluble compound, which was generated on a uniform concentration of another compound.

label: locomotion variant
definition: Animals exhibit deviations in self-propelled movement on a solid medium compared to control animals.

label: dauer metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the chemical reactions and pathways that occur during the dauer life stage, compared to control.

label: body protrusions
definition: Any irregular swelling in discrete regions of the body region between the head and the tail.

label: male gonad morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form or composition of a specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces the male gametes compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: ectopic cleavage furrow early emb
definition: One or more cells of the early embryo (one-cell stage to four-cell stage) exhibit one or more cleavage furrows in locations not normally found in control cells.

label: axoneme short
definition: The microbule-based fibrillar bundle in the core of the cilium is reduced in length compared to axonemes of similar cells in control animals.

label: pseudocleavage defective early emb
definition: Pseudocleavage is atypical in the inviable one-cell embryo.

label: turning variant
definition: Variations in the behavior by which an organism alters its trajectory of movement compared to control, excluding shifts from forward to backward movements (this is reversal).

label: tail morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of the most posterior region of the body compared to control. The anterior bound of the tail is not well defined though it might range from the position of the post-deirids to the opening of the anus (Wormatlas).

label: heteroplasmy
definition: The presence of a mixture of more than one type of an organellar genome (mitochondrial DNA (mtDNA) or plastid DNA) within a cell or individual.

label: fungal resistance increased
definition: Animals are less prone to infection by a fungus compared to control.

label: body posture amplitude increased
definition: Animals exhibit variations in body posture caused by an increase in the extent of displacement measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control animals.

label: alimentary system physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the alimentary system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: yolk synthesis variant
definition: Variations in the generation of the nutrient protein produced by intestinal cells and secreted by them into the pseudocoelom, from which it can be shared with other tissues in the body compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: serotonin catabolism defective
definition: Animals are unable to carry out any chemical reaction or pathway resulting in the breakdown of serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine), a monoamine neurotransmitter.

label: adult body morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of the animal after it has completed progression through the larval stages compared to control animals.

label: tail spike variant
definition: Any variation in the structure or appearance of the thin cuticle specialization found at the extreme posterior end of the tail compared to control.

label: feeding inefficient
definition: Animals are unable to ingest nutrients at a rate similar to control animals.

label: axonal transport variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in nerve cell axons.

label: obsolete no male variantity scored
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: organism response to pH variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response and ability to survive over a range of pH conditions compared to control.

label: light body touch resistant
definition: Animals do not respond to stroking to the head or tail with a hair or similar fiber, but does respond to stronger mechanical stimuli such as prodding with a fine platinum wire or similar tool compared to controls.

label: dauer feeding suppressed variant
definition: Any variation in the inhibition of feeding which is induced/occurs during the dauer stage compared to control.

label: pharyngeal pumping rate in response to light variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in pharyngeal pumping rate in response to light, compared to controls.

label: endoplasmic reticulum metabolism variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways of the endoplasmic reticulum compared to control.

label: selenium response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to selenium compared to that observed in control animals.

label: pronuclear number defective early emb
definition: There are more than two pronuclei in the inviable embryo.

label: basement membrane gap expansion variant
definition: Animals display variations in the manner in which an opening in the basement membrane (a thin, dense, sheet-like structure built on a network of polymeric laminin and type IV collagen) expands to make way for intertissue connections, compared to control animals.

label: excretory secretory system morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form, structure or composition of related tissues that allow the animal to secrete saline fluid and maintain a proper salt balance compared to control. In C. elegans, four cell types (1 pore cell, 1 duct cell, 1 canal cell and a fused pair of gland cells) make up the excretory system (Wormatlas).

label: spontaneous reversal variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern spontaneous backward locomotion compared to control.

label: extra cleavage furrow
definition: One or more extra cleavage furrows are observed in a cell about to undergo division.

label: rod like larval lethal
definition: Animals die as rigid, rod-like larva. In C. elegans this defect is often caused by the misspecification of the excretory duct cell.

label: electrophysiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the electrical properties of any of its cells or tissues compared to control.

label: fluoranthene hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to fluoranthene at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: neurotransmitter metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving neurotransmitters compared to control animals. Neurotransmitters are any of a group of substances that are released on excitation from the axon terminal of a presynaptic neuron of the central or peripheral nervous system and travel across the synaptic cleft to either excite or inhibit the target cell.

label: P2 EMS synchronous division early emb
definition: P2 and EMS divide synchronously.

label: metal homeostasis variant
definition: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of metal ions within an organism compared to control.

label: slow growth
definition: Any variation that causes a reduction in growth rate compared to control.

label: male pigmentation variant
definition: Males exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of the organism compared to control animals.

label: mitotic spindle asters defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubule spindle asters during a mitotic cell cycle.

label: chromosome segregation variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that regulate the apportionment of chromosomes to each of two daughter cells compared to control.

label: stage specific cuticle antigenicity variant
definition: Animals display cuticle components displayed by animals of a different developmental stage, compared to control.

label: dumpy
definition: Worms are shorter and stouter than control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: male spicule development variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the development of the male elongated sclerotized structures covered by a hardened layer of cuticle in the tail (which are actively everted during copulation to fasten the male copulatory fan to the vulva) compared to control.

label: cell migration failure
definition: Characteristic movement of cells from one site to another is abolished compared to control.

label: male tail development variant
definition: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the male tail over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control.

label: pharyngeal inter-pump interval increased
