definition: The time between two pumps of the pharynx is increased compared to control animals.

label: silver nanoparticle hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to silver nanoparticles (AgNPs) at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: chromosome decondensation variant
definition: Any variation in the progressive decompaction of chromatin that changes chromosome structure from the condensed form to a relaxed disperse form.

label: body wall muscle morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the body wall muscle compared to control animals.

label: autophagy variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the process by which their cells digest parts of their own cytoplasm, compared to control.

label: early eggs laid
definition: Eggs are laid at an earlier stage of development when compared with control animals.

label: spermatogenesis delayed
definition: The progression of immature germ cells to functional sperm is retarded compared to control.

label: pentanedione chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of pentanedione.

label: cell cell contacts abnormal
definition: Cell-cell contacts are abnormal, compared to control animals.

label: seam cell fusion variant
definition: Variations in the ability of seam cells to fuse to form a continuous syncytium along the body wall late larval development, (separate from the hyp 7 syncytium), compared to control (WormAtlas). Hypodermal seam cells lie along the lateral body wall to form longitudinal stripes of epithelial cells underlying the alae, and are required for alae formation.

label: neuron positioning variant
definition: The placement of neuronal cells, as a whole or of a specific class of neuron in the animal, deviates from that observed in control animals.

label: extra pharyngeal muscle cells
definition: Animals contain an excess number of pharyngeal muscle cells compared to control. In C. elegans, pharyngeal cells are derived from MS-blastomere. The overproduction of pharyngeal tissues is a result of other blastomeres adopting an MS-like fate.

label: relative cell cycle timing defective early emb
definition: Relative cell cycle timing during the first four cell divisions is aberrant.

label: cell body spike frequency variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the autonomously initiated periodic trains of calcium transients observed in cell bodies, which are independent of presynaptic inputs.

label: manganese homeostasis variant
definition: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of manganese ions within an organism compared to control.

label: commisure growth variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the extension of the part of the axon that forms a bridge between body regions, compared to control animals.

label: frequency body bend reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a reduction in the frequency of oscillations between adjacent body segments from that observed for control animals.

label: fibrous body-membranous organelle (FB-MO) assembly variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the assembly of the fibrous body-membranous organelle (FB-MO), a nematode sperm-specific organelle involved in cytoplasmic partitioning during spermatogenesis, compared to control animals.

label: body wall muscle physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the body wall muscle system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: outward rectifying current variant
definition: The driving force of the outward flow of ions does not exceed the inward flow for the opposite driving force or is otherwise altered when compared to that measured for control animals.

label: sperm pseudopod variant
definition: Variation in the morphological appearance or composition of the pseudopod, a cellular projection that facilitates motility of the spermatozoa.

label: temperature induced dauer formation defective
definition: Animals do not enter dauer at a temperature that induces dauer formation in control animals.

label: squashed vulva
definition: The apparent partial collapse of the vulval invagination and the elongation of central vulva cells often leading to a flattened appearance.

label: striated muscle development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of muscle cells that contain fibers that are divided by transverse bands into striations, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: rudimentary gonad
definition: Animals have very few or no germline nuclei and gonad arms that are very small or missing.

label: germ cell hypersensitive ionizing radiation
definition: Germ cells exhibit increased sensitivity to the effects of ion producing radiation compared to control animals.

label: excess pharyngeal cells
definition: Animals contain an excess number of pharyngeal cells compared to control. In C. elegans, pharyngeal cells are derived from MS-blastomere. The overproduction of pharyngeal tissues is a result of other blastomeres adopting an MS-like fate.

label: cord commissures fail to reach target
definition: Axon tracts fail to complete the connection between nerve cords. In C. elegans, these tracts grow circumferentially around the animal, completing the connection between the ventral and dorsal nerve cords.

label: sodium acetate adaptation defective
definition: Animals do not exhibit characteristic chemoattractive desensitization to sodium acetate in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control.

label: phosphatidylinositol 3-phosphate levels reduced
definition: The levels of phosphatidylinositol 3-phosphate (a.k.a. PtdIns3P or PI3P) are reduced compared to those of control animals

label: failure to hatch
definition: Animals fail to emerge from an egg shell.

label: wing cilia bulbous
definition: Animals exhibit wing cell sensory cilia that are truncated and swollen unlike that observed in control animals.

label: increased pathogen accumulation
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in pathogen accumulation, persistent colonization, and luminal distension of the intestine.

label: nuclear rotation variant
definition: Any variation in the rotation of centrosomes and associated pronuclei in one-cell embryo, occurring as a transition between pronuclear migration and pronuclear fusion compared to control.

label: fewer egg laying events during active
definition: Fewer egg-laying events occur within the active phase of egg laying, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events, compared to control.

label: locomotor coordination variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their ability to maintain characteristic and effective locomotion compared to control.

label: nuclear anchoring variant
definition: The nucleus or nuclei are not positioned in a similar manner or pattern in the cell or syncytium to that observed in controls.

label: pheromone production variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the amount and/or quality of pheromone produced compared to control animals at a defined stage.

label: fewer sex myoblasts
definition: Animals produce a reduced number of sex myoblasts compared to controls.

label: nuclear division variant
definition: Any variation in the process by which a cell nucleus is divided into two nuclei, with DNA and other nuclear contents distributed between the daughter nuclei, compared to control.

label: pattern protein expression variant
definition: Any variation in the cellular or subcellular distribution of a protein compared to that observed in control animals.

label: scrawny
definition: Animals are slight or meager in body size compared to control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: cell death sexually dimorphic variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the rate or extent of programmed cell death as it pertains to a sex-specific feature, compared to control populations.

label: enzyme activity reduced
definition: Any variation that results in a decrease in the catalytic activity of an enzyme compared to control. Catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component).

label: nuclear appearance variant
definition: The morphological appearance of nuclei differs from control animals.

label: germ cell arrest
definition: Germ cells fail to undergo meiotic differentiation to form mature gametes.

label: growth rate variant
definition: The increase in size or mass of an organism over time during the lifespan of the organism or over any developmental stage(s) is not similar to that observed for control animals.

label: bordering
definition: Animals tend to accumulate at the thickest part of the bacterial lawn.

label: colchicine hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to colchicine at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: gut obstructed
definition: Any variation in the developmental progression of the intestine that leads to a blockage in the alimentary canal.

label: spicules crumpled
definition: The elongated sclerotized structures covered by a hardened layer of cuticle in the male tail (which are actively everted during copulation to fasten the male copulatory fan to the vulva) are deformed. In C. elegans males there are two copulatory spicules.

label: cation positive chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to move towards attractive cations.

label: backing decreased
definition: Animals spend less time backing compared to control animals.

label: amphid channel axoneme morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the microtuble-based fibrillar core, axoneme, of the cilia of the neurons that project through the sensillum pore to the outside of the animal, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: polysome mRNA association variant
definition: The extent of mRNA ribosome associations varies from controls.

label: AWC odorant chemotaxis defective
definition: In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards typically attractive volatile organic molecules sensed by the AWC compared to control.

label: sperm transfer continuation defective
definition: Any variation in the continued movement of sperm through the vas deferens, exiting the cloaca, compared to control. In C. elegans, when all sperm that exit the seminal vesicle have been released, the spicules retract into the male.

label: extra gonadal sheath cells
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the number of somatic sheath cells surrounding each gonad arm compared to controls.

label: Q lineage variant
definition: The descendants of Q L or QR cells exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: temperature induced dauer formation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the entry into the dauer stage when exposed to temperatures that induce dauer formation in control animals. In C. elegans, many Daf-c animals enter dauer at 25C, whereas Hid animals enter dauer at 27C.

label: second adult cuticle
definition: A duplication of the developmental program that forms the adult-type rigid external coating which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells.

label: sheath cell secretion variant
definition: Variations in the regulated release of substances by nonneuronal cells that enclose or ensheath the tips of the sensory dendrites compared to control.

label: antibody subcellular localization variant
definition: Any variation in the placement of a protein, as detected by antibody staining, within in a cell or cellular compartment compared to control.

label: tail movement increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the movement of the most posterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: progeny variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the progeny of an animal at any time from its fertilization to adulthood compared to control.

label: locomotion reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in any parameter used to measure locomotion compared to control animals.

label: occurences of decapitation
definition: Animals exhibit constrictions in the anterior portion of the head that result in decapitation.

label: sexually dimorphic morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the outcome of morphogenic processes required for formation or proper placement of sex-specific structures that distinguish the animal as one sex or the other in the population, from that observed for control animals.

label: multiple nuclei oocyte
definition: Haploid female germ cells (oocytes) contain more than one nucleus.

label: body wall muscle development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the principal muscle cell type whose contractile activity generates body motion in the nematode over time compared to control. In C. elegans they consist of 95 unfused cells in the adult organized into four muscle quadrants. Their sarcomeres are obliquely striated and lie lengthwise along the body wall (Wormatlas).

label: carbon dioxide avoidance variant
definition: Variations in the characteristic movement away from specific CO2 levels compared to control. C. elegans avoids high levels of CO2.

label: resistant to copper
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of copper that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to copper to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: ATP levels reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the cellular levels of Adenosine-5'-triphosphate (ATP), compared to control. ATP is a nucleotide that plays a versatile role in cell biology.

label: axon regeneration enhanced
definition: Any increase in regenerative regrowth of axons compared to control animals.

label: negative chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of an animal in response to chemical repellants as defined by control animals.

label: precocious oogenesis
definition: Relatively unspecialized germ cells prematurely acquire the specialized properties of mature oocytes.

label: tail bend angle increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of the maximum flex of the most posterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: no oocytes
definition: Hermaphrodites lack fully specialized female gametes that are competent for fertilization.

label: generation calcium signal defective pharynx
definition: Rhythmic calcium increases in the pharynx are observed less often than in control animals. In C. elegans, rhythmic increases in intracellular calcium are often observed using a transgenically expressed cameleon, a ratiometric calcium indicator.

label: lysosome-related organelle localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosome-related organelles (LROs) that, like lysosomes, have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell but are distinct in function, composition, and morphology, compared to control.

label: chemical hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to a specific chemical at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: embryonic cell lineage variant
definition: The descendants of an embryonic precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: mating plug production variant
definition: Males differ from control animals in their ability to form copulatory plugs or their placement of these plugs. In C. elegans, males of the Hawaiian strain (CB4856) typically form mating plugs.

label: pharyngeal pumping variant
definition: Any variation in the contraction and relaxation movements of the pharyngeal muscle that mediate feeding in nematodes compared to control.

label: mRNA surveillance defective
definition: Defects in the cellular machinery that targets aberrant mRNAs species (nonsense codons, splice errors, altered untranslated regions etc.) for degradation. In C. elegans, mutations in such loci often act as allele-specific non gene-specific recessive suppressors of certain allele phenotypes and cause abnormal morphogenesis of male and hermaphrodite genitalia.

label: bursa elongated
definition: The length of the adult male tail, including the lateral fan and rays, is extended compared to control.

label: chromosome morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form or composition of a structure in the cell nucleus which contains the genetic material encoded as DNA and surrounded by histone proteins and other regulatory elements compared to control. In C. elegans the normal cell contains 5 pairs of 'autosomes' and one or two X chromosomes (Wormatlas).

label: pronuclear breakdown asynchronous early emb
definition: Instead of breaking down synchronously, the two pronuclei break down asynchronously in the inviable one-cell embryo.

label: nose movement decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the movement of the extreme anterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: sexually dimorphic lethality
definition: Animals die prematurely at any stage of the life cycle in a sex dependent manner.

label: synapsis maintenance defective
definition: Animals are unable to maintain paired chromosome throughout pachytene.

label: expulsion defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the expulsion of gut contents. In C. elegans, this refers to the final step of the defecation cycle in which the intestinal muscle and anal depressor contractions further pressurize intestinal contents and open the anus to permit expulsion.

label: diplotene region organization variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations from control animals in the organization of the germ cell nuclei in the gonad that are in the diplotene stage. In C. elegans the diplotene region follows the pachytene region and occurs just distal to, and coincident with, the loop in the gonad arm. In the diplotene region germ cell compartments become organized into a single file.

label: G tract instability
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the rate of deletion events in mono-G or G-rich tracts within the genome compared to control.

label: body wall muscle actin organization defective
definition: The characteristic organization of actin filaments into I-bands is disrupted. In C. elegans, actin filaments no longer appear as thin continuous longitudinal stripes along the muscle quadrants.

label: viral resistance increased
definition: Animals are less prone to infection by virus compared to control.

label: anoxia hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to anoxic (trace oxygen levels) stress after a shorter exposure time compared to control.

label: head bend angle variant
definition: Any variation in the extent of the maximum flex of the most anterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: pharyngeal physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the pharynx to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: RAB-11 recycling endosome morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes, positive for the RAB protein RAB-11, that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: obsolete ray loss
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: prolonged pharyngeal contraction
definition: The time in which a muscle contraction event that controls feeding is increased compared to control. Contractions of the pharynx are necessary for bacterial uptake from the surrounding environment.

label: organism metabolism processing variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways, including anabolism and catabolism, by which living organisms transform chemical substances compared to control.

label: retrovesicular ganglion development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion which lies at the anterior limit of the ventral nerve cord, near the ventral ganglion and nerve ring in the head posterior to the excretory pore over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: cytoplasmic appearance defective early emb
definition: Embryos exhibit defects in the form, structure or composition of any cellular contents (excluding plasma membrane and nucleus), compared to control embryos.

label: excess coelomocytes
definition: The number of coelomocytes are increased compared to control animals. Coelomocytes are free-floating spherical cells lying in the pseudocoelomic cavity of animals that can endocytose many compounds.

label: organism segment development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the overall structure or appearance of any anterior/posterior section of an animal's anatomy over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: pathogen infected pharynx decrease
definition: Animals exhibit a lesser extent of pathogen invasion into the pharynx compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite sperm fertilization defective
definition: Any perturbation that renders hermaphrodite derived sperm incompetent at fertilizing an oocyte.

label: outer labial morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the outer labial ring compared to control. In C. elegans, this ring consists of four sensilla (OLQ) or the two additional lateral sensilla (OLL), which are part of the labial sensillum.

label: repetitive transgene expression variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the expression of repetitive exogenous DNA compared to control.

label: male tail sensory ray development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan from its formation to the mature structure when compared to control animals.

label: meiotic spindle defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubule spindle during a meiotic cell cycle.

label: copper homeostasis variant
definition: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of copper ions within an organism compared to control.

label: pronuclear migration failure early emb
definition: Neither of the pronuclei migrate and they never meet.

label: Bacillus thuringiensis toxin hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to Bacillus thuringiensis toxins (Bt toxins) at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: neuron physiology variant
definition: Activity of the neuron varies from that observed for control animals or neurons. In C. elegans neuron activity is often assayed by observing calcium spikes.

label: parental chromosome mixing defective
definition: Parental chromosomes fail to undergo appropriate mixing upon pronuclear fusion resulting in a zygotic nucleus in which parental genomes remain segregated.

label: avoids bacterial lawn
definition: Lawn avoidance refers to behavior in which animals initially enter the bacterial lawn but later exit and remain near the edge of the bacteria. Lawn avoidance is often a response to bacterial food, that is pathogenic or low quality to the animal.

label: male reproductive system morphology variant
definition: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the male reproductive system compared to control. The reproductive system is involved in the generation of progeny which contain genetic material inherited from the parents.

label: body constriction
definition: Animals contain body regions that are more narrow or drawn together than adjacent body regions.

label: absolute cell cycle timing defective early emb
definition: Absolute cell cycle timing during the first four cell divisions is aberrant.

label: dorsorectal ganglia development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion which lies above and behind the rectum in the tail, in close continuity with the anal hypodermal ridge over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: suppression of head oscillations defective
definition: Animals fail to suppress head oscillations in response to anterior touch. In C. elegans, this behavior is a result of tyraminergic signaling.

label: embryonic cell organization biogenesis variant
definition: Variations in the processes that are carried out at in the embryo which results in its formation or the arrangement of constituent parts, compared to control.

label: oocyte accumulation
definition: An increased number of oocytes are retained in the gonad without becoming endomitotic, compared to control.

label: excretory canal short
definition: The structure made by the processes of the excretory canal cell is reduced in size compared to control. In C. elegans this is an H-shaped structure which extends almost the full length of the body on both sides of the animal, generally in contact with the lateral hypodermis and the pseudocoelom (Wormatlas).

label: body elongation variant
definition: Any variation in the elongation of embryonic epidermal cells compared to control. In C. elegans, this elongation occurs along an anterior-posterior axis, which is required to transform the bean-shaped embryo into the elongated shape of the worm.

label: axon guidance variant
definition: Variations in the cue-directed extension of an axon towards a specific target site compared to control. (Axon guidance often depends on a combination of attractive and repulsive cues).

label: first polar body position variant
definition: Variations in the placement of the polar body formed in the first division of meiosis of a primary oocyte, compared to control. A polar body is the by-product of meiosis (destined to degenerate) in female or hermaphrodite animals.

label: EGF-induced sleep variant
definition: Animals do not respond with sleeping behavior induced through the EGF pathway. The EGF-induced sleep pathway is thought to represent a distinctmolecular pathway from developmentally linked sleep. The EGF-induced sleep state occurs in two contexts: by overexpressing the EGF ortholog (LIN-3C), or by EGF signaling after stress (such as temperature elevation) in wildtype animals.

label: no rectum
definition: Animals lack the passage connecting the posterior intestine to the rectal valve.

label: hypersensitive to iron deficiency
definition: Animals exhibit detrimental responses to iron deficiency more readily than control animals.

label: ascaroside biosynthesis defective
definition: Animals lack the ability to produce ascarosides that are capable of being produced in control animals.

label: body wall muscle dense body variant
definition: Any variation in the attachment plaque for thin filaments onto the cell membrane. The dense body in body wall muscles is especially large, indenting far into the cytoplasm to border each sarcomere, thus providing a long row of coherent attachment sites at regular intervals (WormAtlas).

label: excretory duct cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the excretory duct cell compared to control animals.

label: enzyme activity variant
definition: Any variation in the function of naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes compared to control. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component).

label: obsolete synaptic input abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: rectal development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the cuticle-lined sinus opening on the posterior ventral surface of the animal over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas). The function of the rectum is to excrete waste products from the alimentary system.

label: posterior body wall contraction defective
definition: Animals lack or exhibit defects in the posterior body muscle contractions during the defecation cycle.

label: posterior body wall contraction defecation cycle variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the sustained posterior body muscle contractions that precede the remaining contractions of the defecation cycle compared to control animals.

label: P granule defective
definition: Localization or structural appearance of P-granules is altered compared to control. P-granules are cytoplasmic structures associated with germ nuclei in the C. elegans gonad, and are localized exclusively to germ cells, or germ cell precursors, throughout the life cycle.

label: hypersensitive to galactose
definition: Animals exhibit negative effects on growth, development, or metabolism when exposed to a galactose-rich diet, compared to control animals.

label: aster AB defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the array of microtubules emanating from a spindle pole that do not connect to kinetochores in the AB cell.

label: voltage measurement variant
definition: Any observed variation in the measurement of voltage across the cell membrane compared to measurements in control animals. Voltage is the difference in electric potential energy per unit charge between two points.

label: epithelial cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of epithelial cells compared to control animals.

label: AAD response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to the amino-acetonitrile derivatives (AADs) class of synthetic anthelmintics, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism oxidative stress resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the levels of reactive oxygen species that elicit a response in control animals.

label: pentanol chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of pentanol. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, pentanol is an attractant.

label: mRNA poly-A tail length increased
definition: Animals exhibit one or more mRNAs with increased length of the 3' polyadenine tail, compared to control.

label: organelle metabolism variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways of an organelle compared to control.

label: cell fate transformation to body wall muscle
definition: Animals develop body wall muscle from precursor cells that do not normally produce body wall muscle.

label: intestinal physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the intestine to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: pericellular component morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of pericellular components compared to control animals.

label: egg laying circuit variant
definition: Neuromuscular signaling between neurons and egg laying musculature varies from that observed for control animals.

label: nucleolus variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the appearance of nucleoli compared to control animals.

label: locomotion rate serotonin variant
definition: Any variation in the locomotion rate after application of exogenous serotonin compared to control.

label: body region morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a discrete region of their anatomy compared to control animals.

label: nose touch hypersensitive
definition: Animals tend to initiate a response more often, compared to control, after nose-on collisions with an object. In C. elegans, animals initiate backwards movement in response to nose touch.

label: bursa morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the adult male tail including the lateral fan and rays compared to control.

label: no transport distal segment cilia
definition: The bidirectional transport of molecules along the distal segment of axonemal microtubules of the cilia is absent.

label: no cleavage furrow first division early emb
definition: One-cell embryos do not form the shallow groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate at the onset of cytokinesis.

label: iodide chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to iodide. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards iodide.

label: oviduct muscle defective
definition: Variations in the progression of the muscles of the adult hermaphrodite oviduct over time from their initial formation to their mature structure compared to control.

label: sustained spicule protraction defective
definition: Males exhibit defects in the prolonged, tonic, spicule extrusion through the vulva prior to sperm transfer.

label: protein turnover variant
definition: The dynamics of the replacement of old proteins by newly synthesized or modified proteins varies from that of control animals. This phenotype is often measured by fluorescence recovery after photobleaching (FRAP).

label: detergent hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to a detergent at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: germ cell differentiation variant
definition: Variations in the ability of a relatively unspecialized cell to acquire the specialized features of a mature gamete compared to control.

label: inhibition of synaptogenesis defective
definition: The processes that inhibit the location or frequency of formation of synapses are downregulated resulting in the formation of synapses or synapse-like structures in areas of the neuron that are typically devoid of synapses in control animals.

label: presynaptic vesicle morphology altered
definition: Vesicles in the presynaptic terminal differ in size, shape, or composition from those observed in control animals.

label: reactive oxygen species homeostasis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in endogenous levels of reactive oxygen species (chemically reactive molecules containing oxygen) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: pheromone sensation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any of a series of events in which a pheromone stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal that influences behavior in control animals.

label: skiddy
definition: Apparently normal sinusoidal movement, but appear to have poor traction on the agar surface of a culture plate.

label: anterior pharynx variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the anterior portion of the pharynx over time compared to control. In C. elegans the anterior region includes the corpus (procorpus and metacorpus - first bulb).

label: mid larval arrest
definition: Animals arrest during the stage between early and late larval development. In C. elegans, mid larval arrest occurs during the L2 to L3 stages of development.

label: excretory cell development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a protokidney cell with an internal lumen that is suggested to collect and secrete salt solutions outward via the excretory sinus, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: gonad displaced
definition: The specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces gamete is shifted from its customary place as defined by control.

label: serotonin induced fat reduction variant
definition: Animals retain a significantly greater proportion of their fat upon serotonin treatment, compared to control.

label: nucleolus refraction variant
definition: Any variation in the change in direction of a wave of light after passage through the nucleolus compared to control. The nucleolus is a small dense body in the nucleus.

label: organism oxidative stress response hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to a lower concentration of reactive oxygen species or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: obsolete vulval invagination L4 abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: pointed tail tip male
definition: Male tails fail to undergo tip retraction thereby forming a 'leptoderan' or 'pointed' adult tail.

label: path curvature variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the extent to which the overall path of movement is curved, compared to control animals.

label: AB lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the AB blastomere exhibit variations in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: obsolete ray fusion
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: siRNA processing defective
definition: Animals are unable to produce or maintain short interfering RNA (siRNA) from double stranded RNA (dsRNA). siRNAs are required to initiate interference of gene expression.

label: cation positive chemotaxis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic movement towards typically attractive cations compared to control.

label: mate finding defective
definition: Males exhibit defects in their response to the mate-finding cue.

label: lawn leaving behavior variant
definition: Variation of the time an individual spent on a patch of food (bacterial lawn) before leaving, compared to control animals.

label: aboc expulsion missing
definition: The anterior body contraction and expulsion steps of the defecation cycle are absent; posterior body contractions are still present.

label: amphid sheath cell morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the amphid sensillum cell that ensheathes the dendrite tips of channel neurons and wing cell dedritic processes, from that observed in control animals. Sheath cells in C.elegans have highly invaginated and vesiculated surfaces, which provide a specialized environment for the dendritic structures.

label: muscimol resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of muscimol that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: cell type morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of specialized cell types, compared to control. Includes the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: obsolete slightly dumpy
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: pathogen resistance increased
definition: Animals are less prone to infection compared to control.

label: pachytene progression during oogenesis variant
definition: Developing oocytes show defects in their entry, progression through or exit from the pachytene stage compared to control animals. Pachytene is a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the third stage of prophase I in meiosis, in which crossing over occurs between a chromatid in one partner and another chromatid in the homologous chromosome.

label: coelomocyte development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a free-floating spherical cell lying in the pseudocoelomic cavity of animals that can endocytose many compounds, possibly for immune surveillance, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: UV induced apoptosis decreased
definition: Programmed cell death caused by UV radiation is reduced compared to control animals. In C. elegans, this is often measured in the pachytene region of the gonad.

label: foraging behavior variant
definition: Variations in the behavior by which an organism locates food compared to control animals. In C. elegans roaming or dwelling activity on food are two examples of parameters used to assess this behavior. Roaming is defined as moving in a high-speed forward direction with brief backward movement, often traversing wide regions. Dwelling is defined as low-speed/high turning movement restricted to a confined region.

label: ventral enclosure variant
definition: Any variation in the process that regulates the migration of ventral epidermal cells toward the ventral midline (to encase underlying cells in an epithelial monolayer) in developing embryos compared to control.

label: endoderm absent
definition: Animals lack the early blast cells that give rise to the gut tissue (Wormatlas).

label: transgene expression undetectable cell specific
definition: The expression of a gene product produced by DNA coded for by exogenous genetic material that has been introduced into the organism is reduced below the threshold of detection in specific cells.

label: gap junction plaque morphology abnormal
definition: One or more cells exhibit variations in the morphology of one or more gap junction plaques, sets of associated gap junctions, compared to controls.

label: hermaphrodite sex muscle development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the muscles of the adult hermaphrodite reproductive system over time form their initial formation to their mature structure compared to control.

label: embryo delayed at pronuclear contact early emb
definition: Embryos are either delayed or arrested at pronuclear contact.

label: obsolete temporal frequency of sinusoidal movement decreased
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: intestinal cell proliferation variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern the expansion of intestinal cell populations compared to control.

label: male attraction response variant
definition: Males do not respond to small molecules or compounds that have been shown to attract control males. This phenotype is often measured by an increase in reversal frequency or time spent in a specified scoring region

label: obsolete translational repression variant
definition: OBSOLETE. Any variation in the prevention of mRNA translation that normally occurs in certain cells, compared to control.

label: muscle cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a muscle cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: unfolded protein response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any of the series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of the presence of unfolded proteins in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) and or the mitochondria, compared to control. One such response is the increase in expression of chaperones.

label: synaptogenesis variant
definition: Any variation in the biosynthesis of a synapse compared to control.

label: sensilium sheath cell variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of an interfacial epithelial cell which forms a specialized environment surrounding the ciliated sensory ending(s) of one or more neurons and is often accompanied by a more distal socket cell compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: obsolete protein localization abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE. Any change in the subcellular localization of a protein.

label: egg laying levamisole resistant
definition: Animals are not induced to lay eggs in reponse to exogenous levamisole. In C. elegans, levamisole stimulates egg-laying.

label: SM migration variant
definition: Variations in the movement of sex myoblasts compared to control animals. In C. elegans, the larval SM migrate anteriorly to the precise center of the developing hermaphrodite gonad.

label: obsolete polar body reabsorbed first early emb
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: early larval arrest
definition: Larvae arrest during early larval development. In C. elegans, this occurs during the L1 or L2 stages of larval development.

label: lysosome localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosomes, that have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell, compared to control.

label: germ cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the germ cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to cues, compared to control animals.

label: posterior body behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the longitudinal axis that spans from the midpoint to the tip of the tail of an animal in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: rachis narrow
definition: The nucleus-free core of germline cytoplasm in the gonad is not as wide as control animals.

label: organism hypertonic lethality increased
definition: Animals exhibit increased lethality as a result of exposure to environments with a higher solute concentration than their own internal environment, compared to control.

label: dauer inner labial sensillum variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the inner labial ring compared to control. In C. elegans, the ring is composed of six sensilla, which include associated neurons IL1 & IL2.

label: histone ubiquitination variant
definition: The pattern or state of ubiquitin modifications of histones varies from that of controls.

label: protein RNA interaction variant
definition: Variations in the selective and non-covalent physical association between a protein and a specific RNA sequence, compared to control.

label: plugged excretory pore
definition: Males receive copulatory plugs from other males, deposited on their excretory pores. This phenotype is polymorphic among C. elegans strains and also in C. briggsae.

label: accumulated somatic cell corpses
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the quantity of non-germ line cells that have undergone programmed cell death but have not been engulfed.

label: crossover formation variant
definition: The number of crossover events differs from that of observed in control animals.

label: long defecation cycle
definition: The mean time between the onset of the defecation motor program is greater than that observed for control animals.

label: pharyngeal pumping increased
definition: The contraction and relaxation movements of the pharynx occur at a greater frequency compared to that observed for control animals.

label: manganese toxicity resistant
definition: Animals fail to exhibit toxicity to the concentration of manganese that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans toxic responses to manganese include dopamine (DA) neuron neurodegeneration.

label: blast cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a blast cell (precursor cell) over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: pirouette variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in turning bouts, consisting of one or more sharp turning events separating consecutive runs, which serve to orient the animal within a gradient, compared to control.

label: excretory secretory system development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the excretory secretory system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control. The excretory secretory system consists of the excretory system and its associated glands.

label: quiescence variant
definition: Exhibition of quiescent behavior under inappropriate conditions and improper recovery from quiescent state. Quiescent behavior is normally coupled with lethargus.

label: male copulatory structure development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the specialized structures of the male tail which allow the animal to sense the presence of the hermaphrodite, search her body for the vulval opening, grasp onto the vulva, and to transfer sperm over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: intestinal degeneration
definition: Animals exhibit degeneration of the intestine, compared to control animals.

label: hermaphrodite sex muscle morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the muscles of the adult hermaphrodite reproductive system compared to control. In C. elegans hermaphrodites these muscles include the vulval and uterine muscles, located near the vulva in the midbody, which all derive from the M myoblast (Wormatlas).

label: increased levels of reactive oxygen species
definition: Animals exhibit increased endogenous levels of reactive oxygen species (chemically reactive molecules containing oxygen) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: blast cell proliferation reduced
definition: The processes governing the expansion of blast cell populations vary, such that cell populations are decreased compared to control.

label: polar body number size early emb
definition: Defects are either seen in the number or size of the polar bodies in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: abamectin resistant
definition: Animals survive longer, or do not respond to the same degree as control animals under similar conditions of abamectin exposure.

label: embryonic lethal
definition: Animals die during embryonic development. In C. elegans, often assayed as refractile eggs that fail to hatch; when applied to large-scale RNAi screens in C. elegans, more than 10% of embryos die.

label: spermatid maturation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the ability of a relatively unspecialized spermatocyte to acquire the properties of a spermatid cell compared to control.

label: cleavage furrow termination defective early emb
definition: Embryos exhibit defects in the maintenance or termination of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate during cytokinesis.

label: anterior body morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the anatomy contained in the anterior region, compared to control animals.

label: biosynthesis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the energy-requiring part of metabolism in which simpler substances are transformed into more complex ones compared to control.

label: no induction of antimicrobial peptide expression after infection
definition: Animals exhibit no induction of expression of an antimicrobial peptide after an infection, unlike control animals.

label: metabolite content decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the quantity of metabolites, small molecule products or intermediates required for the metabolic functioning of the cell or organism

label: peptide uptake by intestinal cell variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the degree to which or manner in which an intestinal cell is able to uptake peptides (for example, di- or tripeptides) from the intestinal lumen, compared to control animals.

label: odorant adaptation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic desensitization to a volatile organic chemo-attractive signal in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control animals.

label: spindle rotation defective early emb
definition: Rotation of the embryonic spindle is aberrant.

label: dauer defective
definition: Failure to form dauer larvae under dauer-inducing conditions.

label: neuropil development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a dense feltwork of interwoven cytoplasmic processes of nerve cells (dendrites and axons) and support cells, over time from an initial condition to a later condition, compared to control.

label: zinc homeostasis variant
definition: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of zinc ions within an organism compared to control.

label: L1 L2 molt defect
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates L1 to L2 transition.

label: spermatheca morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the somatic gonad structure that connects the distal gonad arm to the uterus compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: coiler
definition: The body of an animal assumes a coil-like shape when it attempts to move.

label: butanone chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of butanone. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, butanone is an attractant.

label: later divisions prolonged
definition: The time interval in which late embryonic cell divisions occur is increased compared to control.

label: transgene expression reduced male
definition: Any decrease in the intensity of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA, exclusively in the male, that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: hypoxia response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in response to hypoxia, low oxygen conditions, compared to controls.

label: apoptosis protracted
definition: Animals exhibit a decreased pace of the programmed cell death pathway, compared to that observed for control cells.

label: hexanol chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute characteristic response to hexanol compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of hexanol.

label: osmolarity modulated swimming variant
definition: The swimming behavior of animals are influenced or modulate by the osmolarity of the swimming buffer. The swimming of wild-type C. elegans animals are not affected by the osmolarity of the swimming liquid.

label: hermaphrodite mating efficiency reduced
definition: The number of cross progeny produced by hermaphrodites is reduced compared to control hermaphrodites.

label: endoplasmic reticulum symmetry variant early emb
definition: Any variation in the normally asymmetric distribution of the endoplasmic reticulum during cell divisions of the early embryo. The endoplasmic reticulum (ER) is an irregular network of membranes, that occurs in the cytoplasm, and forms a complex meshwork of tubular channels. The ER has two forms, rough (or granular), with ribosomes adhering to the outer surface, and smooth (with no ribosomes attached).

label: germ nuclei rachis
definition: Germ nuclei are misplaced in the gonad and are observed in the rachis. Sheath cells are observed protruding between these nuclei. Meiotic or mitotic specification of germ nuclei is not affected.

label: cloacal morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the structural appearance of the epithelial chamber that links the genital and alimentary tracts to the exterior via the anus (cloacal opening) compared to control animals.

label: dosage compensation variant
definition: Variations in the process of normalizing the expression level of X-linked genes between XX and XO animals compared to control.

label: body region development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the overall structure or appearance of a discrete region of an animal's anatomy over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: tail swelling
definition: Swelling in the post anal region compared to control. In C. elegans this swelling can be associated with infection from the nematode-specific bacterial pathogen, Microbacterium nematophilum.

label: starvation induced dauer formation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the entry into the dauer stage when exposed to nutrient poor conditions that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: mitotic spindle defective early emb
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubule spindle during a mitotic cell cycle.

label: anaphase I progression variant early embryo
definition: Compared to controls, embryos exhibit variations in the part meiosis I in which homologous chromosomes separate and migrate away from each other.

label: male P lineages variant
definition: The descendants of any of the P precursor cells (P1-P12) in male animals exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: lipid hydrolysis regulation variant
definition: Variations in the process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lipids, compared to control.

label: larval development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a larva over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control. The larva is the early, immature form of an animal between hatching and adulthood.

label: cadmium resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of cadmium that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to cadmium to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: calcium channel modulator resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of calcium channel modulators that elicit a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: cGMP chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of cGMP.

label: egg long
definition: The fertilized oocytes have a greater than standard length measured end to end compared to control.

label: lysosomal refractile body accumulation
definition: Lysosomal refractile bodies are apoptotic-like cell corpse; however, they differ in size and shape and can be described as resembling irregular cell corpses. These bodies have been shown to represent enlarged lysosomes and can occur in conjunction with altered programmed cell death programs.

label: organism heat hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to heat at a lower temperature or a shorter exposure time compared to control animals.

label: plasma membrane leaflet composition variant
definition: Any variation in the components that make up either of the two leaflets of the semipermeable bilayer surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment compared to control.

label: axon morphology variant
definition: Animals display variations in the structure, organization of components, or spatial pattern of the projection that conducts signal away from the cell body, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: sodium chloride chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute characteristic response to sodium chloride compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards attractive concentrations of sodium chloride.

label: marginal cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of marginal cells compared to control animals.

label: alternative splicing variant
definition: Any variation in the process of generating multiple mRNA molecules from a given set of exons by differential use of exons from the primary transcript(s) to form multiple mature mRNAs that vary in their exon composition compared to control.

label: obsolete spermatocyte division abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: ethosuximide resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of ethosuximide, which acts as an anticonvulsant, that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: chemical response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific chemical compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cytoplasmic appearance variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any cellular contents (excluding plasma membrane and nucleus), compared to control animals.

label: pharyngeal pumps brief
definition: The time interval of the stereotyped sequence of muscle contractions by individual pharyngeal muscles that act to draw food into the pharynx is shorter compared to that observed in control (Wormatlas).

label: excess axon outgrowth
definition: Any perturbation that causes an increase in the frequency of axon outgrowth compared to control. As a result, an excess number of axonal projections are generated.

label: organism UV response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to ultraviolet radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: aqueous positive chemotaxis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the movement towards typically attractive water-soluble chemicals compared to control.

label: synapse density variant
definition: The number of synapses per unit area of a neuron differs in the animal compared to that observed for control animals.

label: gonad vesiculated
definition: Animals contain small, fluid-filled, anucleate, spherical membrane-bound structures within the gonad.

label: engulfment variant
definition: Any variation in the removal of a cell corpse, by a neighboring cell or a phagocyte compared to control.

label: temperature influenced life span variant
definition: Life span of the animal is not influenced by changes in temperature in the same manner as control animals.

label: vulva morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the gross structure or organization of the reproductive organ required for depositing eggs and for influencing male mating behavior compared to control.

label: cholesterol depletion resistant
definition: Animals are more resistant to the reduction of cholesterol in the environment compared to control animals.

label: cell number variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the number of cells that make up the organism compared to control animals.

label: mate searching variant
definition: Any variation in the ability of an animal to search for a mate compared to control. In C. elegans, this is defined by failure of the leaving assay.

label: inhibition of oocyte maturation variant
definition: Variations in the processes that negatively regulate the meiotic progression of oocytes (exit from diakinesis) in the absence of a signal compared to control animals.

label: developmental delay
definition: The developmental progression of an animal over time, from its formation to its mature structure is delayed compared to control.

label: neuromuscular synaptic transmission variant
definition: Any variation in the process of communication across a synapse between a neuron and a target muscle cell compared to control animals.

label: body wall muscle relaxation defective
definition: Animals fail to relax their body wall muscles to the same extent as muscles in control animals.

label: age associated fluorescence reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the intensity of fluorescence signals in intestinal cells with advancing age, compared to control.

label: ethanol resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of ethanol that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to ethanol to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C.elegans the phenotype designation Jud is short for JUDang, which is Korean for resistant to alcohol.

label: burrowing assay distance abnormal
definition: Animals exhibit variations, compared to control, in the distance traveled in a burrowing assay, in which animals are placed in a tube, separated from an attractant by solid medium through which the worms can burrow. Variations in distance traveled during the burrowing assay, when controlled for chemosensation defects, have been suggested to reflect variations in neuromuscular efficacy of locomotion.

label: body region pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency or translucency of a particular body region.

label: endocytic transport defect
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the directed movement of substances into, out of or mediated by the endosome, a membrane-bound organelle that trafficks material to different compartments of the cell or back to the plasma membrane for recycling.

label: velocity of movement decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the net velocity of an animal.

label: body muscle displaced
definition: The arrangement of the principal muscle cell type whose contractile activity generates body motion in the nematode differs from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans they consist of 95 unfused cells in the adult organized into four muscle quadrants. Their sarcomeres are obliquely striated and lie lengthwise along the body wall (Wormatlas).

label: serotonin response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of serotonin compared to that observed in control animals. Serotonin is a monoamine neurotransmitter.

label: no anchor cell
definition: Animals are missing the anchor cell. In C. elegans the anchor cell is a key organizer of vulval patterning and morphogenesis.

label: neuron function reduced
definition: Neurons show impaired ability in the detection, transmission, coordination or their response to information about an animal's internal and external environments.

label: germ cell compartment small
definition: Germ cell compartments are smaller than that of control animals.

label: axon development variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that influence the generation of neuronal extensions, that carry efferent (outgoing) action potentials from the cell body towards target cells compared to control.

label: lysosome homeostasis deficient
definition: Animals are deficient in the formation or disassembly of lysosomes.

label: gonad migration variant
definition: Variations in the gross movement of the whole structure of the gonad along the body wall, behind the gonadal leader cell and away from the developing vulva compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: germline transgene silencing variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the homology-dependent transcriptional level silencing of the expression of exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism, in the germline, compared to control.

label: ectopic organ
definition: Animals exhibit one or more organs of a particular type in locations not normally found in controls.

label: UV induced apoptosis increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to the nucleic acid damaging agent, UV irradiation, compared to control.

label: backward locomotion variant
definition: Variations in the spontaneous or induced backward crawling locomotion of an animal compared to control.

label: hypersensitive to protein aggregation induced paralysis
definition: Animals respond to protein aggregation at a lower concentration of aggregates or in less time compared to control animals.

label: male mating efficiency reduced
definition: The number of cross progeny sired by males is reduced compared to control.

label: zinc response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a zinc ion stimulus compared to control.

label: mechanosensory system variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the mechanosensory system over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals. The mechanosensory system is involved in the perception of a mechanical stimuli, its conversion into a signal and the recognition and characterization of the resulting signal.

label: dauer labial sensillum variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the sensilla of the mouth compared to control. In C. elegans, these sensillum are arranged in two (inner and outer) concentric rings around the mouth.

label: metabolic pathway variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in processes that are responsible for chemical changes compared to control animals. Metabolic processes typically transform small molecules, but also include macromolecular processes such as DNA repair and replication, and protein synthesis and degradation.

label: proctodeum development variant
definition: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the male proctodeum over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control. The union of the vas deferens and the intestine give rise to the proctodeum which contains copulatory spicules.

label: fewer glutamatergic neurons
definition: Animals exhibit fewer glutamatergic neurons compared to control animals.

label: thrashing reduced
definition: The number of body thrashes within an aqueous environment in a given period of time are reduced compared with control worms.

label: embryo osmotic pressure sensitive early emb
definition: Embryos rupture when placed on a 2% agar pad and covered with a coverslip.

label: forward point velocity decreased
definition: Animals exhibit decreased velocity of forward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: L3 arrest
definition: The developmental program of the animals does not continue past the third larval stage (L3).

label: muscle cell ultrastructure variant
definition: Animals display variations in the structure or organization of the components of the muscle, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: ectopic cell
definition: Animals exhibit one or more cells of a particular type in locations not normally found in controls.

label: hermaphrodite fertility variant
definition: Hermaphrodites exhibit variations in the time of onset or duration of the fertile period, or variations in the production of viable offspring, including number and state of fertilized eggs laid, compared to controls.

label: synapse morphology variant
definition: Animals display variations in the appearance of the subcellular junctional structure composed of a presynaptic terminal directly opposite the post-synaptic target and separated by a synaptic cleft.

label: antibody staining increased
definition: Any variation that results in an increase in the characteristic expression of a gene product, as detected by antibody staining, compared to control animals.

label: dopamine catabolism defective
definition: Animals are unable to carry outany chemical reaction or pathway resulting in the breakdown of dopamine, a catecholamine neurotransmitter and a metabolic precursor of noradrenaline and adrenaline.

label: pace of P lineage defective early emb
definition: More than five minutes between AB and P1 divisions.

label: developmental behavior variant
definition: Any variation in the behavior characteristic during certain developmental stage(s) compared to control.

label: spermatheca physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the spermatheca to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: anterior pale
definition: Animals have decreased accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that causes increased translucency of the anterior body axis compared to control.

label: myopodia present
definition: Animals exhibit ectopic plasma membrane extensions from muscle, these extensions are random projections that are thinner than the typical muscle arm.

label: alimentary system morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form, structure or composition of the series of related tissues lying within the body cavity and devoted to feeding and digestion compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: lipid synthesis increased
definition: The endogenous anabolism of any lipid species has been increased compared to that observed in control animals.

label: dauer pharynx morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form or composition of the mouthparts at the anterior end of the digestive tract during the dauer stage, compared to control.

label: calcium response to light variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the changes in calcium levels in response to light compared to controls.

label: chromosome condensation failure
definition: The progressive compaction of dispersed interphase chromatin into threadlike chromosomes prior to mitotic or meiotic nuclear division, or during apoptosis in eukaryotic cells is abolished.

label: mitochondrial content variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the overall amount of mitochondria present in the animal, as determined by, for example, Mitotracker staining.

label: programmed cell death variant
definition: Developmentally regulated termination of a cell or cell group does not occur as in control animals.

label: cortical granule exocytosis variant
definition: The process of secretion by a cell that results in the release of intracellular molecules contained within a specialized secretory vesicle that fuses with the plasma membrane during egg activation.

label: anesthetic resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of anesthetic that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: ventral region development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of an animal's anatomy contained in the ventral region over time, compared to control animals.

label: nucleocytoplasmic transport defective
definition: The directed movement of molecules between the nucleus and the cytoplasm is impaired.

label: muscle system physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the muscle system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: struts variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity or patterning of electron-dense columnar structures that join the basal and cortical cuticle layers, from that observed in control animals.

label: levamisole resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of levamisole that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans resistance to levamisole is often assayed via body contraction response, ventral tail curling response etc.

label: spindle aster variant
definition: Any variation in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubule spindle asters during a cell cycle.

label: backing not sustained
definition: Animals initiate but do not continue backward movement, similar to control animals.

label: chromium response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to chromium compared to that observed in control animals.

label: body size variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the physical dimensions of its body compared to control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: embryonic morphology defective early emb
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts during the early embryonic stage.

label: retrograde transport variant
definition: Animals exhibit variation in the directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell periphery in nerve cell axons to the cell body, compared to control.

label: osmotic integrity variant
definition: Any variation in the process involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of water within an organism, compared to control.

label: homologous recombination increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increased frequency of exchange of genetic material between non-sister chromatids of a pair of homologues.

label: nuclear membrane morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the structure, form or composition of the membrane-bounded organelle of eukaryotic cells in which chromosomes are housed and replicated, compared to control.

label: M line absent
definition: Animals lack the planar structure within the muscle sarcomere which lies midway within the thick filament (A) band, attaching to the plasma membrane at its base and running up towards the inward surface of the myofilament lattice, compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: surface antigenicity variant
definition: Cuticles of animals or cuticular extracts exhibit an altered pattern of antibody binding compared to Bristol N2 animals of the same developmental stage.

label: copper hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to copper at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: mitotic metaphase to anaphase transition defect
definition: Cells exhibit variations in the process whereby a cell progresses from metaphase to anaphase during mitosis, compared to control. Metaphase is the second stage of chromosome segregation in the cell cycle where chromosomes become aligned on the equatorial plate of the cell and anaphase is the stage where sister chromatids separate and migrate towards the poles of the spindle.

label: enhanced burst pharyngeal pumping response to light
definition: Animals exhibit an enhanced burst pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that during the5-10 seconds after light exposure onset the pharyngeal pumping rate increases to a greater extent than in controls.

label: neurite connectivity defective
definition: An effective connection between reciprocal target neurons is not established properly.

label: body lengthening response to muscimol variant
definition: The length of the animal does not increase to the same extent as observed for control animals, in response to exposure to muscimol.

label: constitutive egg laying
definition: Eggs are laid under conditions where egg laying is normally inhibited.

label: P4 lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the P4 blastomere exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: cell division variant
