definition: Any variation that alters the physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells compared to control.

label: dopamine adaptation variant
definition: Animals show variations in their decreased responsiveness after prolonged or repeated exposure to dopamine compared to that in control.

label: swimming variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in movement in liquid from that observed for control animals.

label: three fold arrest
definition: Cessation of development that normally occurs in C. elegans 520-620min after the first cleavage at 20C, the stage between the 2-fold and fully elongated embryo.

label: neuronal cell fate specification variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern acquisition of neuronal cell fates compared to control.

label: spindle variant
definition: Any variation in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the array of microtubules and associated molecules that forms between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis and serves to move the duplicated chromosomes apart compared to control.

label: satiety behavior variant
definition: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of an animal after completion of feeding, typically after a fast, compared to that observed in control animals. In C. elegans worms become behaviorally quiescent and cease feeding and moving when sated.

label: endogenous synaptic amplitude variant
definition: The amplitude (magnitude) of currents elicited by fusion of a single endogenous vesicle of transmitter in the absence of presynaptic action potentials is altered compared to control. Changes in amplitude are often interpreted as alterations of postsynaptic responsiveness to the transmitter.

label: mercury hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to mercury at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: cytokinesis fails early emb
definition: Cells of the embryo attempt to divide but fail to form two daughter cells.

label: lectin binding does not occur
definition: Animals are not observed to contain targets for exogenously applied lectins.

label: drug induced locomotion variant
definition: Locomotion of the animal is not influenced by drug exposure in the same manner as control animals.

label: organism UV resistant
definition: Organisms respond to UV at a higer dose or a longer exposure compared to control animals.

label: no back end
definition: Animals lack a properly developed posterior region compared to control. In C. elegans, mutants exhibit a severely deformed posterior region with a variable knob-like shape; accompanied by arrest at about the time of hatching with fairly normal pharyngeal and anterior development. Most mutants arrest as L1 larvae, and 5% do not hatch.

label: tumor prolapse frequency decreased
definition: Animals with a tumorous germline exhibit a decreased frequency of the presence of a tumor prolapse, a protrusion of tumor cells from the vulva, compared to control.

label: pharyngeal morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form or composition of the mouthparts at the anterior end of the digestive tract which contain a series of radial muscles, related neurons and epithelial cells, and several gland cells which may aid in digestion compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the cell, tissue, organ system or organism to carry out its normal functions and activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli compared to control animals.

label: pumping asynchronous
definition: The rhythmic contractions of pharyngeal compartments are no longer synchronized compared to control. In C. elegans the corpus and terminal bulb normally contract simultaneously.

label: stress induced lethality variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in survival when exposed to stress stimuli that induce lethality in control animals.

label: bis phenol A response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to bis phenol A compared to that observed in control animals.

label: energy expenditure variant
definition: Variations in the amount of energy consumed by an organism compared to control. Energy expenditure is often determined by assaying oxygen consumption.

label: DNA damage checkpoint variant
definition: Mitotic cells exhibit variations in the execution of cell-cycle arrest in response to DNA damage.

label: protein degradation variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the directed breakdown of a protein (via the destruction of its native, active configuration) compared to control.

label: omega turns variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the rate of sharp head to tail turns compared to control animals.

label: odorant negative chemotaxis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations through directed movement, in response to repellant volatile organic chemicals, compared to control.

label: lima bean arrest
definition: Cessation of development at an intermediate stage in embryogenesis, immediately following the completion of gastrulation. In C. elegans this occurs around 350-390 minutes after first cleavage, cell number is at approximately 560 cells. At this time cell proliferation ceases and the embryo begins morphogenesis and elongation. The shape of the entire embryo within the eggshell resembles a lima bean (Wormatlas).

label: protein carbonylation increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the covalent modification of one or more native amino acid side chains in proteins to carbonyl derivatives such as an aldehyde or ketone.

label: head movement variant
definition: The anterior portion of the animal exhibits variations in its movement compared to control.

label: reproductive longevity shortened
definition: Animals stop producing progeny significantly before the time reproduction stops in control animals.

label: cell proliferation variant
definition: Any aberrancy in the processes that govern expansion of cell populations compared to control animals.

label: vulval muscle physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the vulva muscle system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: plate tap reflex variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to substrate vibration compared to control.

label: cytokinesis failure
definition: Cells attempt to divide but fail to form two daughter cells.

label: excretory canal morphology variant
definition: Variations in the form or composition of structures made by the processes of the excretory canal cell compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: enflurane hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to the anesthetic enflurane at lower concentrations or shorter exposure times than control animals.

label: rubber band
definition: When prodded on the head, worm contracts and then relaxes along its entire body without moving backwards, compared to a control worm which contracts its anterior end and backs away in response to prodding.

label: organism hypersensitive desiccation
definition: Animals respond to less severe drought-like conditions or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: alae absent
definition: Animals lack the small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle, lengthwise along the body (Wormatlas).

label: gene expression level reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the intensity of expression of a gene product compared to that observed in control animals.

label: tumorous germline
definition: Germ cells do not exit the mitotic cycle, resulting in a expansion of the unspecialized germ cell population compared to control.

label: organism osmotic stress response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to osmotic stress compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism ionizing radiation response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response ionizing radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: response to multiple stressors variant
definition: Any variation in an animal's response to exposure to multiple stressors occuring simultaneously or during an overlapping temporal window compared to control.

label: male postdeirid sensilla absent
definition: Males lack the specialized sensory papillae that lie along the posterior half of the body.

label: acidification level defective
definition: Animals are unable to acidify compartments to the same level as that observed in control animals given the same stimulus.

label: aqueous negative chemotaxis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations through directed movement, in response to repellant water soluble chemicals, compared to control.

label: increased susceptibility to fungal infection
definition: Animals are more prone to infection from fungal pathogens compared to control animals.

label: oocyte morphology variant
definition: Haploid female germ cells (oocytes) exhibit variations in their overall structure, appearance or contents compared to control.

label: innate immune response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their defense responses that are mediated by germline encoded components that directly recognize components of potential pathogens.

label: inactive phase short
definition: The period during which a worm usually does not lay eggs is short compared with control animals, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: amplitude of sinusoidal movement variant
definition: Any variation in the extent of a vibratory movement (as a worm bend) measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control.

label: Z1 hermaphrodite lineage variant
definition: Z1 descendants exhibit altered developmental programs in the hermaphrodite compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: vulva location variant
definition: Any variation in the male's ability to locate his partner's vulva when backing along the ventral side of the partner during mating compared to control. In C. elegans the male stops at the vulva, coordinates his movements to the hermaphrodite's, and positions his tail precisely over the vulva so that he may insert his spicules and ejaculate.

label: pesticide response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to any chemical substance that is used for killing pests, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cyproheptadine resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of cyproheptadine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: pathogen infection clearance rate decreased
definition: Infected animals exhibit a decreased rate of clearance of pathogen infection compared to controls.

label: obsolete unclassified
definition: OBSOLETE. Animals display a phenotype that has not yet been assigned to a current classification.

label: bacterially unswollen
definition: Animals do not exhibit tail-swelling in response to infection by a bacterial pathogen (such as Microbacterium nematophilum) compared to control.

label: dwelling increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the low-speed/high turning movement that usually restricts them to a confined region compared to control.

label: branched adult alae
definition: The small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle of adults are branched as opposed to having an unbiforcated arrangement, lengthwise along the body (Wormatlas).

label: germline RNAi resistant
definition: Animals show reduced susceptibility to gene silencing in the germline triggered by double stranded RNA (RNAi), compared to control.

label: intraflagellar transport velocity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variation rate of directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in nerve cell axons, compared to control.

label: proximal germ cell proliferation variant
definition: Any variation in the spatial pattern of proliferation and differentiation in the germ line compared to control. In C. elegans, this refers to an ectopic mass of proliferating germ cells that occupies the proximal adult germ line, a region normally occupied by gametes.

label: cell membrane physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the composition, component distribution, or other aspect of membranes of the cell, compared to control animals.

label: obsolete connected mitochondria epithelial
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: hormetic temperature induced life span extension defective
definition: Pre-treatment with stress-inducing temperatures does not result in a life-span extension as it does in control animals.

label: DMPP response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to DMPP compared to that observed in control animals.

label: asymmetric cell division variant
definition: Any variation in a cell's ability to divide asymmetrically to produce two daughter cells with different developmental potentials compared to control.

label: intestinal integrity reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a reduction in the integrity of the intestine, compared to controls.

label: isthmus morphology defective
definition: Any observed morphological defects of the isthmus.

label: body vacuole
definition: Vacuoles accumulate in the body. A vacuole is a closed structure, found only in eukaryotic cells, that is completely surrounded by unit membrane and contains liquid material.

label: coiling frequency decreased
definition: Animals spend less time with their body posture in a coil or they decrease the frequency with which they form coils compared to control animals.

label: extra gonad arms
definition: Animals produce an excess number of gonad arms compared to controls.

label: E lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the E blastomere exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: ammonium chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to ammonium compared to control animals.

label: paralyzed
definition: Animals do not move and are not responsive to external mechanical stimulation.

label: dauer axial ratio variant
definition: Any variation in the ratio of the body length to body width in a dauer stage animal, compared to control. Long thin animals will have a high axial ratio.

label: head twisted
definition: The anterior end (which typically includes the anterior sensilla, pharynx and all muscles that are innervated by the nerve ring)of the body appears distorted, usually due to uncharacteristic winding.

label: male nervous system morphology variant
definition: Male animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any component that is part of the complement of organ tissues that serve to detect, relay and coordinate information about an animal's internal and external environments and to initiate and integrate its effector responses and activities, compared to that in control animals.

label: protein acetylation increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the covalent addition of an acetyl group to one or more native amino acid side chains in proteins.

label: cAMP chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to cAMP as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, cAMP is typically an attractant.

label: pseudocleavage absent early emb
definition: No pseudocleavage is observed before or during pronuclear migration.

label: turning frequency variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the frequency of execution of the behavior by which the animal alters its trajectory of movement compared to control, excluding shifts from forward to backward movements (this is reversal).

label: genetic pathway variant
definition: Any variation in the set of interactions occurring between a group of genes who depend on each other's individual functions in order to make the aggregate function of the network available to the cell, compared to control.

label: persistence of paternal mitochondria
definition: Mitochondria from spermatazoa persist in the developing embryo and animal as a result of bypassing the degradation mechanism that normally destroys paternal mitochondria immediately after fertilization. This can often lead to a form of heteroplasmy.

label: spindle oscillation variant
definition: The spindle in the early embryo is aberrant in the characteristic posterior aster oscillations that occur along the transverse longitudinal axis of the spindle.

label: endo siRNA binding variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their selective interactions with small interfering RNA molecules compared to control.

label: nuclear envelope breakdown variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the controlled breakdown of the nuclear envelope, compared to control.

label: membrane fluidity variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in fluidity of cell membranes, compared to control animals.

label: cell UV hypersensitive
definition: Cells respond to a lower dosage of UV or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: body posture wavelength variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in body posture with regard to the distance between repeating units of a wave pattern compared to control animals. In C. elegans, characteristic sinusoidal body posture is sinusoidal.

label: coelomic system physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the coelomic system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: cell division failure
definition: The process of physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells is abolished.

label: male turning defective
definition: The inability of a male to properly turn during mating behavior. In C. elegans, males typically turn via a sharp ventral arch of the tail, as he approaches either the hermaphrodite head or tail.

label: egg morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of fertilized oocytes that are laid compared to those laid by control animals.

label: accessory cell morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure, organization or placement of the cells that support sensory neurons, compared to that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, this category collectively refers to socket cells, sheath cells, and structural cells, or their processes.

label: late embryonic arrest
definition: Cessation of development during the final stages of embryogenesis. In C. elegans, this stage normally occurs 620-800 min after the first cleavage at 20C and is the stage after elongation.

label: fewer seam cells
definition: The population of the lateral, alae-producing epithelial cells (seam cells) is reduced compared to control animals.

label: obsolete no hermaphrodite variantity scored
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: pheromone suppressed pumping defective
definition: Animals treated with pheromone do not exhibit a decrease in pumping rate similar to that observed for control animals.

label: somatic gonad development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the components of the gonad that are separate from the germline proper over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: dauer reduced locomotion variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit a decrease in self-propelled movement on a solid medium compared to control animals.

label: acute pumping response to light variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the acute pharyngeal pumping response to light, during which the pharyngeal pumping rate initially (0-5 seconds after light exposure onset) decreases in response to light, compared to controls.

label: centration defective early emb
definition: The coordinated movement during prophase of the two centrosomes and the two pronuclei towards the center of the one cell embryo is abolished.

label: iron hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to iron at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: pronucleus formation failure early emb
definition: Either the maternal or paternal pronucleus is absent.

label: apical constriction variant
definition: Animals differ from control animals in cortical actomyocin dynamics leading to internalization of endodermal precursor cells during gastrulation.

label: obsolete excretory system morphology abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: spontaneous reversal rate variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern the rate at which spontaneous backward locomotion is initiated compared to control. In C. elegans, animals moving forward consistently initiate backward locomotion approximately 10 times per 3 minutes.

label: octanol chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to 1-octanol as defined by control animals. In C.elegans 1-octanol is typically a repellant.

label: evoked postsynaptic current variant
definition: Variations in the synaptic currents that are elicited by firing an action potential in a population of axons, compared to control.

label: serotonin metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine), a monoamine neurotransmitter, compared to control.

label: cell cell contacts abnormal in four cell embryo
definition: Aba, ABp, EMS, or P1 contacts fewer of its sister cells than in control embryos.

label: sick
definition: Animals exhibit some combination of abnormal features relating to size, movement, body integrity, pigmentation, viability, fertility etc.

label: DMPP resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of DMPP that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: meiotic spindle defective
definition: Cells undergoing meiosis exhibit defects in the overall function or activity of the meiotic spindle.

label: gametogenesis variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern the generation and maintenance of gametes compared to control.

label: cuticle physiology variant
definition: Animals produce cuticles that vary in components such as proteins or carbohydrates, observed in control animals of the same developmental stage and raised under the same conditions.

label: synaptic transmission variant
definition: Any variation in the process of communication across a synapse between a neuron and a target cell (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) compared to control animals.

label: gubernaculum development variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the development of the sclerotic cuticle that forms the roof of the proctodeum (gubernaculum) compared to control.

label: electrophoretic variant protein
definition: Any variation in the movement of a protein through a gel matrix when an electric field is applied compared to control.

label: hindgut morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the more posterior portion of the intestine, just anterior to the sphincter valve, which is subject to squeezing by the somatal-intestinal muscles compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: pharyngeal pump duration increased
definition: The duration of the contraction of the pharyngeal muscle during pumping is increased compared to controls.

label: increased susceptibility to viral infection
definition: Animals are more prone to infection by virus compared to control animals.

label: chromosome decondensation failure
definition: The process of decompaction of chromatin that changes chromosome structure from the condensed form to a relaxed disperse form is abolished.

label: male longitudinal muscle morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the male longitudinal muscle compared to control animals.

label: germ cell resistant ionizing radiation
definition: Germ cells fail to respond to the dosage of ion producing radiation that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, germ cells require a higher dosage or a longer exposure to ion producing radiation to elicit the same response as control animals.

label: starved
definition: Animals exhibit morphological characteristics that are the outcome of nutrient deprivation. In C. elegans, starved worms have fewer refractile granules in intestinal cells, making them appear pale. Strongly starved mutants are small and thin, and tend to retain fewer eggs than control animals.

label: unfertilized oocytes laid
definition: Animals lay inactivated oocytes. In C elegans this may be due to perturbations that eliminate spermatogenesis or result in the production of defective sperm.

label: odorant discrimination defective
definition: Animals fail to discriminate between distinct odorants.

label: pheromone behavioral response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the behavioral response to pheromones, compared to control.

label: precocious seam cell fusion
definition: Seam cells fuse to form a continuous syncytium along the body wall at an earlier stage of development compared to control.

label: protein expression reduced hermaphrodite
definition: Variations that result in a decrease in protein expression in hermaphrodites compared to that observed in control animals.

label: fewer body wall muscles
definition: Any variation that results in a fewer than control number of body wall muscle cells.

label: exaggerated asynchrony early emb
definition: Asynchrony of the second division is exaggerated and P1 divides more slowly than normal.

label: cell size decreased
definition: The diameter, volume, or area taken up by a cell differs from that measured in control animals.

label: manganese response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to manganese compared to that observed in control animals.

label: telomere homeostasis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the processes that affect and monitor the activity of telomeric proteins and the length of telomeric DNA, which allow the chromosome to persist from generation to generation, compared to control.

label: late stage egg laid
definition: The eggs being deposited by adults are of a later developmental stage, compared to control. In C. elegans, this is likely to be a consequence of delayed active egg-laying periods.

label: supernumerary asters
definition: Dividing cells exhibit additional arrays of microtubules emanating from a spindle pole that do not connect to kinetochores, compared to control.

label: larval physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the larva to carry out its normal metabolic functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: voltage gated channel activity variant
definition: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a solute by a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded is altered from that observed for controls.

label: male longitudinal muscle development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of somatic (striated) muscles that run longitudinally in males over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control. In C. elegans males have 3 additional sets of sex-specific longitudinal muscles (anterior and posterior outer, anterior and posterior inner, and caudal) that contribute to the body wall musculature (Wormatlas).

label: RNA degradation variant
definition: Variations in the regulated breakdown of RNA species via the action of cellular enzymes (RNases) compared to control.

label: DNA metabolism variant
definition: Variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of DNA in the organism compared to control.

label: excess intestinal cells
definition: Animals contain an excess number of intestinal cells compared to control. In C. elegans, intestinal cells are derived from E-blastomere. The overproduction of intestinal tissues is a result of other blastomeres adopting an E-like fate or excess cell proliferation in the E lineage.

label: sodium chloride adaptation defective
definition: Animals do not exhibit characteristic chemoattractive desensitization to sodium chloride in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control.

label: backing uncoordinated
definition: Backward movement is not coordinated as in control. This often causes jerky or spastic backward locomotion.

label: DNA damage induced focus formation variant
definition: Variations in the aggregation of molecules at the site of DNA strand breakage or damage compared to control.

label: pale larva
definition: Larva show deficiencies in chroma resulting in increased translucency.

label: glucose intolerant
definition: Animals do not live or live poorly in the presence of glucose concentrations that normally do not have an effect on control animals.

label: inactive phase variant
definition: The period during which the animal is less likely to lay eggs is not typical compared with control animals, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: extra rays
definition: Animals exhibit an extra number of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan.

label: sinusoidal movement variant
definition: Any variation in the propagation of the contraction sine wave along the body while an animal travels from one location to another, compared to control.

label: transmission of nerve impulse variant
definition: Transmission of the signal along the neuron varies from control.  This process includes the flow of information from the neuron cell body to the synapse and across to the postsynaptic cell.

label: hypersensitive to laser ablation
definition: Animals respond more severely to laser ablation than control animals subjected to the same laser ablation conditions.

label: resistant to bioactive compound
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of a bioactive compound that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.  A bioactive compound is a chemical found in small amounts in organisms or, synthetically produced, that has effects on biological processes in another organism.

label: extra sex myoblasts
definition: Animals produce an excess number of sex myoblasts compared to controls.

label: male ray morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan compared to control animals. In C. elegans, nine bilateral rays project from the tail in a radial pattern with a smooth and slightly tapered appearance. Although one neuronal member of each ray sensillum is exposed to the outside, male rays rarely take up dye.

label: protein expression ectopic
definition: Any variation that results in the cellular expression of a protein in cells/tissues, that is otherwise not observed in control animals.

label: mechanosensation variant
definition: Any variation with respect to perception or response to mechanical stimuli compared to control animals.

label: cell survival sexually dimorphic increased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the rate or extent of programmed cell death and thus an increase in cell survival, as it pertains to a sex-specific feature, compared to control populations.

label: enzyme activity increased
definition: Any variation that results in an increase in the catalytic activity of an enzyme compared to control. Catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component).

label: patchy coloration
definition: Animals exhibit an uneven distribution of biochromes or any other substances that cause disparate transparency/translucency compared to control animals.

label: embryonic arrest
definition: Cessation of development during any stage occurring after fertilization and until hatching compared to control.

label: chemosensation defective
definition: Animals fail to receive, process or recognize a sensory chemical stimulus in the same manner as control animals.

label: non bordering
definition: Animals do not accumulate at the thickest part of the bacterial lawn. Animals do not preferentially deplete bacterial food at the thicker parts of the lawn.

label: colchicine resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of colchicine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: nullo X gamete
definition: Animals produce ova/sperm that contain no X chromosome in a nonmendelian segregation pattern.

label: rays fused
definition: Any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan are joined to one another.

label: aqueous positive chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to move towards attractive water-soluble chemicals.

label: forward locomotion variant
definition: Variations in the spontaneous or induced forward crawling locomotion of an animal compared to control.

label: amphid channel axoneme short
definition: The microtuble-based fibrillar-bundles of the amphid sensory cilia are reduced in length compared to those in control animals.

label: pre miRNA processing defective
definition: The production of mature miRNA from pre-miRNA is significantly deficient compared to controls. Deficiencies in this process can result in the accumulation of pre-miRNA species and or the absence or smaller amount of mature miRNA compared to controls.

label: AWA odorant chemotaxis defective
definition: In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards typically attractive volatile organic molecules sensed by the AWA compared to control.

label: sperm release defective
definition: Any variation in the initial movement of sperm through the vas deferens, exiting the cloaca, compared to control.

label: fewer gonadal sheath cells
definition: Animals exhibit fewer somatic sheath cells surrounding each gonad arm, compared to controls.

label: acetylcholinesterase inhibitor hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to an acetylcholinesterase inhibitor at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: ectopic expression antibody
definition: Any variation that results in the detection of protein expression in cells/tissues through antibody staining, that is otherwise not observed in control animals.

label: cilia absent
definition: Neurons lack the finger-like dendritic projections, which are observed extending from similar cells in control animals.

label: pausing variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of time spent in a paused state, which is neither moving forward or backward, compared to control animals.

label: obsolete metaphase to anaphase transition fails
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: protein expression reduced
definition: Any change that results in lower than normal levels of protein expression compared to control animals.

label: population fitness variant
definition: Populations exhibit variations in the ability to survive, grow and reproduce, thus affecting the contribution to the gene pool over generations compared to control populations.  In C. elegans the fitness of a population can by assessed by measuring the rate at which E. coli is consumed.

label: male morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the outcome of morphogenic processes required for formation or proper placement of sex-specific structures that distinguish the animal as a male in the population, from that observed for control males.

label: oocytes lack nucleus
definition: Haploid female germ cells (oocytes) lack a nucleus.

label: bloated
definition: Worms appears turgid or swollen as a result of an excess number of eggs being retained in the uterus.

label: cholesterol depletion hypersensitive
definition: Animals are more sensitive to the reduction of cholesterol in the environment compared to control animals.

label: presynaptic vesicle cluster localization variant
definition: Animals display variations in the distribution of transmitter-filled vesicles in relation to the electron-dense membrane specialization of the neuron,compared to that observed in control animals.

label: mitochondria spacing variant
definition: Variations in the spatial distribution of the mitochondria within the cell compared to control.

label: garlic chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to garlic as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, garlic is typically a repellent.

label: fertilization defective hermaphrodite
definition: Any perturbation that disrupts the fusion of male and female gametes (sperm and oocyte) in adult hermaphrodites during sexual reproduction.

label: organ system pigmentation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of a organ system.

label: synchronization calcium signal defective pharynx
definition: Calcium spikes lack synchrony in the musculature of the corpus and the terminal bulb as seen in control.

label: body proportion decreased
definition: Animals exhibit decreases in the body-area-to-length ratio and/or the width-to-length ratio, compared to control animals.

label: exo-RNAi response variant
definition: RNAi silencing mechanisms triggered by exogenously introduced (foreign) dsRNA, do not work to the same degree as in control animals.

label: gut granules enlarged
definition: Animals exhibit larger inclusions within the intestinal cytoplasm, including birefringent crystalline objects and other dark-staining endosomes. In C. elegans these contents typically include glycogen granules (polysaccharide storage), rhabditin (carbohydrate storage), yolk granules (lipid and protein), and concentrated waste products (Wormatlas).

label: postembryonic cell lineage variant
definition: The descendants of a postembryonic precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: mating plug produced
definition: Males form copulatory mating plugs.

label: positive chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of an animal in response to chemical attractants as defined by control animals.

label: dauer induction variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the entry into the dauer stage when exposed to conditions that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: yolk synthesis in males
definition: Males generate yolk, the nutrient protein, normally produced and secreted by hermaphrodite or female intestinal cells.

label: protein phosphorylation variant
definition: Variations in the processes that incorporate phosphate groups to one or more amino acids within a protein, compared to control.

label: amphid phasmid morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the neuronal cells of the amphid and phasmid sensilla from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling experiments using FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: pronuclear morphology defective early emb
definition: Pronucleus morphology is atypical in the inviable embryo.

label: nose movement increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the movement of the extreme anterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: X0 lethal
definition: XO-bearing individuals die preferentially over other animals in the population. In C.elegans, X0 animals die preferentially over XX animals.

label: synapsis formation variant
definition: Animals differ from controls in respect to the formation of paired chromosome loci.

label: cryophilic
definition: Animals tend to track and stay within low temperature environments.

label: pachytene region organization variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations from control animals in the organization of the germ cell nuclei in the pachytene stage region of the gonad. In C. elegans the pachytene region begins just proximal to the germline's transition zone, where germ cells coordinately switch into the leptotene/zygotene stage from the premeiosis stage (WormAtlas).

label: axon midline crossing variant
definition: Regulated ventral midline crossing by axons vary either in the frequency of crossing events or the maintenance through development of process positions compared to control.

label: body wall muscle cell polarization variant
definition: Variations in the accumulation of muscle proteins at membranes where adjacent muscle cells contact each other and the hypodermis compared to control. In C. elegans, during early embryonic body wall muscle development, muscle, basement membrane, and hypodermal components are all colocalized in a continuous linear structure at the site of muscle-hypodermal contact.

label: pharynx length variant
definition: Animals vary in the distance between most anterior and the most posterior ends of the pharynx from that observed in control animals.

label: anoxia resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to trace amounts of oxygen that elicit a response in control animals.

label: head bend angle decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of the maximum flex of the most anterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: pharyngeal muscle physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for muscles in the pharynx to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: lysosome-related organelle morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosome-related organelles (LROs) that, like lysosomes, have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell but are distinct in function, composition, and morphology, compared to control.

label: dauer recovery inhibited
definition: The process through which a dauer larva reverts to normal developmental programs is blocked.

label: vulval cell induction increased
definition: An excess number of vulval precursor cells receive an inductive signal leading to an increased number of VPCs adopting vulval fates compared to control animals.

label: RNA processing variant
definition: Variations in the processes involved in the conversion of one or more primary RNA transcripts into one or more mature RNA molecules compared to control.

label: fewer pharyngeal cells
definition: Animals contain fewer pharyngeal cells compared to control animals.  In C. elegans, pharyngeal cells are derived from MS-blastomere.

label: embryonic behavior variant
definition: Activity characteristic of an embryo is altered compared to control.

label: tunicamycin hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to tunicamycin at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: quinine chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to the bitter tastant quinine, as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, quinine is typically repellent.

label: neuronal ECM variant
definition: Any variation in makeup, density or area of the ECM lending structure to neurons compared to control animals. In C. elegans, the neuronal ECM is sometimes referred to as a mantle.

label: repetitive transgene expression reduced
definition: Animals exhibit reduced expression of repetitive exogenous DNA compared to control.

label: excretory canals long
definition: The structure made by the processes of the excretory canal cell is increased in size compared to control. In C. elegans this is an H-shaped structure which extends almost the full length of the body on both sides of the animal, generally in contact with the lateral hypodermis and the pseudocoelom (Wormatlas).

label: organelle organization biogenesis variant
definition: Intracellular membrane bound compartments vary in shape or size from that observed in control animals.

label: octopamine metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving octopamine, 1-(p-hydroxyphenyl)-2-aminoethanol, compared to control.

label: hypersensitive to zinc deficiency
definition: Animals exhibit detrimental responses to zinc deficiency more readily than control animals

label: paternal pronucleus migrates early emb
definition: Instead of the maternal pronucleus migrating to the posterior end of the one-cell embryo, the paternal pronucleus migrates to meet the maternal pronucleus in the anterior end.

label: pore forming toxin response variant
definition: Animals are not affected to the same degree as control animals under similar conditions of pore forming toxin exposure.

label: adult lethal
definition: Premature lethality during the adult stage. When applied to large-scale RNAi screens in C. elegans, this phenotype is present in at least 10% of analyzed worms, or at least 30% in the case of rrf-3 perturbed background.

label: high sodium chloride concentration osmotic avoidance defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to high concentrations of sodium chloride solution. C. elegans typically avoids high concentrations of sodium chloride solution.

label: gamma ray induced apoptosis decreased
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to the nucleic acid damaging agent, gamma irradiation, compared to control.

label: cilia length variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the length of the microtubule-based dendritic projections extending from the cell body, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism osmostic stress resistant
definition: Animals exhibit resistance to osmotic stress compared to that observed in control animals.

label: endosome morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as endosomes,  that traffic material between the plasma membrane and internal compartments of the cell, compared to control.

label: sperm transfer initiation defective
definition: Any defect in the movement of sperm out of the seminal vesicle and into the vas deferens following tonic insertion of spicules into the mating partner compared to control.

label: reduced body bend
definition: The maximum ventral and dorsal flex of the animal is reduced compared to that observed for control animals.

label: zygotic development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a zygote from formation (gamete fusion) to just prior to the first cell division compared to control.

label: cell cell contacts abnormal early emb
definition: Cell-cell contacts are abnormal in the early embryo.

label: serotonin hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to serotonin at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: lateral ganglia development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the left and right lateral ganglia which lie beside the nerve ring in the head over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: Dosage compensation complex assembly variant
definition: Any variation in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins on DNA or RNA to form the complex that mediates dosage compensation on one or more X chromosomes, compared to control.

label: spindle elongation integrity defective early emb
definition: The embryos exhibit defects in the cell cycle process whereby the distance is lengthened between poles of the spindle.

label: presynaptic vesicle number variant
definition: Animals exhibit a variation in the ratio of synaptic vesicles per synapse of a neuron, compared to control animals.

label: organ system physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in a physical or chemical process required for organs or tissues to carry out their normal functions or for their ability to perceive and respond to stimuli compared to control.

label: dauer pheromone sensation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any of a series of events in which a pheromone stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal that induces dauer formation in control animals.

label: sperm excess
definition: Animals produce an increased sperm population compared to control.

label: acetylcholinesterase inhibitor resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of acetylcholinesterase inhibitor that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: EGF-induced sleep resistant
definition: Animals respond with sleeping behavior induced through the EGF pathway, more rigorously than control animals. The EGF-induced sleep pathway is thought to represent a distinct molecular pathway from developmentally linked sleep. The EGF-induced sleep state occurs in two contexts: by overexpressing the EGF ortholog (LIN-3C), or by EGF signaling after stress (such as temperature elevation) in wildtype animals.

label: distal tip cell migration variant
definition: Variations in the migration pattern of distal tip cells compared to control animals. In C. elegans, DTCs located on the anterior and posterior ends of the gonad primordium typically migrate in a symmetrical U-shaped pattern.

label: nose twisted
definition: The extreme anterior part of the body appears distorted, usually due to uncharacteristic winding.

label: phytochelatin synthesis deficient
definition: Animals do not produce the same amount of functional phytochelatins as measured in control worms. Phytochelatins are any of a group of peptides that bind metals (Cd, Zn, Cu, Pb, Hg) in thiolate coordination complexes.

label: ivermectin resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to or exhibit an attenuated response to ivermectin under conditions that elicits a response in control animals.

label: M line variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a planar structure within the muscle sarcomere which lies midway within the thick filament (A) band, attaching to the plasma membrane at its base and running up towards the inward surface of the myofilament lattice, compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: excretory socket cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the excretory socket cell compared to control animals.

label: exocytosis variant
definition: Variations in the process of secretion by a cell that results in the release of intracellular molecules (e.g. hormones, matrix proteins) contained within a membrane-bounded vesicle by fusion of the vesicle with the plasma membrane of a cell, compared to control.

label: obsolete synaptic output abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: obsolete muscle activation defective
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: obsolete posterior body wall shortened interval
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: P granule localization defective
definition: The restricted localization of P granules to germ cells or germ cell precursors is altered compared to control.

label: galactose metabolism variant
definition: Animals process dietary galactose differently than control animals, these differences can result in increased and or decreased levels of intermediary galactose metabolites.

label: aster AB resembles P1 aster early emb
definition: The morphology of the AB aster resembles that of the P1 aster in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: biotin chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute the characteristic response to biotin as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, biotin is typically an attractant.

label: neuronal sheath cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a neuronal sheath cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control. A neuronal sheath cell is a structural cell that forms a specialized environment surrounding the sensory endings of a neuron.

label: benomyl response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to the microtubule-depolymerizing drug benomyl, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: spindle orientation defective early emb
definition: The alignment of the spindle relative to other cellular structures in the cells of an embryo varies from that observed in control animals.

label: X chromosome nondisjunction
definition: The frequency of sex chromosome segregation is perturbed, resulting in the production of exceptional gametes (e.g. ova or sperm) and populations with a sex ratio altered from the rate of 1:500 as observed for control populations.

label: axon cisternae
definition: Axons of animals contain flattened membrane-bound compartments. In C. elegans, these cisternae-like structures are typically absent.

label: pyrazine chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of pyrazine. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, pyrazine is an attractant.

label: pathogen avoidance variant
definition: Variations in the characteristic movement away from specific disease causing agents (pathogens) compared to control animals.

label: expulsion infrequent
definition: The final step of the defecation motor program does not occur at each cycle, but is activated occasionally. During this step in C. elegans specialized enteric muscles contract to expel the contents of the gut through the anus.

label: coenzyme Q depleted
definition: Animals contain a lower level of coenzyme Q, an oil-soluble vitamin-like substance present in most eukaryotic cells, primarily in the mitochondria, compared to control. It is a component of the electron transport chain and participates in aerobic cellular respiration.

label: no dauer recovery
definition: Animals fail to exit from the facultative diapause of the dauer larval stage of nematode development.

label: male somatic gonad development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the components of the male gonad that are separate from the germline proper over time, from its formation to its mature structure compared to control.  In C. elegans, the male somatic gonad consists of three tissues: distal tip cells (DTCs), the seminal vesicle, and the vas deferens (Wormatlas).

label: obsolete NaCl response variant
definition: OBSOLETE. Organismal response to NaCl differs from control animals.

label: basal lamina morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the basal lamina compared to control animals.

label: enhanced taste aversion defective
definition: The conditioned aversion to a specific chemical compound as a result of that compound being coupled with an unfavorable condition, such as starvation, does not increase to the same extent as observed for control animals.

label: obsolete cellular secretion abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: locomotion rate serotonin hypersensitive
definition: The decrease in locomotion rate in the presence of serotonin is greater than control animals.

label: cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the form or composition of the basic structural and functional unit of all organisms compared to control. Includes the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: octanol chemotaxis hypersensitive
definition: Animals execute a response, via directed movement to octanol at a lower concentration or shorter exposure time compared to control. In C. elegans, animals avoid octanol.

label: obsolete cloaca morphology abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: anterograde transport defective
definition: The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell body toward the cell periphery in nerve cell axons is disrupted.

label: body wall muscle contraction abnormal
definition: Initiation, strength, extent or cessation of body wall muscle activity that results in the shortening of the muscle, is aberrant compared to control animals.

label: lithium chemotaxis defective
definition: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to lithium. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards lithium.

label: apoptotic DNA degradation defective
definition: Dying animals cells exhibit defects in the fragmentation of chromosomal DNA into oligonucleosomal-length fragments compared to control animals. This process can be monitored by the quantity and quality of TUNEL (TdT-mediated dUTP nick end labeling)-positive nuclei.

label: approximate vulval location variant
definition: Any variation in the mating process that includes the male stopping at the vulva (usually after backing) compared to control. In C. elegans general vulva location (stopping) requires the hook sensillum.

label: bivulva
definition: Animals exhibit a secondary vulval invagination that is anterior or posterior to the primary opening depending on the the inappropriate placement of daughter cells along the anterior/posterior axis during vulval development.

label: hypoxia hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to hypoxic (low oxygen levels) stress after a shorter exposure time compared to control.

label: obsolete spermatocyte germ cell differentiation abnormal
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: inhibition of synaptogenesis hyperactive
definition: The processes that inhibit the location or frequency of formation of synapses are upregulated compared to control.

label: conditional attraction to bacterial lawn
definition: Animals show a stronger preference for a particular bacterium that has been grown under conditions that differ from a control lawn.

label: oxidative DNA damage variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in levels of DNA damage caused by oxidative stress.

label: transgene expression variant
definition: Any variation in the characteristic expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to control animals.

label: mid larval lethal
definition: Animals die in between the early and late larval stages. In C. elegans, this occurs during the L2- L3 larval stages of the life cycle.

label: excretory duct cell development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of an interfacial epithelial cell which forms a lumen to receive the outflow of the excretory gland and excretory canal cells, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: endomitotic oocytes
definition: Any variation that results in the presence of mature oocytes with distended polyploid nuclei. In C. elegans, such oocytes mature and exit diakinesis, but are often not properly ovulated or fertilized.

label: embryonic rupture
definition: During development of the embryo, the epidermis loses integrity and the contents of the embryo are expelled.

label: isothermal tracking behavior variant
definition: Variations in the ability of an animal to remain within a defined temperature. In C. elegans, animals tend to track and stay within a temperature that is most closely related to their cultivation temperature.

label: egg laying serotonin hypersensitive
definition: Animals lay eggs at a greater rate in response to exogenous serotonin compared to control animals.

label: distal germline variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the lineages that gives rise to all germ cells, lying in the region adjacent to the proximal gonad (on the side furthest from the founder cells of the somatic gonad), over time compared to control animals.

label: over retracted male tail
definition: Adult males exhibit a truncated tail, often without a fan or have well-developed fans but squarish, truncated back ends compared to control. In C. elegans this is due to precocious male tail tip retraction beginning in the early L3 stage (normally retraction begins in the L4 stage). Condition can be lethal if the function of the anus is affected.

label: path curvature increased
definition: Animals exhibit increases in the extent to which the overall path of movement is curved, producing tighter and more frequent curves compared to control animals.

label: pharyngeal intestinal valve development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the cells that form a narrow passage connecting the posterior bulb of the pharynx to the anterior intestine over time compared to control. In C. elegans this valve is composed of 3 pairs of cells each forming a flattened disc-like ring and is lined by a layer of cuticle (Wormatlas).

label: intraflagellar transport slow
definition: The rate, frequency or extent of bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum is lower compared to control.

label: small RNA germline expression variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations from controls in the expression, biogenesis, processing, or stability of any class of small RNA species in the germline. Small RNAs include microRNAs (miRNAs), tiny noncoding RNAs (tncRNAs), cluster of small X-chromosome derived RNAs (X cluster), and endogenous short interfering RNA (endo-siRNAs).

label: anion positive chemotaxis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic movement towards typically attractive anions compared to control.

label: male response to contact defective
definition: The inability of a male to respond properly to a potential mate after contact. In C.elegans, proper response includes apposing the ventral side of his tail to the hermaphrodite's body and swimming backward.

label: long range axon migration variant
definition: Animals exhibit axons with migration behaviors that differ from those observed in control animals after the axons cross a half-way point between opposing neural cords. In C. elegans this point is marked by the lateral seam cells between the ventral and dorsal cords.

label: larval pigmentation variant
definition: Larva exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter its transparency/translucency compared to control animals.

label: cytoplasmic processing body variant
definition: Discrete foci within the cytoplasm containing congregations of mRNA translational suppression and degradation mechanisms vary in their arrangement, clustering or are otherwise not well-defined compared to control.

label: distal tip cell reflex failure
definition: A migrating distal tip cell (DTC) fails to follow the stereotypical path. In C. elegans this path is U-shaped and results in the formation of reflexed gonadal arm.

label: muscimol hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to muscimol at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: pattern of gene expression variant
definition: Any variation in the cellular or subcellular distribution of a gene product compared to that observed in control animals.

label: drug susceptible
definition: Animals are affected by exposure to the drug.

label: developmental growth variant
definition: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) during any development stages compared to control animals.

label: diplotene progression during oogenesis variant
definition: Developing oocytes show defects in their entry, progression through or exit from the diplotene stage compared to control animals. Diplotene is a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the fourth stage of prophase I in meiosis, in which the homologous chromosomes begin to separate and the synaptonemal complex dissolves.

label: intraflagellar transport variant
definition: Variations in the bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum, compared to control.

label: neuropeptide metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of signalling peptides in the organism compared to control.

label: osmotic avoidance variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the avoidance response to solutions of a particular osmotic strength compared to control. In C. elegans, animals typically avoid solutions of high osmotic strength.

label: nuclei enlarged
definition: Nuclei of specific cells are larger compared to control animals.

label: progressive paralysis
definition: Animals become increasingly sluggish/immobilized as they age.

label: break induced focus formation variant
definition: Variations in the generation of foci that mark crossover recombination events, compared to control. These foci mark the boundary of asymmetric synaptonemal complex disassembly.

label: gap junction plaque number increased
definition: One or more cells exhibit an increase in number of gap junction plaques, sets of associated gap junctions, compared to controls.

label: vulva uterus connection defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the continuity of lumen between the vulva and uterus compared to control animals.

label: division EMS before P2 early emb
definition: EMS divides before P2.

label: obsolete temporal frequency of sinusoidal movement increased
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: lineage variant
definition: The descendants of a particular precursor cell exhibit variations in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: oxygen consumption variant
definition: Variations in the process of gaseous oxygen intake between an organism and its environment compared to control animals.

label: neuron development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a neuron over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: habituation variant
definition: Any variation in the decrease in a behavioral response to a repeated stimulus compared to control.

label: protein subcellular localization variant
definition: Any variation in the placement of a protein within in a cell or cellular compartment compared to control.

label: defecation cycle variable length
definition: Animals exhibit variation in the time of onset of the defecation motor program significantly greater than that observed for control animals.

label: late larval arrest
definition: Larvae arrest during late larval development. In C. elegans, larval arrest occurs during the L3 or L4 stages of larval development.

label: gonad sheath contraction rate reduced
definition: Basal contraction rate and or peak contraction rate of the gonadal sheath is reduced relative to control animals.

label: recycling endosome localization variant
definition: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes,  that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: gland cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the gland cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to signals, compared to control animals.

label: anterior body behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the longitudinal axis that spans from the midpoint to the tip of the head of an animal in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: rachis absent
definition: The nucleus-free core of germline cytoplasm in the gonad is missing.

label: vesicle trafficking variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in vesicle-based directed movement of substances into, out of, or within a cell compared to control.

label: dauer outer labial sensillum variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the outer labial ring compared to control. In C. elegans, this ring consists of four sensilla (OLQ) or the two additional lateral sensilla (OLL), which are part of the labial sensillum.

label: RNA methylation variant
definition: Variations in the processes that incorporate methyl groups to one or more bases within RNA, compared to control.

label: protein DNA interaction variant
definition: Variations in the selective and non-covalent physical association between a protein and a specific DNA sequence, compared to control.

label: dauer lifespan shortened
definition: The life span of dauer-staged animals is shorter than that observed in control dauer animals.

label: fat content variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of fat or lipids present in the organism compared to control animals.

label: crossover distribution variant
definition: The location-specific frequency of crossover events differs from that of observed in control animals, while the total number of crossover events does not significantly differ.

label: short defecation cycle
definition: The mean time between the onset of the defecation motor program is shorter than that observed for control animals.

label: pharyngeal pumping reduced
definition: Pharyngeal pumping motion occurs at a slower rate than control animals.

label: fewer eggs laid
definition: Animals lay fewer total number of eggs over the lifetime of the animal.

label: epithelial cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of an epithelial cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: pirouette frequency variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the number of directional changes over time from that observed for control animals.

label: excretory system development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the excretory system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The excretory system is required for the elimination of metabolic waste. In C. elegans, the excretory system is comprised of the excretory cell, excretory duct cell and excretory socket cell.

label: terminal bulb morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the posterior region of the pharynx compared to control.

label: protein glycosylation variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the degree to which some proteins are glycosylated, compared to controls.

label: hermaphrodite copulatory structure development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the specialized structures of a hermaphrodite which allow the successful transfer of sperm from a male, compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite reproductive system morphology variant
definition: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the hermaphrodite reproductive system, compared to control. The reproductive system is involved in the generation of progeny which contain genetic material inherited from the parents.

label: accumulated cell corpses
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the quantity of cells that have undergone programmed cell death but have not been engulfed.

label: reduced levels of reactive oxygen species
definition: Animals exhibit reduced endogenous levels of reactive oxygen species (chemically reactive molecules containing oxygen) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: polar body number defective early emb
definition: Polar body number is abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: embryonic terminal arrest variable emb
definition: The developmental program does not continue past embryogenesis; stage of arrest is not consistent from animal to animal.

label: abamectin repsonse variant
definition: Animals are not affected to the same degree as control animals under similar conditions of abamectin exposure.

label: fertilization defective
definition: Any perturbation that disrupts the fusion of male and female gametes (sperm and oocyte) during sexual reproduction.

label: excess seam cells
definition: Animals execute supernumerary cell divisions during the development of the lateral, alae-producing epithelial cells, resulting in a larger number of these cells than control animals.

label: posterior body morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the anatomy contained in the posterior region, compared to control animals.

label: chondroitin biosynthesis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of chondroitin sulfate compared to control.

label: pathogen adherence decreased
definition: Pathogens exhibit decreased adherence to the surface of host animals.

label: food absorption rate variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the rate at which food is absorbed by the intestine, as determined by a time-course recording of fat staining (by C1-BODIPY-C12, for example) normalized to controls

label: peptide uptake by intestinal cell increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the degree to which an intestinal cell is able to uptake peptides (for example, di- or tripeptides) from the intestinal lumen, compared to control animals.

label: anterior body contraction defecation cycle variant
definition: Variations in the anterior body muscle contraction (aBoc) step of the defecation cycle compared to control animals. Under normal conditions, anterior body wall muscles contract and pressurize the intestinal contents during the aBoc step.

label: P0 spindle rotation failure early emb
definition: P0 spindle fails to rotate and extends perpendicular to the long axis of the embryo.

label: cord commissures variant
definition: Variations in the structure, organization or path of axon tracts that grow circumferentially around the animal in a single, directed trajectory to bridge the ventral and dorsal cords, compared to control animals.

label: pharyngeal nervous system development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the pharyngeal nervous system over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals. The nervous system is involved in the coordination and control of bodily activities and the interpretation of information from the senses.

label: L2 L3 molt defect
definition: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates L2 to L3 transition.

label: cell growth variant
definition: Variations in the process(es) by which a cell irreversibly increases in size over time by accretion and biosynthetic production of matter compared to control.

label: reduced levels of reduced glutathione
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the cellular levels of reduced glutathione (GSH), compared to control. Reduced levels of GSH may be an indication of susceptibility to oxidative stress.

label: ventral coiler
definition: A coiling body that bends ventrally.

label: rhythmic tolerance to osmotic stress variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in light/dark cycle recurrence of reactions to osmotic stress compared to that observed for control animals.

label: no uterine cavity
definition: Animals lack the inner space of the uterus through which the fertilized egg passes on its way out of the nematode via the vulva (Wormatlas).

label: posterior neuron migration variant
definition: Any variation in the orderly movement of neurons along the posterior axis of the animal(abolished, misdirected or incomplete) compared to control.

label: anoxia response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in response to anoxia, trace oxygen conditions, compared to controls.

label: oogenesis variant
definition: Any aberrancy in the processes that influence the generation and maturation of oocytes compared to control animals.

label: egg laying event infrequent
definition: The rate of the intrinsic behavioral program that serves to move fertilized eggs down the uterus, through the vulva, and out of the worm onto the substrate is reduced compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: increased acidified compartments
definition: Animals contain excess acidified intracellular compartments. These compartments are positive for indicators such as Acridine Orange as well as LysoTracker Red, in a lysosome-like manner.

label: neuron migration variant
definition: Any variation in the normal orderly movement of neurons from one site to another compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite mating efficiency eliminated
definition: Hermaphrodites do not produce cross progeny.

label: aneuploidy
definition: Any variation in the number of chromosomes in a cell compared to control.

label: pheromone induced larval display defective
definition: Animals are not induced to display surface antigens by exposure to pheromone as observed for Bristol N2 animals.

label: pharyngeal intestinal valve morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the structure or appearance of the cells that form a narrow passage connecting the posterior bulb of the pharynx to the anterior intestine compared to control. In C. elegans this valve is composed of 3 pairs of cells each forming a flattened disc-like ring and is lined by a layer of cuticle (Wormatlas).

label: obsolete reporter gene expression variant
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a cell from when it is first formed to when it becomes a mature structure when compared to control animals.

label: transient bloating
definition: Worms sporatically appear turgid or swollen as a result of an excess number of eggs being retained in the uterus.

label: starvation induced dauer formation increased
definition: Animals are more likely to form dauers under nutrient conditions that do not induce dauer entry in control animals.

label: spindle absent early emb
