definition: Early embryos lack the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis.

label: cortical blebs present
definition: Embryos display cortical protusions during cytokinesis.

label: male M lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the M precursor cell in male animals, exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: lipid modification variant
definition: Variations in the covalent alteration of one or more components (eg: fatty acids, sterols etc.) in a lipid, resulting in a change in the properties of the lipid, compared to control.

label: L1 larval development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of a newly hatched animal through the first larval molt compared to control.

label: cadmium hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to cadmium at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: head levamisole resistant
definition: The heads of animals fail to respond to the concentration of levamisole that elicits a response in control animals. In C. elegans, heads contract at >10uM for intact animals and >1uM for cut animals.

label: acetone chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of acetone. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, acetone is an attractant.

label: sister cell division timing asynchrony reduced
definition: Animals exhibit sister cells that have lost otherwise normal asynchrony of cell division timing, compared to control animals. This results in sister cells aberrantly dividing in synchrony.

label: cell division incomplete
definition: The physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells is interupted.

label: increased genetic pathway signal
definition: Any variation that increases the magnitude of a signal generated by a set of gene interactions in a given pathway, compared to control.

label: axon trajectory variant
definition: Animals display variations in the directed path taken by the axon compared to the path the nerve fiber follows in the nervous system in control animals.

label: X ray induced mitotic germ cell arrest defective
definition: Animals do not arrest mitotic germ cell division, as control animals, when treated with X-ray radiation.

label: butanone chemotaxis defective
definition: Failure to execute characteristic response to butanone compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of butanone.

label: muscle cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of muscle cells compared to control animals.

label: cell corpse digestion variant
definition: The degradation of genomic and or cellular material of the corpse does not occur at the same rate or under the same conditions as observed in control animals undergoing cell death.

label: obsolete disorganized muscle
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: halothane resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of the anesthetic halothane that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: bleach response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to bleach compared to that observed in control animals.

label: intestinal vacuole
definition: Vacuoles accumulate in the intestine.

label: isthmus corpus slippery
definition: Failure of muscle contractions in the corpus and isthmus to trap and transport bacteria posteriorly in the pharynx.

label: male mating latency variant
definition: Any variation in the length of time required for a male to find a mate and initiate the search for the vulva. In C. elegans, the latency period includes the time males spend to find a hermaphrodite and pause to press its ventral side against the surface of the hermaphrodite and initiate a backing up search for the vulva.

label: pathogen induced cell death increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to a pathogen or pathogenic cue, compared to control.

label: odorant chemosensory response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the chemosensory response to volatile organic compounds compared to control.

label: supernumerary centrosomes
definition: A cell or cell of the animal exhibits extra centrosomes (a subcellular body consisting of two centrioles embedded in a protein matrix) compared to control.

label: Variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations compared to a given control.

label: everted vulva
definition: The eversion process, in which the vulval invagination is turned inside out during the final molt, is disrupted. In C.elegans, such variations in vulval eversion are primarily due to developmental defects in the somatic gonad (and sometimes vulva).

label: response to injury variant
definition: Variations in the processes that restore integrity to a damaged tissue following an injury, compared to control.

label: germ cell death response to 5 FU resistant
definition: Germ cell death fails in response to the concentration of 5-FU that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans, in addition to cell death, 5-FU exposed animals exhibit condensed germ cell nuclei or unhealthy nuclei.

label: ammonium chloride chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of ammonium chloride. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, ammonium chloride is an attractant. NH4Cl has also been used to assay for Cl- attraction.

label: axonal degeneration
definition: Spontaneous axon breaks leading to degeneration of separated segments.

label: pathogen induced cell death reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to a pathogen or pathogenic cue, compared to control.

label: cell number decreased
definition: The number of cells in the organism is reduced compared to control animals.

label: excessive blebbing early emb
definition: Excessive shaking and movements are seen in the cell membrane or cytoplasm of one-cell or two-cell embryos.

label: inhibition of ovulation variant
definition: Any variation that alters the control mechanisms that inhibit oocyte maturation and release of a mature oocyte into the spermatheca (for subsequent fertilization), compared to control.

label: amphid physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for an amphid to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: feeding behavior variant
definition: Behavior associated with the intake of food is altered compared to control.

label: endosome biogenesis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the formation or disassembly of membrane bound organelles that traffic material between the plasma membrane and internal compartments of the cell, compared to control.

label: Q neuroblast lineage migration variant
definition: The daughters of the Q neuroblasts exhibit variation in their characteristic movements compared to control animals.

label: paralysis response to ethanol resistant
definition: Animals in the presence of ethanol continue to respond to touch under conditions when control worms have stopped responding to stimuli.

label: burrowing assay distance reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a reduction, compared to control, in the distance traveled in a burrowing assay, in which animals are placed in a tube, separated from an attractant by solid medium through which the worms can burrow. Reductions in distance traveled during the burrowing assay, when controlled for chemosensation defects, have been suggested to reflect deficits in neuromuscular efficacy of locomotion.

label: spicule insertion defective
definition: Males exhibit defects in the insertion of the male copulatory spicules into the mating partner. In C. elegan spicule insertion behavior initiates when the male cloaca contacts the vulva. During most mating encounters, the spicule tips will prod the vulva continuously until they partially penetrate, which then causes the protractors to contract completely so that the spicules extend through the vulva.

label: coelomocyte physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the coelomocyte to carry out its normal functions or activities, compared to control animals.

label: velocity of movement increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the net velocity of an animal

label: alpha amanitin resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of alpha amanitin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: DAPI staining variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the pattern of a chemical nuclear stain which is commonly used in fixed specimens and produces a bright blue label, compared to control. DAPI (4'-6-Diamidino-2-phenylindole) forms fluorescent complexes with natural double-stranded DNA (Wormatlas).

label: reduced translation initiation
definition: The rate of the process preceding formation of the peptide bond between the first two amino acids of a protein is reduced. This process includes the formation of a complex of the ribosome, mRNA, and an initiation complex that contains the first aminoacyl-tRNA.  Increase in free ribosomes (monosomes) are indicative of reduced translation initiation.

label: interphase entry defective early emb
definition: Embryos do not enter or take longer to enter first interphase compared to control.

label: germ cell compartment large
definition: Germ cell compartments are larger than that of control animals.

label: cilia mislocalized
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the placement of the microtuble-based dendritic projections in relation to the sensillum neuron, from that observed in control animals.

label: memory retention defective
definition: Animals are deficient in their recalled and repeated responses to stimuli they are exposed to during learning and memory paradigms.

label: gonad development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of the organ that produces gametes over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control.

label: somatic transgene silencing variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the homology-dependent transcriptional level silencing of the expression of exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism, in the soma, compared to control.

label: ectopic vulva
definition: Animals exhibit one or more vulvae in locations not normally found in controls.

label: presynaptic vesicle cluster variant
definition: Animals display variations in the organization, accumulation or distribution of transmitter-containing membrane-bound organelles (synaptic vesicles) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: pharyngeal pumping rate variant
definition: The number of coordinated contraction-relaxation cycles (pumps) exhibited by the pharyngeal muscle deviates from that observed for control animals.

label: DNA repair variant
definition: Any variation in the process of restoring DNA after damage.  DNA damage can be caused by a many chemical or physical agents, and this damage is repaired by a variety  of different DNA repair pathways.

label: serotonin induced pumping variant
definition: Pharyngeal pumping is not influenced by serotonin treatment in the same manner as control animals.

label: pharynx unattached
definition: The pharynx or pharyngeal muscle does not form a functional connection to the mouth or buccal cavity.

label: synaptic vesicle exocytosis variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the fusion of intracellular neurotransmitter-filled membrane-bound vesicles with the pre-synaptic membrane of the neuronal cell compared to control.

label: dauer amphid sensillum variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of any specialized chemosensory organs located on the head, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: oxygen response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to oxygen compared to that observed in control animals.

label: spermatheca absent
definition: Animals lack the somatic gonad structure that connects the distal gonad arm to the uterus.

label: thermosensory behavior variant
definition: Variations in behavior that is dependent upon the sensation of temperature, compared to control.

label: dead eggs laid
definition: Animals lay eggs that are inviable.

label: egg integrity defective early emb
definition: The structure of the egg is impaired, flawed or no longer intact.

label: L4 arrest
definition: The developmental program of the animals does not continue past the fourth larval stage (L4).

label: forward point velocity increased
definition: Animals exhibit increased velocity of forward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: protein complex organization variant
definition: The formation, organization, or stability of a protein complex is altered in comparison to corresponding complexes in control animals.

label: germ cell compartment nuclei number variant
definition: Germ cell compartments contain an an atypical number on nuclei compared to control.

label: associative learning variant
definition: Variations in the behavioral plasticity induced by the integration of two sensory signals compared to control. In C. elegans animals exhibit enhancement of butanone chemotaxis by preexposure to butanone and food.

label: microtubule depolymerization variant
definition: Any variation that alters the characteristic removal of tubulin heterodimers from one or both ends of a microtubule compared to control.

label: ectopic endoderm
definition: Animals exhibit one or more endodermal cells in locations not normally found in controls.

label: G lineages variant
definition: The descendants of the G1 or G2 exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: alimentary system development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the alimentary system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control. The alimentary system includes all the body structures involved in preparing food for absorption into the body and excretion of waste products.

label: no cuticle
definition: Animals lack the rigid external coating which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells (Wormatlas).

label: foraging hyperactive
definition: Animals extend intensity of roaming and or dwelling activity compared to control animals. In C. elegans, hyperactivity may include an increase in nose-lifts per minute.

label: gastrulation variant
definition: Variations in the process by which the germ layers become positioned in an embryo compared to control animals. Gastrulation involves the proper ingression of small groups of cells at various times into the blastocoel space.

label: dauer behavior variant
definition: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of dauer stage animals in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: spermatheca dilation defective
definition: Animals exhibit defects in any physical or chemical process involved in the dilation of the distal spermatheca which is required for the oocyte exit from the gonad arm.

label: fluoxetine hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to fluoxetine at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: synaptic vesicle tag abnormal in mechanosensory neurons
definition: The pattern of localization of presynaptic markers is disrupted compared to control animals.

label: coelomic system morphology variant
definition: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the coelomic system, compared to control. The coelom is the fluid compartment that is in contact with internal organ.

label: mitosis variant
definition: Any variation in the division of the eukaryotic cell nucleus to produce two daughter nuclei that contain the identical chromosome complement of their mother compared to control.

label: dauer excretory gland variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a pair of large cells in the head that fuse to form a single gland whose contents are released into the excretory duct through a specialized secretory membrane, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: ectopic vulva in male
definition: Formation in the male of the egg-laying organ of female and hermaphrodite nematodes. In nematodes, the vulva is formed from ventral epidermal cells during larval stages to give rise to a fully formed vulva in the adult.

label: head cavity
definition: The head contains cavities, possibly indicative of inappropriate cell death.

label: mitochondrial content increased
definition: Animals exhibit increases in the overall amount of mitochondria present in the animal, as determined by, for example, Mitotracker staining.

label: non apoptotic cell death variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the specific activation or halting of processes within a cell that occur through necrosis or programmed cell death pathways different from apoptosis, so that its vital functions markedly cease, rather than simply deteriorating gradually over time, which culminates in cell death, compared to control.

label: dopamine resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of a dopamine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: dorsal region development variant
definition: Variations in the progression of an animal's anatomy contained in the dorsal region over time, compared to control animals.

label: nuclear export defective
definition: The directed movement of substances out of the nucleus is impaired.

label: nervous system physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the nervous system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: helical cuticle
definition: Animals exhibit a helically twisted cuticle. In practice the degree of twisting is measured as the number of helical twists the alae make about anterior/posterior axis of the animal.

label: twitcher
definition: Animals exhibit spasmodic muscle twitching superimposed on normal sinusoidal motion.

label: cell gamma ray response variant
definition: Cells exhibit variations in their response to gamma ray radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: CAN cell migration variant
definition: Variation in the migration pattern of CAN neurons. In C. elegans, CAN neurons move posteriorly from their birthplace in the head to positions near the middle of the embryo.

label: embryonic morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts during any developmental stage ranging from zygote formation to hatching compared to control.

label: slow embryonic development
definition: The progression through stages between fertilization to hatching are temporally retarded.

label: accessory cell physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required by a subset of interfacial cells to carry out its normal function or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control. It can refer to socket cells, sheath cells and structural cells or their processes (Wormatlas).

label: hydroxyurea response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of hydroxyurea compared to that observed in control animals. Hydroxyurea stops DNA from being replicated.

label: male fertility variant
definition: Males exhibit variations in the time of onset or duration of the fertile period owing to differences in sperm competence and/or function compared to control animals.

label: surface coat variant
definition: The electron dense, amorphous envelope that comprises the outermost layer of the cuticle varies in composition from that observed in control animals of the same developmental stage. The integrity of the surface coat is often revealed by an altered antigenicity or biochemical make up.

label: cell migration variant
definition: Any variation in the orderly movement of a cell from one site to another.

label: sperm pseudopod physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the pseudopod of the sperm to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: reduced burst pharyngeal pumping response to light
definition: Animals exhibit a reduced burst pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that during the5-10 seconds after light exposure onset the pharyngeal pumping rate increases to a lesser extent than in controls.

label: postsynaptic component localization variant
definition: Animals display variations in the distribution of the constituents of the postsynaptic side of the active zone, compared to control animals, that are required for receiving signals from the presynaptic side.

label: carbohydrate metabolism variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of an internal store of carbohydrates within the organism or cell compared to control.

label: hyperactive egg laying
definition: Eggs are laid at an earlier stage of development, eggs are laid in the presence of inhibitors of egg laying, or the inactive phase of the egg-laying cycle is significantly shorter when compared to control.

label: W lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the W precursor cell exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: pharyngeal contraction defective
definition: Any defects in the muscle contractions that control feeding. Contractions are necessary for bacterial uptake from the surrounding environment.

label: dopamine adaptation defective
definition: Animals do not exhibit decreased responsiveness after prolonged or repeated exposure to dopamine.

label: spastic locomotion
definition: Animals exhibit uncharacteristic muscle contractions during the process by which they travel from one location to another.

label: comma arrest emb
definition: Cessation of development during the middle stage in embryogenesis of the worm in which the embryo is slightly folded within the eggshell (Wormatlas).

label: linker cell migration variant
definition: Variations in the stereotypical migration pattern of the linker cell in a developing male compared to control.

label: spindle assembly defective
definition: Cells exhibit defects in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle, the array of microtubules and associated molecules that serves to move duplicated chromosomes apart.

label: acetylcholinesterase reduced
definition: Any variation that results in a decrease of acetylcholine esterase levels, compared to control.

label: presynaptic region morphology variant
definition: Animals display variations in the structure, configuration, distribution or ratio of the components of the vesicle-filled varicosities of the synapse compared to control.

label: lead hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to lead at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: loose mitotic furrow early emb
definition: Once formed, the mitotic furrow can "slide"laterally.

label: resistant to lectin
definition: Exposure to lectin has no affect on the behavior, growth, or development of the animal compared to controls.

label: meiotic spindle assembly defective
definition: Early embryos exhibit defects in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the meiotic spindle, the array of microtubules and associated molecules that serves to move duplicated and/or homologous chromosomes apart.

label: spermatogenesis defective hermaphrodite
definition: Variations that specifically disrupt sperm production in XX hermaphrodites. By contrast, spermatogenesis in XO males remains unaffected.

label: VPC cell division precocious
definition: VPCs (vulval precursor cells) divide at an earlier stage of development compared to control animals; in C. elegans, VPCs divide in the mid-L3 stage to generate the 22 cells that comprise the vulva.

label: tumor prolapse frequency increased
definition: Animals with a tumorous germline exhibit an increased frequency of the presence of a tumor prolapse, a protrusion of tumor cells from the vulva, compared to control.

label: chromosome instability
definition: Variations in the frequencies of translocations, inversions, deletions, or gene amplifications and variations in chromosome fusion events and or chromosomal loss compared to control.

label: bis phenol A hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to bis phenol A at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure time compared to control animals.

label: eggshell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of the protective barrier which isolates the embryo from the external environment, compared to control .

label: DNA recombination variant
definition: Variations in the process by which a new genotype is formed by reassortment of genes resulting in gene combinations different from those that were present in the parents, compared to control.

label: no pharynx
definition: Embryos fail to generate cells that exhibit pharyngeal specification.

label: GABA levels variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of GABA compared to control animals at a defined stage.

label: nonanone chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of nonanone. In C. elegans, nonanone is typically a repellant.

label: blastocoel variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of the fluid-filled compartment inside the developing embryo at the onset of gastrulation over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: genetic pathway activation variant
definition: Any variation in triggering of the set of interactions occurring between a group of genes who depend on each other's individual functions in order to make the aggregate function of the network available to the cell, compared to control.

label: cleavage furrow defective
definition: Cells exhibit defects in the formation, maintenance or termination of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate during cytokinesis.

label: cell proliferation increased
definition: The processes governing the expansion of cell populations are altered compared to control animals, such that cell populations are increased.

label: vulval muscle homeostasis metabolism variant
definition: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium within the vulval muscles compared to control.

label: antimonite hypersensitivity
definition: Animals respond to antimonite at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: slowing response on food variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in modulating their locomotory rate in response to its food , compared to control. Basal slowing response refers to when well-fed animals move more slowly in the presence of bacteria than in the absence of bacteria . Second , food-deprived control animals , when transferred to bacteria , display a dramatically enhanced slowing response that ensures that the animals do not leave their newly encountered source of food.

label: magnesium homeostasis variant
definition: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of magnesium ions within an organism compared to control.

label: age dependent somatic depletion of fat
definition: A depletion of somatic, but not germline, lipid stores are observed near the end of the reproductive period.

label: intestinal cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of an intestinal cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: isoflurane hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to the anesthetic isoflurane at lower concentrations or shorter response times than control animals.

label: ventral nerve cord development variant
definition: Variations in any process whose specific outcome is the development and/or maintenance of the ventral nerve cord.

label: emetine hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to emetine at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: arecoline hypersensitive
definition: Animals respond to arecoline at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: anterior neuron migration defective
definition: The orderly movement of neurons along the anterior axis of the animal is abolished, misdirected or incomplete compared to control.

label: gene expression level high
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the intensity of expression of a gene product compared to that observed in control animals.

label: embryonic growth variant
definition: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) during the embryonic stage compared to control animals.

label: amphid sheath cell development variant
definition: Any variation in the progression of a sheath cell of the amphid sensillum over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: feminization of XX and XO animals
definition: Both hermaphrodites and males develop into fertile females.

label: intestinal microvilli variant
definition: Any variation in the formation of intestinal microvilli. Microvilli are actin-based cellular structures that form plasma membrane projections into the extracellular space and whose specialized shape provides increased cellular surface area. Microvilli are a crucial component of the terminal differentiation process for many epithelial cell types, usually ones that play an absorptive or filtering role.

label: organism gamma ray response variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in their response to gamma ray radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: garlic chemotaxis variant
definition: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of garlic compared to control. In C. elegans, garlic is typically a repellant.

label: increased susceptibility to bacterial pathogens
definition: Animals are more prone to infection by bacterial pathogens compared to control animals.

label: muscle excitability variant
definition: The extent or other quality of the excitatory postsynaptic potential (EPSP) induced by in vitro stimuli differs from that of controls.

label: active phase switch defective
definition: Activation of the active phase of egg laying is defective, leading to an abnormally long inactive phase, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: frequency of body bend variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the frequency of oscillations between adjacent body segments from that observed for control animals.

label: multivulva
definition: Multiple vulva-like protrusions are present along the ventral side of the animal. In C. elegans, this is usually a result of all six vulval precursor cells adopting primary or secondary vulval fates.

label: mianserin resistant
definition: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of mianserin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: extra neuron
definition: Animals produce an excess number of neurons compared to controls.

label: vulval invagination variant L4
definition: The characteristic Christmas-tree shaped invagination formed by the terminal vulval cells at the mid-late L4 stage is altered.

label: male mating defective
definition: Males exhibit defects in the specific actions or reactions that are associated with reproduction.

label: dwelling reduced
definition: Animals exhibit a decrease in the low-speed/high turning movement that usually restricts them to a confined region compared to control.

label: reduced viability after freezing
definition: Animals show a decrease in survivorship after thawing compared to control.

label: axon outgrowth variant
definition: Any variation in the processes that govern the extension of axons compared to control.

label: pheromone induced dauer formation enhanced
definition: Animals enter the dauer stage when exposed to lower concentrations or shorter exposure times of chemicals that induce dauer formation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: leaving assay defective
definition: Males remain on food in the absence of mates, a defect in male mate-searching behavior observed in control males.

label: pronuclear nuclear appearance defective early emb
definition: The morphology of pronuclei and nuclei are defective in the early embryo. In C. elegans, this defect is often characterized by pronuclei and nuclei that are small or missing altogether and are often accompanied by spindle defects.

label: cell endomembrane physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the composition, component distribution, or other aspect of membranes of within the cell, compared to control animals.

label: obsolete connected mitochodria muscle
definition: OBSOLETE.

label: siRNA expression variant
definition: Variations in the biogenesis and stability of the small interfering class of RNA molecules compared to control. In C. elegans these molecules are antisense to mRNA's and may be processed from long double-stranded RNA.

label: feminization of germline
definition: Hermaphrodites are transformed into fertile females; In C. elegans, XO fog animals are somatically male but produce oocytes instead of, or in addition to, sperm.

label: multiple anchor cells
definition: Animals contain more than one anchor cell. In C. elegans, presumptive ventral uterine cells undergo fate transformation and instead acquire the properties of an anchor cell (often due to defects in lateral signaling).

label: corpus morphology defective
definition: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the extended anterior region of the pharynx lying just anterior to the isthmus and terminal bulb compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: pumping absent
definition: Animals completely lack any pharyngeal pumping motion.

label: hydrogen peroxide levels increased
definition: Animals exhibit increases in steady-state levels of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) compared to control.

label: intraflagellar transport complex destabilized
definition: The intracellular complex of proteins that participates in bidirectional transport of molecules (cargo) along axonemal microtubules is not made up of or does not maintain the proper number or ratio of components as found in control animals.

label: linker cell absent
definition: The gonads of male animals do not produce the linker cell involved in guiding the developing male gonad to the sex organs in the male tail.

label: F lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the F cell (which divides only in the males) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: aging variant
definition: Any variation in an organism's decline over time from its optimal fertility and viability compared to control animals.

label: roller
definition: The body of the animal rotates around its long axis as the animal moves, causing the animal to move in a circular pattern. In liquid media, wave propogation is helical rather than planar.

label: dauer gut variant
definition: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the chain of cuboidal cells which form a central lumen lined by microvilli that allow the passage of food, compared to control. Food passes from the posterior pharynx to the intestine where it is digested and then on to the rectum which processes the waste products for excretion.

label: jerky movement
definition: Animals exhibit abrupt transitions while traveling from one location to another.

label: proctodeum morphology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the structure and organization of the chamber in the male tail that extends from the termination of four canals (vas deferens, gut, and left and right spicule channels) to just before the cloaca, from that observed in control animals.

label: meiotic DNA double strand break formation increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase the creation of double-strand breaks that occur during meiosis that may result in the initiation of meiotic recombination.

label: odorant positive chemotaxis variant
definition: Movement towards typically attractive volatile organic chemicals is altered as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, these odorants are typically sensed by the AWA and AWC neurons.

label: pseudocleavage exaggerated early emb
definition: Embryos have more pronounced pseudocleavage than normal.

label: turning frequency increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the frequency of execution of the behavior by which the animal alters its trajectory of movement compared to control, excluding shifts from forward to backward movements (this is reversal).

label: cuticle attachment variant
definition: Any variation in the attachment of the rigid external coating (which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells) to the outer body of an animal compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: histone acetylation variant
definition: The pattern or state of acetylation modifications of histones varies from that of controls.

label: reproductive longevity extended
definition: Animals continue to produce progeny significantly past the time reproduction stops in control animals.

label: endo siRNA production variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the length or amount of any endogenous small interfering RNA molecule populations compared to control.

label: X linked gene expression enhanced
definition: Levels of transcripts associated with genes on the X chromosome are increased compared to control.

label: germline precursor cell morphology variant
definition: Any variation in the morphological appearance of germline precursor cells compared to control animals.

label: gamma ray induced apoptosis increased
definition: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to the nucleic acid damaging agent, gamma irradiation, compared to control.

label: body posture wavelength decreased
definition: Animals exhibit variations in body posture caused by a decrease in the distance between repeating units of a wave pattern compared to control animals. In C. elegans, characteristic sinusoidal body posture is sinusoidal.

label: epithelial system physiology variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the epithelial system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: intestinal cell division failure
definition: The physical partitioning and separation of an intestinal cell into daughter cells is abolished.

label: spontaneous mutation rate increased
definition: Animals accumulate a greater number of genetic lesions than control animals in the absence of an externally controlled mutagen. In C. elegans, this is often measured by observing the number of reversion events of a known mutant gene function over a couple generations.

label: exploded through vulva
definition: The animal is ruptured at the vulva and displays an extrusion of internal organs at the site of rupture.

label: oocytes stacked
definition: Oocytes are found one on top of the other in the dorsal to ventral orientation in the gonad.

label: B lineage variant
definition: The descendants of the B cell (which divides only in the males) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: starvation suppressed pumping defective
definition: Animals deprived of food do not exhibit a decrease in pumping rate similar to that observed for control animals.

label: egg laying variant
definition: Animals exhibit variations in the stage of eggs laid, egg laying cycle, number of eggs or egg laying in response to stimuli compared to control.
